name: The Bellows' Studio Loft  (3rd floor apartment)
summary: Famous American artist George Bellows home with studio loft apartment, features a completely private oasis for two with private bath, kitchenette, dining and sitting areas. Walk to downtown with easy access to the freeway and public transportation. The homeowners are both artists and guests will enjoy the art that adorns the walls. And the gardens and patio which are a quiet oasis from city life.
space: This historic home features a totally private and secure studio loft apartment, which is accessed through the spacious entry hallway. It has sitting and dining areas, bedroom with a queen size bed, kitchenette and private full bath. A quiet retreat with plenty of light and great views.

neighborhood_overview: A historic neighborhood of beautiful victorian homes on lovely tree lined streets, located just a short walk from the downtown, the Main Library, Art Museum and Topiary Park (great for walking or jogging).   There are plenty of places to eat, drink and have fun only a few steps away ( bakery, coffee house, pizza parlor, tavern, restaurant and more.)
notes: we have wifi access for your phone and computer as well as cable TV.
transit: The home has plenty of on street parking with easy access to the freeway and public transportation and is only a 10 minute ride from the airport.  Bicycle and car2go rentals are also available in the area.
access: The back yard features gardens with several sitting areas and a pond.  Guests are welcome to enjoy this quiet oasis from city life.
interaction: The owners are both artists and would love to share their historic home with you.
house_rules: No unauthorized guests or late night partying. No smoking. Sorry no pets .
host_about:
My husband Eric and I are both artists, sharing studio space in our house. We have 2 daughters and 3 grandchildren, all of whom live in Columbus.  I've been a yoga teacher since 1988. I have taught at Yoga on High since it's inception in 2000 and earned my certification from Yoga Alliance of ERYT 500 at Yoga on High. I love sharing this ancient practice with all kinds of people. I have seen it have profound effects on people's lives. It is an honor and a responsibility for which I am very grateful. 
 Eric and I have lived in this historic home for over 35 years, in what we consider the best neighborhood in the city, Olde Towne. We love sharing our home with friends and now airbnb guests. We enjoy walking in the woods, gardening, biking, kayaking, reading and, of course, practicing yoga. 
We also love to travel. We've been told we are easy guests. We like to take care of ourselves and not add unduly to our hosts workload. Car camping is a favorite vacation of ours.
 I'd say our airbnb hosting style is also casual: I try to think of anything a guest might need and supply it, so they can have a relaxed stay with us. We have maps of the neighborhood and menus for the local cafes and the bakery in a notebook in The Loft. We try to help out with rides when we can. We have a table in The Loft that is perfect for working or dining. A guest set up her sewing machine up there.
My favorite quote is from Emmanuel: "Your life is not your master, it is your child." Let us host your next visit to Columbus as you create your perfect visit.

name: Historic Home 5min CMH & Downtown
space: Just two exits from the Columbus Airport, multiple  private bedrooms and bathrooms available in ~3,500 SF shared, historic house in Woodland Park. Hardwood floors, meticulously clean, huge yard with vegetable garden, apiary and flowers, screened in porch, separate covered patio, fully renovated kitchen with granite counters and stainless appliances. The kitchen even boasts an original 1920's home economics table as the island.  There is tons of light. The living room and dining room even have an original Rookwood Tile fireplace.  A few blocks from Franklin Park with quick access to 670, bus lines, and downtown. It's about a 10 minute drive to OSU, downtown, or the Convention Center. Also, very close to Bexley and Capital. Washer, dryer and tons of storage room available. Off-street parking in the driveway is reserved for guests. We have one short hair cat, Chairman Mao. Please message for more information.  Availability of rooms, pricing and level of privacy varies depending on the day

neighborhood_overview: I like to refer to Columbus as the biggest small town I've ever been to.  So, while it may seem like a big city and even have all the diversity of a larger city, it is remarkably safe and quaint.  That said, our home is in what some call a "gentrifying" or "revitalizing" neighborhood.  It's not for everyone - but we love it and call it home.  Take the time to say good morning to the neighbors and kids walking down the street, and you'll quickly see what a friendly and diverse area it is.  You might meet Ms. Kay, our neighbor who was the first black family to purchase a home in this previously segregated area, or you might meet James and David, a lively couple two doors down.  Almost everyone knows us for riding bikes or hosting some of the best shin-digs around. Definitely check out the Conservatory and also the restaurants at 18th and Oak!  Also, if you make it to the Columbus Museum of Art, you might note that Emerson Burkhart's house is on our block - the corner of Woodland and Rich
transit: Columbus is a car city.  Although there a buses, they aren't particularly convenient... so, consider driving.  We're pretty central to everywhere, and a few minutes from the highway, which gets you across town easily.  UBER is also great in Columbus, and fairly affordable, especially for big events where you might have to pay to park anyways.
access: The house is yours!  If you need anything in the kitchen, just look around.  Same for bathroom items, extra towels, etc.   Please be considerate if staying in a room that has personal items in the closets or dressers - obviously those spaces aren't intended for guests. My office is used as such, so feel free to check out the record collection or my family photos and knick-knacks, but please respect my piles.  :)
interaction: Usually one of us is around to assist.  If not, someone is always nearby.  I'm always available via email and texting!
house_rules: Shoes off at the door and slippers on!  We provide down slippers for use by all of our guests, but do require that shoes are removed upon entry.  I love my hardwood floors and oriental rugs too much.   Otherwise, we're a fun, lively group.  A lengthy email with every thing you ever wanted to know about staying at Parkwood, including access information, will be sent 24 hours prior to your arrival.  Happy to answer any other questions prior to arrival!
host_about:
I'm a 37 year old professional in the affordable housing industry.  I worked on central city redevelopment for the past 8 years and love cycling, cities, and of course, my 16 year old daughter.

I currently attend law school at the Ohio State University where I specialize in International Law and Real Estate.

neighborhood_overview: Welcome to German Village, one of the most storied urban neighborhoods in the U.S. We are an energetic, eclectic mashup of modern lifestyles enjoying the best shops, restaurants and parks found anywhere against a backdrop of brick streets and houses listed on the National Register of Historic Places. German Village is not just preserved architecture from the 1800s; it is the aggregation of more than 130 years of the stories of area people, families and businesses. Character lives on! • Listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1974. • In 2006, German Village was made a Preserve America Community by the White House. • The New York Post listed German Village and Columbus among the Top 5 Travel Spots in the World in 2007. • Travel site (website hidden) lists German Village as a Top 3 “Fodor’s Choice” pick. • We are a 2011 designee as one of the country’s 10 Great Neighborhoods, recognized by the American Planning Association. • We are one of the New York Times’ top rated,

transit: Getting around … Car. Car2go car-share. Bus. Bike (bike-share stations located at Schiller park and near Starbucks in Third St.) Taxi. Foot!

neighborhood_overview: Centrally located off the Livingston Corridor on the Near East Side (a few miles SE of Broad and High, the epicenter of Columbus), Old Oaks is Columbus's first and most well-preserved streetcar suburb. The neighborhood is famous not just for its architecture and history, but also for being one of the last neighborhoods in America where we know our neighbors. Each Wednesday, a different neighbor hosts a social hour on their porch and close to 30 neighbors stop by to catch up with one another. So bizarre is this in modern America that we were featured in the Washington Post for it*.  My home is central to most attractions in town, but is within walking distance to Children's Hospital. It neighbors German Village, Old Town East, Franklin Park and downtown, and is a short distance to the Short North, the OSU campus, Grandview and other central neighborhoods. Also a short bike ride from CCAD and Columbus State if you happen to be visiting either of those campuses.  For more on the Old Oaks
notes: If you stay throughout the week over the summer, I strongly encourage you to attend Wednesdays on the Porch, my neighborhood's weekly gathering.
transit: Uber and Lyft are both available. It's about $8 to the short north, to give you some idea. Bus routes to downtown, where you can connect to get anywhere in the city, are a block away.  Taxis are a phone call away (It's about $8 to get downtown, $12 to the Short North, $15 to the OSU campus). Columbus's bikeshare program (CoGo Bikeshare) has a hub about a ten minute walk east by the hospital.  The recently launched carshare program, Car2Go, has cars available in the area as well. You can walk to Old Town East destinations, German Village, or Franklin Park, bike anywhere, etc.
access: The guest bathroom features a standing tiled shower and a jetted whirlpool tub if you need to wind down from a day on the town. The kitchen (note: not my groceries) is available for your use as well if you prefer to dine in rather than take in some local cuisine from one of our many popular restaurants. There is a large porch that overlooks the boulevard for you to enjoy.  - Short-term guests are NOT permitted to use my laundry facilities.  - Guests are not permitted to use the studio/music room unless special arrangements are made with me personally. - Smaller group reservations will not have access to the master suite.
interaction: In addition to the lovely home, by booking with me, you also gain access to an insider's view of Columbus. I have lived here since 1999 and have friends who have lived here their whole lives who comment that I know more about the city than they ever knew possible. I am well tuned-in to events going on in the city, and can recommend restaurants or attractions to suit any taste. If you like to explore, I can show you parts of this town most don't even know exist (you'll see one such area just by staying with me).
house_rules: - You break it, you buy it - No smoking indoors. - No littering (including cigarette butts) outdoors.  - No Shoes! - Alarm is to be set upon leaving the property (you will be given a code).  - The music room is off-limits unless agreed upon otherwise in a
host_about:
I'm a professional writer and marketer located in Columbus, OH. I am originally from WV, but moved here many moons ago to attend The Ohio State University and have since made this my home. I know nearly everything there is to know about Columbus, and if you're looking for more than a place to lay your head, I'm the host you want when visiting this city.

I spend most of my spare time reading, writing, running, dancing or riding my bicycle. I also enjoy a good happy hour and live shows.

name: Charming 1BR Apt in Clintonville
summary: Fantastic 1BR apartment located in the South Clintonville/North University District area, minutes from OSU or downtown. It is on the ground floor of a lovely 1926 4-unit brick building.  It's beautifully furnished and is ideal for a single or couple who are visiting or relocating to Columbus.
space: The apartment has hardwood floors, wood panel doors, double-hung windows with storm windows and screens, and it has the original 1926 bath and kitchen fixtures.  The kitchen has a full-sized gas stove, a small built-in microwave, a dark wood countertop, a hidden drop-down breakfast table, and a hidden drop-down ironing board. It is equipped with everything you need (toaster, coffee maker, plates, glasses, cups, pots, pans, silverware, and an assortment of utensils) to cook any sort of meal.  The adjoining hall space functions as a continuation of the kitchen and contains a full-sized refrigerator, a narrow hutch, and a utility/pantry closet.  Linens are provided for the bedroom, the bath, and the kitchen, with extras stored inside the utility closet. The bedroom has a queen-sized bed, and the bathroom has single-handle shower and lavatory faucets.  The living room has a decorative fireplace and a 40" Smart TV.  There is an elegant formal dining room with a small antique desk and wirele

neighborhood_overview: This is a wonderful vibrant neighborhood with a mix of rental units and private residences.  There is a ravine park within easy walking distance and an assortment of shops and restaurants on Indianola.  It's a quick drive to High Street and its many shops (including a Giant Eagle supermarket and a CVS Pharmacy), and access to either the I-71 or the 315 freeway is quite close.
notes: Minimum rental period is three nights at $85/night.  Maximum occupancy is two persons. Reduced rate available for Long-term rentals of 3 months or more.  This is a non-smoking apartment, and no pets are allowed. It is not suitable for children.
transit: A city bus line runs in front of the apartment.  It travels primarily south and north and will easily get you to downtown or to Worthington, with transfers available to other directions.  An OSU bus line runs just south of the apartment with a stop 3 blocks away, at Clinton and Indianola.
access: Guests will have one designated parking space at the back of the apartment in a carport/garage structure.  This structure is somewhat small and will accommodate most cars as long as you pull in straight and not at an angle. If your car is particularly large, there is alternate parking available on Indianola Avenue about 1/4 block north of the apartment. There is a private entry to the apartment from the back.  A washer and dryer are available in the basement of the building.
interaction: I live about a block from this apartment and am available to solve any problems pretty quickly.  I have recently retired from my job at OSU.
house_rules: Three of the four apartments in this building are rented to long-term tenants. Please respect their needs by avoiding any loud or boisterous behavior at any hour, and particularly during late hours.
host_about: I have lived in Columbus off and on since coming here to attend Ohio State University in the 60's.  I have a degree in Architecture from OSU, but my real interest has always been in renovations. I have a son who lives in San Francisco and I love to visit there several times a year.  My husband and I have 3 grandchildren - one in California and two in Michigan.  I recently retired from OSU after working there for 18 years.

name: Urban Oasis near Short North, OSU - Free WiFi
summary: Victorian Village Guest House is a private guest suite located in the carriage house on the host's property. You will be the only guest here and are invited to enjoy our patios and garden.  Our location is super convenient and walkable.
space: Built in 2005, Victorian Village Guest House is a dramatic loft suite in the carriage house adjacent to an 1895 Queen Anne home. It includes 850 square feet of living space tastefully furnished with antiques and modern amenities including a bedroom with queen sized bed, bathroom, great room with soaring 17 foot ceilings, a complete kitchen and en-suite laundry.  A twin day bed and twin trundle bed in the great room add sleeping for two additional guests.  The suite can accommodate 3 - 4 people. Guests can expect all the luxuries of an upscale hotel and all the comforts of home.  The guest house includes bath amenities from Paris, spa robes and complimentary coffee, tea, juice, soda and bottled water.  Guests will also enjoy a welcome amenity from award-winning dessert boutique Pistacia Vera. You will be the only guests on the property and will enjoy private access separate from the owners' home.   Located in Victorian Village on historic Neil Avenue just minutes from downtown Columbus

neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village is an historic urban neighborhood nestled in between the vibrant Short North Arts District and the campus of The Ohio State University. It is a highly walkable neighborhood.  Shops and galleries, parks, multi-use fitness trail, restaurants and sports venues are within a short walk of the guest house.
notes: The guest suite is in the carriage house on the host's property. Below the guest suite is the host's garage. You may hear the sound of the automated garage door opening during your stay. Hosts are mindful of guest's privacy and do their best not to open/close the garage door during the wee hours! Please make sure you look at the photos regarding the sleeping arrangements that our guest suite offers! The guest suite has very open loft-style architecture and there are no doors to the bedroom. The wall that separates the bedroom from the great room is more like a giant headboard. There is also a twin daybed with a twin trundle bed in the great room. At most, our guest suite can accommodate 3 to 4 people. We do not allow guests to bring in air mattresses, cots, sleeping bags, etc. nor do we permit them to sleep on the sofa since it is not a sofa bed.  We want guests to be sure they know what the sleeping arrangements are before they book in order to insure they have an exceptional stay! If
transit: COTA bus service is available a half block from the guest house. Car2Go, CoGo Bike Sharing, Uber and taxi service are all available in the neighborhood.  Unrestricted, on-street parking is available in front of the guest house. The neighborhood is well-lit and has sidewalks on most streets.
access: Guests will have access to the guest suite and are invited to enjoy our patios and gardens.  Guests will access the property from Neil Avenue and go through the front and side gate, which are always unlocked.
interaction: The hosts are always in town and on-site when you are staying at Victorian Village Guest House and are available to assist you and insure your stay is enjoyable and hassle-free.  You may call or text Lisa or you may also knock on the door of the main house where the hosts live if you need anything at any time during your stay.
house_rules: We do not permit guests to host any type of events, parties, business meetings or entertain others while at Victorian Village Guest House.   We do not allow any type of video or photo shoots on the property. We do not allow pets of any type and regret that we are not able to accommodate service animals.  We regret that our property is not accessible/ADA compliant.  We do not permit smoking in the guest suite; however, guests may smoke on the patio and we will be happy to provide an ashtray.  Guests may not use any type of incense or scented candles in the guest suite.  Please consult our guest agreement located on our property's dedicated website for further details about "house rules."
host_about:
I'm a former banker who is now an entrepreneur. I love being self-employed in the tourism and hospitality industry as a guesthouse owner and host. I also curate art exhibits for a local university, setting up six exhibitions each year with local artists. 

I'm a big foodie who enjoys dining out, trying new restaurants and local taverns and brew pubs. I love cooking, home-keeping, gardening, collecting art and antiques and rescuing cats! Being a Certified Tourism Ambassador and an Airbnb host is the most fun job I've ever had.

neighborhood_overview: My home is a spacious, fully remodeled with modern updates, 2400 square foot American Foursquare located on a beautiful boulevard in the historic Old Oaks neighborhood of Columbus, Ohio. You can look this up and coming hood up on the web. There's nothing like it! Centrally located off the Livingston Corridor on the Near East Side (a few miles SE of Broad and High, the epicenter of Columbus), Old Oaks is Columbus's first and most well-preserved streetcar suburb. The neighborhood is famous not just for its architecture and history, but also for being one of the last neighborhoods in America where we know our neighbors. Each Wednesday, a different neighbor hosts a social hour on their porch and close to 30 neighbors stop by to catch up with one another. So bizarre is this in modern America that we were featured in the Washington Post for it*. Old Oaks is central to most attractions in town, but is within walking distance to Nationwide Children's Hospital, so it may be of particular intere
transit: I give a detailed guide to confirmed guests with extensive tips and services about getting around Columbus. Again, I can pretty much guarantee no one does it better or knows more. I can tell you a taxi that will be there in three minutes. I share the secret pretty readily, but not to just any ole body!
access: All common areas and 2nd floor bedrooms. The master bedroom is only available to parties of 9 or more by special request.
interaction: I will interact with my guests as much or little as they like. I am an expert on all things Columbus. Some former guests call me Mr. Columbus! I can guide you around town to the hottest spots, best restaurants, trendiest restaurants (not always the best!), etc. And if you need a tour guide, we can make that happen. Brewery tours, city tours, neighborhood tours, home tours, historic tours, I can build'em all at your request.

I'm a professional writer and marketer located in Columbus, OH. I am originally from WV, but moved here many moons ago to attend The Ohio State University and have since made this my home. I know nearly everything there is to know about Columbus, and if you're looking for more than a place to lay your head, I'm the host you want when visiting this city.

I spend most of my spare time reading, writing, running, dancing or riding my bicycle. I also enjoy a good happy hour and live shows.

neighborhood_overview: Beautiful, cheerful, friendly, safe and quiet neighborhood 10-15 minutes drive from downtown and campus, and, the lovely Como park, Park of Roses with bike/walk trail right out of my back door. The house is located 20-25 minutes walk to OSU stadium. Perfect location for getting an urban fix for yourself, and then coming home and relaxing in a quiet area.
notes: The cooling system in the house is window ACs.
transit: North High St. bus stop is just a 7 minutes walk from the house. The bus number 2 takes you Downtown, OSU campus, Columbus Conventional Center, Nationwide Arena in approximately 20-30 minutes and anywhere else in Columbus via transfer.  The bus schedule can be found on COTA website or in the welcome book in the house. So you don't need a car to get around.  Uber is reliable and affordable. If you are returning late Uber will take you here from downtown for about $10-$14. Parking. If you travel in the car, there is plenty of space to safely park in the private spot in the back of the house or on the street. Columbus has a very popular bicycle share program (CoGo, you can download the app) with convenient locations all over Columbus.
access: The bicycles are available if you want to get around neighborhood that way or simply to take a ride in the Olentangy trail that runs closeby. The key to unlock bicycles and the tire pump are by the front door next to the TV. Feel free to borrow books during your stay. The Wi-Fi is provided as well, the password is on top of the guest book. HDMI channel on TV has Netflix, or simply log into your preferred channel via ROKU, just remember to log out after you leave.
interaction: Call or text any time throughout your stay. Please address any questions about the house within first 24 hours of your arrival, so I can fix them and you can enjoy your stay. This is the whole house rental. I am not at the house during your stay.

Welcome to Columbus, where we have a lot to see and to do. I enjoy learning and speaking new languages, listening music and reading books. My son is studying in Germany, and we love to travel. I will do my best to make sure you have a very enjoyable stay!

host_about: We're Bryan & Catherine, a married couple with a love for entrepreneurship, interior design, travel, and QT with family & friends.  We moved to Columbus from NYC in 2012 in search of a better quality of life, and purchased our first home as a part of our move.  We spent a few years updating it and adding special touches to it, and through that process realized our mutual passion for design, renovation, and working together. neighborhood_overview: This is the most desirable neighborhood and creative heart of Columbus. The house sits two blocks off of High Street in the heart of the Short North and Italian Village close to an incredible selection of restaurants, coffee shops, pubs, lounges, galleries, stores, parks and bike paths. Walk to the North Market, Nationwide Arena (NHL Blue Jackets and concerts), Huntington Park (MLB Indians AAA Team) and Express Live concert venue. Ohio State campus and the Horseshoe are minutes away. Free downtown COTA Circulator bus picks up and drops off at the end of Russell Street. Port Columbus airport is less than a 10 minute cab or Uber away.
notes: Amazing windows, natural light and views facing all directions from inside and outside on the 1st and 4th floor patios. The house has a beautiful red oak and steel rail stairwell tower spanning all 4 floors but is not wheelchair accessible. Experience the unique sounds of the city and delicate breeze from the 4th floor patio that also becomes a great vista for Red, White and Boom fireworks for the 4th of July. Our home is strictly non-smoking, non-pets and drug-free.
transit: The house is close to bus routes and the free COTA Circulator picks up and drops off near the corner of Russell and High Street. Uber is typically to your door in 3-5 minutes. Access to city and park bike paths are all close by. There are also several bike rental stands within a short walk of the house.
access: Guests will be provided with lockbox access to keys and have access to the entire home, rooftop deck, 1st floor deck and one off street parking space in the driveway. The garage is used for storage and not accessible to guests.
interaction: At check in and checkout (if needed) and available throughout guests' stay via phone or text to help with questions, reservations, directions and any other special requests.
house_rules: We would expect you to treat our home like it was your own and care for the use of the home, furniture, amenities and grounds. Please inquire about single night stays, additional dates, special events and extended stays shown as "not available" on the calendar. Absolutely no smoking, drugs, pets or loud parties. Please let us know about your stay by leaving a positive review on AirBnB. We prefer that the booking guest(s) have positive feedback and be at least 25 years old or older.

neighborhood_overview: Clintonville is centrally located, a mile from OSU, has excellent bus access, and is bike-friendly. The neighborhood is dense and urban but generally quiet, especially during the week.  There are a lot of new places that I look forward to discovering along with guests.   My neighbors have been very friendly and graciously welcomed me to the neighborhood.  There is a really picturesque park called Glen Echo Ravine a few blocks away.  We get a lot of birds and other various wildlife from the surrounding nature.
notes: The cats are Hazel (black female) & Peanut (tan male).  They are what I consider "aggressively friendly."  They are free to go in and out as they please.   I am friends with neighbors on all sides.  If I'm not around and you need me, let me know and they can help out.

neighborhood_overview: I am located in a diverse, URBAN NEIGHBORHOOD built in the mid 1800's. In its day, it was the about the best real estate you could buy and represented the optimism of a growing city. For old house aficionados, I'm surrounded by interesting architecture, some outstanding restorations, and lots of potential .  Olde Towne East/King Lincoln is one of the city’s largest historic neighborhoods,  over 50 architectural styles can be found here. The diversity of the neighborhood and its many charms include beautiful homes, impressive churches, great restaurants , Central location,  nearby Franklin Park Conservatory and The Columbus Art Museum makes this neighborhood extra special , I know I'm a little bias :-)
notes: This is a 3rd floor level apartment which means there are stairs to negotiate. There is a sturdy handrail, but for some potential guests who need handicap accessibility, this unit may not be appropriate.
transit: The apt. is located 2 minutes  from the interstate. 15 min. from the airport. COGo Bike sharing is located in the neighborhood for bike rentals.  Bus stop is less than 100 ft. from the apt. $5.00 Uber ride downtown.  $8-15 to and from  the airport.
access: Guest space is completely separate from the owner's quarters, so there's little ambiguity over what will constitute "your" space.   Guest unit has a private entrance opened by means of a keypad. Each guest receives a unique key-code. Guest will have access to backyard and deck
interaction: Generally, I am in and out, much of the time  but available by phone. If something out of the ordinary occurs, I'll let you know. I want your stay in Columbus to be pleasant. If you want your privacy, you'll have it. If you want recommendations or advice about things to see and do, I'll be happy to offer them.

neighborhood_overview: The Arena District is Columbus' most popular neighborhood featuring sports, entertainment, and food & drink.  Sports: Experience the rush of NHL Hockey with the Columbus Blue Jackets at Nationwide Arena. Or hit Huntington Park for the Indians Triple-A affiliate, the Columbus Clippers. Entertainment: With four music venues within walking distance, including Nationwide Arena and Express Live, you can check out an up-and-coming band or see the world’s biggest acts nearly every night of the week. Nightlife: Living in one of Forbes’ Five Secret Foodie Cities, complete with Columbus’ best nightlife right outside the door, means your biggest problem will be deciding where to start—and who to join you.
transit: It's easy to get around Columbus. There are lots of great options to get around the city from public transportation to car sharing services.

neighborhood_overview: A peaceful wooded sanctuary feel while being extremely close to many different attractions.  JP Morgan Chase: 5 mins Otterbein University: 5 mins Ohio State University: 20 mins Ohio Wesleyan University: 20 mins Polaris Mall: 5 mins Easton: 20 mins Sailing or walking at Hoover: 5 mins Boating, hiking, mountain biking at Alum Creek State Park: 5 mins
notes: We are a couple in our early 60's. We love family, friends, offering hospitality, and meeting new people.  Our goal is to offer people a private indoor & outdoor space to retreat and experience rest while feeling safe and enjoying themselves. We offer a reasonable rate hoping that it will allow people to stay a little longer in a space that feels like home and that they will in turn take care of it like it is their home.  If you choose to come know that we look forward to hosting you!
transit: We are just off of Gemini/Polaris at I-71.  With no traffic (outside of the rush hours (which are 7:00-8:00 am and 5-6pm) we are 5 minutes off of I-71.
access: This is a private entry, private studio, private outdoor space environment that is attached to our home.  You will park up close to the little fence at the end of the driveway and go down the steps following the sidewalk to your private patio and private studio. We will send you your own entry code the day before your arrival.  We change the codes for each guest (taking off previous guest codes) and keep a list of them so that if you return you will more than likely receive your previous entry code. You will also have your own private fire pit with seating, wood & a starter brick.  If you have children there is a swing set that we would be thrilled for them to use which includes a baby swing. Our private studio is an ideal space for extended stay lodging due to you will have a large walk-in closet that includes two dressers. You will also have your own full size washer and dryer and large refrigerator & freezer.
interaction: If you need us then we will make ourselves available but if you are looking for peaceful & private retreat experience then you will definitely experience that. We will give you our mobile numbers so that you can text or call should you have any questions.
house_rules: Our goal is to offer a retreat or lodging that exists in sanctuary type of environment so that people will feel comfortable, safe, experience peace and find rest.  Because of this we do not allow unauthorized guests or extreme late night partying. You may smoke on the patio or at the fire pit; just not inside.
host_about: We are a professional working couple in our early 60's.  We love family, friends, and hosting people at our home.  Our goal is to provide a peaceful comfortable space for our guests so that they can feel safe, find the rest they may need, feel at home, and fully enjoy themselves. Addison works for a a corporation in downtown Columbus. Teresa is a mental health therapist counseling and coaching individuals, marriages, & families.

description: Deluxe room in a fabulous house with a great location, minutes from downtown, the Short North, Capital University, Columbus State, &OSU. Fully renovated Victorian home in the heart of the city.  Hardwood floors, walk-in closet, & soft sheets. Living room, dining room, kitchen, 1st floor laundry, 2 full bathrooms, & extra large patio. Hulu+ and Netflix included on Smart TV. I live in the home and am readily available, especially nights and weekends. Historic centrally-located neighborhood, with more than one thousand uniquely styled homes, representing over 50 unique architectural styles. At the beginning of the last century, people chose to live here for social status. Today, residents choose to live here for the unique styling of the houses and their appreciation of the diverse community.  You'll find this neighborhood is pedestrian-friendly and just minutes to The Columbus Metropolitan Library, The Columbus Museum of Art, Franklin University, Capitol University Law School, and Columb
neighborhood_overview: Historic centrally-located neighborhood, with more than one thousand uniquely styled homes, representing over 50 unique architectural styles. At the beginning of the last century, people chose to live here for social status. Today, residents choose to live here for the unique styling of the houses and their appreciation of the diverse community.  You'll find this neighborhood is pedestrian-friendly and just minutes to The Columbus Metropolitan Library, The Columbus Museum of Art, Franklin University, Capitol University Law School, and Columbus College of Art & Design. Downtown Columbus is easily accessible by bike or public transport. City, county, state and federal government agencies, several national banks, insurance companies, and major corporate headquarters are all easily accessible.
notes: There is an adorable chocolate lab on the premises. He has his own room, but he loves to play with guests.  Gay friendly
transit: Getting around is easy as there is convenient access to freeways and buses. There are several bus lines within 1 block. Renting a car is recommended but not necessary. Car2go vehicles are readily available for by-the-hour rentals and their cars park for free at meters.  GoGo Bike Share rents bikes by the day and has multiple bike stands in the midtown and downtown areas.  Port Columbus airport (CMH) is a short 15 minute drive.
access: Living room, dining room, kitchen, 1st floor laundry, 2 full bathrooms, & extra large patio. Hulu+ and Netflix included on Smart TV.
interaction: I live in the home and am readily available, especially nights and weekends.
house_rules: Relax and make this your home away from home.  Our only expectation is that you will treat our home with the same care and respect you would your own.  Please be sure to read and follow the instructions in the House Manual for managing the apps for the alarm and the smartlock.  No over-night visitors, pets, or smoking, please.
host_about:
I am a fun-loving traveler who appreciates good design, food, and cocktails. 

My favorite place to visit so far has been Berlin. It is surprisingly affordable, there is tremendous history there, and the people are so welcoming. 

In terms of my hosting style, I want to make sure my guests have a good stay, but I try to be unobtrusive. So, you may not see me around a lot, but I am available if you need assistance. I make an effort to be home when guests arrive, schedule permitting, so that I can give them a tour and find out if there is something they need. 

Architecture and design are hobbies and I want my home to reflect that. I spend a lot of time [and money :( ] making my home comfortable and we'll-appointed. My goal for the guest room is to have guests feel as though they are staying in a well-designed hotel room.

space: The home overlooks a beautiful ravine, with a small creek out back. You'll often see wildlife coming through the property, such as deer, lots of birds and an occasional fox!
description: Beautiful, bright, modern and cozy 4 bedroom home in a historic neighborhood in Worthington, Ohio that is inspired by Frank Lloyd Wright. A one of a kind neighborhood. Ravine view, fireplace, gourmet kitchen, the works! A quiet and peaceful retreat! The home overlooks a beautiful ravine, with a small creek out back. You'll often see wildlife coming through the property, such as deer, lots of birds and an occasional fox!  Guests will have access to private parking, two wonderful and spacious decks for your morning coffee or an evening glass of wine. Both overlook a beautiful ravine with a creek. Guests can also enjoy a fire pit out on the back patio, roast marshmallows, and enjoy our beautiful Ohio sunsets. As much or as little as you desire. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is architecturally unique, with 50+ homes built in the style of Frank-Lloyd Wright's Usonian style. It is listed on the National Registry of Historic Places. Just walking around the neighborhood and enjoying the unique homes is a treat in and of itself!  Just minutes from downtown Worthington, which features quaint shops, a wine shop, an ice cream shop, two pubs, wonderful food, and a Saturday farmer's market in the summer. Downtown Worthington is a nice 10 minute walk through beautiful tree-lined streets; or, if you prefer, a 60 second drive. :)
transit: Conveniently located! Close to bus lines, 5 minutes from the freeway and the outerbelt. 15 - 20 minutes from downtown, the airport and pretty much anything else you want to get to in Columbus.
access: Guests will have access to private parking, two wonderful and spacious decks for your morning coffee or an evening glass of wine. Both overlook a beautiful ravine with a creek. Guests can also enjoy a fire pit out on the back patio, roast marshmallows, and enjoy our beautiful Ohio sunsets.
interaction: As much or as little as you desire. The home is yours while you're here, and I am always a phone call or a few minutes away if needed. I've lived in Columbus all my life, and I'm happy to provide lots of local suggestions for entertainment, the best places to eat, and fun out-of-the-way things to do that you won't see in the travel guides.
house_rules: We would like to rent the home to a family or small group of friends looking for a quiet getaway in Columbus. The neighborhood is calm and peaceful, and we cannot rent the home for: - Weddings - Wedding/bridal showers - Baby showers - Work events - Family gatherings/reunion parties - Bachelor parties - Bachelorette parties - Etc.

name: Comfy Room, Quiet Neighborhood. Must love dogs!
summary: This is a light airy bedroom with a double bed, desk/dresser & a rocking chair. Empty closet, full length mirror. Quiet, clean space. Shared bathroom across the hall. Friendly dogs & lint rollers included at no extra charge!
space: Large open room, with plenty of natural light on a south facing window. Ceiling fan, new soft carpet and a cat sleeping on your bed if you forget to keep the door closed. :)
description: This is a light airy bedroom with a double bed, desk/dresser & a rocking chair. Empty closet, full length mirror. Quiet, clean space. Shared bathroom across the hall. Friendly dogs & lint rollers included at no extra charge! Large open room, with plenty of natural light on a south facing window. Ceiling fan, new soft carpet and a cat sleeping on your bed if you forget to keep the door closed. :) Kitchen, laundry in basement if you need it, back patio in summer months and we have a warm comfortable family room with TV and Netflix etc. I'm home some evenings, good parts of the weekends, and I'm always around at dinner and breakfast to take care of the dogs! I have a grown son in town who shows up to fix peoples cars in my garage-- you'll recognize him by his height, being covered in grease and a big smile. I'm on a dead end street in a no-outlet, low-traffic little area with lots of green around in the summer. The street has a wooded, undeveloped area at the end, but we are right in the
neighborhood_overview: I'm on a dead end street in a no-outlet, low-traffic little area with lots of green around in the summer. The street has a wooded, undeveloped area at the end, but we are right in the city. The general area of Columbus is not exactly the suburbs, :-) but I've lived in this house for more than a dozen years and have loved being here.
notes: Please do not book my rooms if you do not like dogs, do not like dog hair or dogs barking at people who come to the door. I don't know how to stress this enough, they are quiet at night but this is a house with dogs. Dogs are a chocolate lab, very friendly, and a gray shepherd mix, a little more protective, but friendly once she gets to know you.
transit: We're very close to the freeway--about a mile and a half-- and only 15 minutes BY CAR from OSU, 20 from Downtown, 30 mins to the zoo, and 20 minutes to the airport.  Plenty of parking on the street. Please don't park in the driveway. Note to anyone without a car: Columbus does not have good public transportation. Example: Ohio State is 5.5 miles away--12 minutes to drive, but 1 hour and 15 minutes on the bus. (1 hour and a half to walk.) If you'd like to check your transportation distance on a mapping website, use North Linden Elementary School as a starting point.
access: Kitchen, laundry in basement if you need it, back patio in summer months and we have a warm comfortable family room with TV and Netflix etc.
interaction: I'm home some evenings, good parts of the weekends, and I'm always around at dinner and breakfast to take care of the dogs! I have a grown son in town who shows up to fix peoples cars in my garage-- you'll recognize him by his height, being covered in grease and a big smile.
house_rules: Please send a request if you have pets so we can chat first, but most pets are welcome here. Smoking outside or in attached garage if it's below freezing. Please be quiet after 10 pm on weekdays. Clean up after yourself in the kitchen and bathroom, but otherwise, just common courtesy! No overnight guests.
host_about:
I'm a (mostly) empty-nester with a son in the Navy, a son who's an auto mechanic, and a daughter who is still living at home. We have two dogs and two cats, so yes, it's a little overly friendly sometimes here. I work full time, spend lots of time with my friends and otherwise I'm reading or writing. :)
 
I loved my first Airbnb stay, and when my short-term renter moved out, I thought, why not try hosting? Columbus may not be a destination city... but it turns out, lots of people come here for all kinds of reasons! Who knew?

I love traveling, and my oldest calls me a public transportation tourist. (I really do love riding buses and trains. So I guess it fits.)

neighborhood_overview: Welcome to German Village, one of the most storied urban neighborhoods in the U.S. We are an energetic, eclectic mashup of modern lifestyles enjoying the best shops, restaurants and parks found anywhere against a backdrop of brick streets and houses listed on the National Register of Historic Places. German Village is not just preserved architecture from the 1800s; it is the aggregation of more than 130 years of the stories of area people, families and businesses. Character lives on! • Listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1974. • In 2006, German Village was made a Preserve America Community by the White House. • The New York Post listed German Village and Columbus among the Top 5 Travel Spots in the World in 2007. • Travel site (website hidden) lists German Village as a Top 3 “Fodor’s Choice” pick. • We are a 2011 designee as one of the country’s 10 Great Neighborhoods, recognized by the American Planning Association. • We are one of the New York Times’ top rated,

neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is one of the Midwest’s best kept secrets. We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Weinland Park, a cool, urban area on the East side of High St above 5th Ave.   Is the neighborhood safe? We live nearby and feel the neighborhood is relatively safe.  Please note this is the city- we do have petty crime in the Short North and University area, and always advise to practice common sense such as not leaving valuables in your car (we have not had any issues at our apartments, I state this because we are in the city) and walk with a buddy at night on well-lit, busy roads such as High Street, Summit, and 5th Ave. Within walking distance of the following: • Restaurant

name: The Schiller Room- On the Park GV
summary: On the park in the historic Kremer Home, a sun-filled studio apartment with hardwood floors, high ceilings, fine woodwork, period furniture, and contemporary art.  Just steps to all that German Village and downtown Columbus have to offer- a must see!
space: The suite that is currently available is a 400 square foot sun-filled studio apartment with hardwood floors, high ceilings, fine woodwork, period furniture, and contemporary art by Ohio artists. It has its own private entrance, granite-tiled full bath and shower, piano, queen-sized bed, refrigerator, coffee-pot, and generous closet space. Located in the Kremer home, situated on the northeast corner of Schiller Park- this house is one of German Village's best-known residences. Built in 1887 by a leading Columbus architect and developer, Julius Kremer, it has captured the imagination of German Village residents and visitors for over 100 years. Kremer developed the land around the park and designed many well-known structures in Columbus and throughout Ohio, including the Hartman Building, Front's Brewery, and the Union Station.

Kremer developed the land around the park and designed many well-known structures in Columbus and t
neighborhood_overview: Come join us for a memorable glimpse into the past while sharing the vibrancy of one of the Midwest's most progressive cities. It is the perfect spot for an urban vacation. Whether you want to enjoy Shakespeare in Schiller Park, a world class meal, a hockey game, a jog in the park, a festive event or some of Ohio's best bars, they are just a short walk away.
transit: In German Village we recommend many modes of transport: one being the free "C-bus shuttle" that picks up residents only blocks from the apartment and takes them all the way up to North High Street, and back down, running daily from 8-10pm. We are also located in very close proximity to a Co-Go, our city's bike-to-go program- where you can rent a bike for hours at a time and ride around Columbus. We highly recommend Uber and German Village Taxi, if you decide you'd like to venture out of the village.
access: Schiller park is literally 25 feet from the front door of the apartment. There is access to the home's private garden. A major grocery store is one block away as is one of Columbus' finest bars and restaurants. Additionally, the Kremer home is in close walking distance to many more of the best galleries, restaurants, pubs, bars, restaurants, diners, bakeries, and boutiques and shops that German Village has to offer.
interaction: Guests are welcome to call me with pertinent questions. I can be available if you need-- otherwise, the Schiller Room offers the privacy that an apartment or hotel room provides.
house_rules: This is a non-smoking space. We also do not currently allow pets.

neighborhood_overview: We love that Woodland Park is a hidden gem, a lovely pocket of early 1900's large homes with different architectural styles, including Arts and Crafts, Spanish, Cape Cod, Georgian, English Tudor, and more, all visible from our front step and your window! The neighbors are an eclectic mix of young, old, black, and white who are community minded.  We are two blocks from Franklin Park Conservatory, and a five minute ride to great restaurants, music and theater in the Short North, Downtown and German Village areas. Columbus is an exciting, young, trend-setting city that we are proud to be a part of.

house_rules: No Pets- If you have a pet at the apartment you will be charged a fine of $50/night for each night you had a pet at the apartment. Parking pass- if the parking pass is not returned on the day you check out, there is an automatic $100 fine. If the pass is not returned within 48 hours after checkout, there is an additional $300 fine.

name: Tiny House Rainbow Bungalow
summary: Our Rainbow Bungalow is a community built, artistic space.  A "tiny house" made with upcycled materials. This private stand alone structure shares the kitchen & bathroom inside the main house. Complete with wifi, memory foam bedding, and breezes from the river. An urban camping experience with no A/C.
space: Welcome! to our "tiny house" Artist Bungalow :)  This space is much like urban camping but without the hassle of the tent and with the luxury of electricity, internet, and comfortable full size bedding. Guests are provided filtered water, towels, fresh bedding, shampoo, coffee and a list of places to eat.  The bungalow is completely yours, cozy & private. Right outside your door is a metro park AND an amazing bike path to travel the city. Along the river bike path, OSU is a beautiful 20 minute walk and 8 minute bike ride. The park is equipped with a brand new basketball court, tennis court, playground and shelter house. Bring your bike, basketball, or tennis rackets for extra adventure. The space has 8 windows and 1 window door which provides beautiful lighting and fresh air. The floor is bamboo, the walls & ceiling are pine. There is no TV but internet for your Netflix needs. neighborhood_overview: Clintonville is one of the best neighborhoods in Columbus!!   Endless walkable options for bars or dining, and super easy access to the rest of the city and Ohio State University Campus.
notes: I do have a dog and cat inside my home. They are super friendly indoor/outdoor animals. Please do not let them in the bungalow.
transit: Public transport is available at the end of the street...$2 on our local city bus each way.   We also have Uber...Car2Go is quite popular, these cars are always in the neighborhood if you are a member.

interaction: I am available to help at any time. Please feel free to text me.

host_about:
I am an artist creating interactive community art.
I make giant body puppets and use them as tools to spread messages 
of kindness through performance and improv. 
I am a mother, bicyclist, gardener, animal, & nature lover.
I love sushi & dancing. I spend much of my time in my studio doing headstands and art.
I am enjoying being a host for Airbnb guests and sharing my awesome 
artist bungalow with people from all over the world.
This tiny home was built with love, creativity, and recycled materials.
 I am a flexible, easy going, and available host. 
Although, I'm rarely home I spend much of my time working in my studio just 5 min away.
I look forward to meet & greet & welcome you. 
YOU keep the artist bungalow alive :)

summary: A calm, peaceful home in Westerville, a suburb of Columbus, with a room & private bathroom to rent. Located only 2 minutes from the highway, our home is situated in a prime location with access to a multitude of attractions, shopping, entertainment, and dining options all within 5-15 minutes, including Downtown Columbus, Port Columbus International Airport, Easton Town Center, Short North, & OSU. Complimentary coffee & tea is also available. We gladly welcome all long & short term reservations!
space: Its calm, relaxing atmosphere in a quiet neighborhood with lots of walking paths, yet remarkably close to several key points of interest in the city. Depending on where you are going, it generally takes about 20 minutes to anywhere in the city!

neighborhood_overview: As part of the Little Turtle Community, our neighborhood offers a secluded sanctuary from the normal bustle of a large metro area, yet with incredible accessibility to immediate shopping, entertainment, and dining within 5-10 minutes of our home. In a wooded development, there are also several fantastic walking paths around the neighborhood and golf course for a relaxing run or walk.  House manual provides multiple links to various destinations nearby and in the Columbus vicinity.
notes: We do have several furbabies on the premises who will gladly keep you company if you desire. We do keep our home exceptionally clean as we have 3 cats (Joey, Zoey, & Simba) & 2 dogs (Meeka, Jasmine). All are very friendly if not shy. Dogs are caged in the evenings & when we are not home. Guests are more than welcome to keep the door closed if you do not wish them to be in your room. Additionally, for the safety of all residents in our home, we do have a Ring video doorbell as well as one visible interior camera directed at our main entrance. For those seeking long term stays, airbnb will only charge you one month at a time, not the entire amount upfront.
transit: We are conveniently located 2-3 minutes from major highways with immediate accessibility to shopping, entertainment, dining, and key destinations throughout the city. As there is no bus service in our neighborhood, a car is highly recommended. Uber and taxis are also available. Ask me for a discount code!
access: Guests are welcome to enjoy our home, including the guest room, guest bath, main living room, lower level living room, dining room, kitchen, laundry room, gym, and backyard deck. Please feel free to partake in any of the relaxing spaces throughout the home, especially our deck and landscaped yard.
interaction: We love meeting new people, but fully respect their privacy and need for downtime. We are glad to socialize as much or as little as you are comfortable with. If you have any questions about the area, please feel free to ask as we are happy to help!
house_rules: Simply to treat their space with the same respect they would give their own home.  1. Pickup & clean after every meal.  2. Keep doors locked upon entrance and exit. 3. Please flush only toilet paper down toilets (no wipes, tissues, feminine hygiene products, etc.). 4. No tobacco or drug use.  5. Extra sets of linens and towels are available. Laundry facilities and detergent are available for your use free of charge. Long term guests are expected to clean all linens and towels as needed.  6. Please keep noise to a reasonable level as others guests may be present. 7. For the comfort and safety of our guests and family, only registered guests are permitted on the property.  Additional details provided upon arrival.
host_about: My husband Tim & I have been together for 8 years & love where we live. We are both very easy to get along with & are happy to help those not familiar with the area. We both love this city, the arts, music & foodie scene which is phenomenal! There are quiet nights at home, but we also spend time regularly with our friends & always look forward to making more!

name: A warm family welcome
summary: We offer a very private "mother-in-law suite" of bedroom, sitting room (or second bedroom, but the two rooms are interconnected) and private bathroom. You can also enjoy your own kitchenette in an additional space which is not as private.  Although our guests basically have one level of the house to themselves (1/2 flight of stairs down), the entrance foyer and stairway are shared with the rest of the house; it is not a stand alone apartment. Surcharge on more than 4 guests. Pets are negotiable.
space: There is a comfortable full size bed (sleeps two), dresser and a large closet in the inner bedroom.  The outer room  of the suite has a desk, chair, plenty of shelves and a futon couch that can be set up as a second full size bed for two more guests.  A small private bathroom is immediately adjacent.  The whole suite is in the lower part of the house which makes it secluded from the rest of the house, but the entrance foyer and the stairway are shared. There is a small refrigerator and cooking area in the lower part of the house for the guests convenience. It contains a one portable burner, mictowave, coffee machine, electric hot water kettle and all pots, pans dishes silveware, cooking utensils etc needed to cook simple meals.  In the summer you can take advantage of our BBQ, patio and outdoor eating area facing into a quiet backyard.

neighborhood_overview: We are one block away from Scioto river park (3 miles of park along the river) which is great for jogging, biking or walks by the river.  We are also 15 minutes away from Columbus award winning ZOO (9 miles) and 15 minutes away from OSU campus (8 miles). Downtown Columbus is 20 minutes away (10 miles) and Riverside Hospital is 10 minutes away.  All by car.
notes: We are empty nesters with an academic and international background and we welcome visiting scholars or medical students on rotations.  We can make additional rooms available short term for large parties on special occasions, please inquire directly with me.
transit: The house is in a quiet residential area with plenty of parking.  There is unfortunately no public transportation within walking distance so a car, bike, Uber or taxi are your choices for getting around. We have one bike we can lend to long term visitors.
access: Other then the"mother-in-law" suite, the whole lower level of the house is freely accessible together with the kitchenette and patio on the same level and laundry in the basement.  The upper bedrooms are private unless you make arrangements with me directly for a larger party.
interaction: We are both working long hours so we are available only in the evenings or on weekends for face to face interactions which we enjoy whenever possible.  Even if I am not around, I will be happy to help via text or email at any time during the day. Check in and check out could be self help depending on the time.
house_rules: -Please take your shoes off in the entrance foyer. -Absolutely no smoking anywhere in the house; outside is ok.  -Please keep quiet after 10pm. -People other than those in guest party are not permitted to stay overnight in the property without prior notif
host_about:
I am originally from Prague, Czech Republic but the winds of life landed me in Ohio.  I love to explore new places, people and food.  I work as a student science labs manager at Ohio State University where my husband is a professor of economics. Our two sons are students at the same university.
I usually travel with my husband Dean and sometime with our adult sons as well. We tend to travel by car and stay with friends whenever we can.  We hope Airbnb will help us make friends in places where we do not have any yet. 
We love using Airbnb as travelers and so we also became hosts.  As empty nesters, we hate to see the space in our house idle.  We have always welcomed friends from around the world, but Columbus does not seem to be a hot spot tourist destination (imagine that!).  Airbnb gives us an opportunity to host more often.

name: Glenbrook House Park-like Relaxing Setting
summary: A bright bed room with a queen bed & wooded view; private bath adjacent to the bedroom. 1920's home in beautiful spacious setting in the heart of the city. A block to the bus. Minutes to downtown & OSU.
space: Our home is located on the edge of the Overbrook Ravine, surrounded by woods, gardens and tranquility.  Right in the heart of Columbus, this house, built in the 1920's is tucked away on large parcel of land and has maintained much of the original unusual character of the house.  The bed room is comfortable and overlooking the tree tops of the ravine, a private bath with a soaking tub (or shower) is adjacent the room.  It's a special place to live, it's a special place to share.

neighborhood_overview: The Clintonville area of Columbus is north of Downtown, Short North, Victorian Village and Ohio State. It is a family oriented, welcoming neighborhood.  Tree lined streets, places to walk, parks to enjoy, great restaurants, easy access to the bus.
transit: Easy access to both Interstate I70 and 315. The COTA Bus #2 runs the length of High Street; it's a block from the house.  Taxis and Uber are easily available.
access: Guests have access to the entire house and grounds, except for our private bedroom.
interaction: We're social people, enjoy big parties and small.  The guest's desires for how much and what kind of interaction they wish is most important to us.
house_rules: We're easy.  Be happy to work with guests if they have special needs.
host_about:
Jan and I met in college in Wisconsin, been in Ohio since 1973 and have had fun living in this house for over 20 years.  Jan likes making the people around her happy.  It's worked for me for over 50 years.  We're now both retired.  I play the auto harp and sing traditional American and Irish folk songs.  It keeps a smile on my face.  We have a special affinity for Ireland, where we have lived and visited many times.  I love to cook, make the gardens beautiful.  Over the years Jan and I developed a purpose for our lives -- "Spread joy, have fun doing it."  We're counting on our guests enjoying their visits, in the way they want to enjoy them!!  
We may be traveling when you're here, but we have excellent local support and resources.  The grass gets mowed, the gutters cleaned, the driveway plowed if needed.

host_about:
I am a very active individual and enjoy being outside when possible. My favorites things to do are Rowing, Swimming, Biking, Running, Triathlons, hiking and just working in the yard. I have worked in Hospitality for a long time starting in restaurants in high school. I now work at a Hilton and when I retire I plan open a B&B in Saugatuck/Douglas Michigan. 

I do both traveling and hosting on Airbnb and love both. Its just great to meet different people and visit different places. If there is anything you would like to know about Columbus when you are here don't be shy!! If I am staying with you I know I wont be shy to ask about the area.

I do love animals and have a dog of my own named Chance. He is weimaraner and is just over a year old. He is a great big bundle of joy and is always willing to play a game of fetch.

I do have a life motto that I got from my favorite book the peaceful warrior. It is there simple words - paradox, humor, and change. If you know the book you know the meaning if you have not read the book you should. It is a great conversation piece if I am staying at your place or if you are staying at mine just ask I would be more then willing to explain. 

Happy Traveling

name: The Perfect Pad All To Yourself
summary: This condo could not be located in a better area of Columbus -- in the Short North and right on High St. You'll be on top of the best food and nightlife Columbus has to offer. It'll be clean for you :)
space: My condo is 442 square feet of simple, clean city living. It (and me!) was featured on HGTV's House Hunters last fall. Hilarious! Feel free to check it out the episode on iTunes. It's right on High Street -- Columbus' main drag -- and on the most vibrant stretch of the street. If you need parking, there is a large parking garage one block north at Russell and High. It can be noisy on Friday and Saturday nights, so if you need it absolutely quiet to sleep, you might want to look elsewhere if you're visiting on a weekend. It's a third floor walk up. Burning those calories walking up the stairs is sure to make that late night pizza guilt free ;)

name: German Village Apartment - Schiller
summary: My fun and eclectic apartment is located right next to Schiller Park in historic German Village in Columbus, Ohio.  The area is rich with history and world famous food options! You can't beat the location and window view of Schiller!
space: Love world famous hamburgers or giant cream puffs?  Then my apartment is the perfect spot for you! It's within walking distance of The Thurman Cafe (as seen on Man vs. Food) and Schmidt's (homemade German sausage galore).  My apartment is ideal for anyone with a love for movies, pop culture, and a catch all of fun.  If you're a super minimalist, you may find my quirky decor a bit much, but most people enjoy the "character." Free and abundant parking is a HUGE pro with my location.  Very hard to find in German Village.

Avid traveler and runner  :) Always up for an adventure.  LOVE my Ohio State Buckeyes!

We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Weinland Park, a cool, urban area on the East side of High St above 5th Ave.   Is the neighborhood safe? We live nearby and feel the neighborhood is relatively safe.  Please note this is the city- we do have petty crime in the Short North and University area, and always advise to practice common sense such as not leaving valuables in your car (we have not had any issues at our apartments, I state this because we are in the city) and walk with a buddy at night on well-lit, busy roads such as High Street, Summit, and 5th Ave. Within walking distance of the following: • Restaurant

Our life motto- Live like someone left the gate open!

neighborhood_overview: German Village is a historic neighborhood in Columbus, Ohio, just south of downtown. It has brick lined roads, small shops, restaurants, coffee spots and bars that make it a wonderful place to stroll around  and get 'lost' in the neighborhood.  Schiller Park is a short walk from our house. It is a wonderful green space that offers tennis courts, a basketball court, picnic tables and plenty of paths to walk around the park. During the summer months the park offers a Free outdoor theater production. Shows are every Thursday, Friday, Saturday and Sunday evenings at 8pm.  Theater schedule can be found by searching- Actors Theater of Columbus

name: Comfy room close to OSU/downtown!
summary: We live in the popular Grandview Heights area of Columbus, rated a very unique and walkable area! We love Columbus and know all of the hot spots to check out!  We are a just a quick trip from downtown, OSU, and all of the fun districts!
space: Relaxing private room with a queen size bed!   The room has a dresser, closet and minifridge stocked with drinks/snacks.  There are extra blankets and pillows also in the room, if needed.  The bathroom is just out in the hallway and is stocked with towels, toiletries and all bathroom essentials you may need, including a hairdryer and iron/ironing board.  We do have another room that we book only for large events going on in the area which shares the bathroom with this listing, so feel free to ask whether the other room will be booked during your stay. We have our own bathroom upstairs so it is mostly private!
description: We live in the popular Grandview Heights area of Columbus, rated a very unique and walkable area! We love Columbus and know all of the hot spots to check out!  We are a just a quick trip from downtown, OSU, and all of the fun districts! Relaxing private room with a queen size bed!   The room has a dresser, closet and minifridge stocked with drinks/snacks.  There are extra blankets and pillows also in the room, if needed.  The bathroom is just out in the hallway and is stocked with towels, toiletries and all bathroom essentials you may need, including a hairdryer and iron/ironing board.  We do have another room that we book only for large events going on in the area which shares the bathroom with this listing, so feel free to ask whether the other room will be booked during your stay. We have our own bathroom upstairs so it is mostly private! Guests have access to the bedroom, a full bathroom, kitchen and living areas on the first floor as well as outdoor areas. There also is a laundry
neighborhood_overview: We live in the charming Fifth by Northwest area of Columbus.  We are just a few miles from the Arena district, Short North, OSU, and downtown areas. Within just a few blocks is the Grandview Avenue area full of shops, bars and restaurants as well!
notes: We do have a friendly dog named Maddie who lives in this home.  She loves kids and other dogs and will be kept either with us or in our room during your stay.  All around the home is open street parking and you can usually find a spot right outside!
transit: We are close to two bus stops (COTA bus), and are less than a mile away from the CoGo bike share stop.  You can also get an Uber or a cab in minutes and for minimal fare to downtown or OSU areas. All areas are also a nice, safe walk!
access: Guests have access to the bedroom, a full bathroom, kitchen and living areas on the first floor as well as outdoor areas. There also is a laundry area in the basement available for use if needed.
interaction: Andrew and I will be available to help with anything you may need but are often running around enjoying our great city!  Let us know if we can be of service in any way during your stay!
house_rules: We ask that you respect our belongings and home and do not allow smoking inside the house.  We do work early hours during the week as well as have another AirBNB room that is booked occasionally so we do ask guests to be respectful of noise during later hours.  We do love dogs and would be willing to have your pup join you during your stay, as long as they are friendly!
host_about: I am a lifelong Columbus resident who loves all of the new and exciting things going on here!  I love to travel, love sports and the outdoors!

We have been long-time hosts and are passionate about hosting travelers of all varieties, when we cannot be traveling ourselves. Please do not hesitate to contact us, as we would be delighted to host you.

name: Classy Condo - Spacious and Updated
summary: The Classy Condo has 1900 square feet of living space. Updated for guests. Four designated parking spaces in additon to street parking. It is within 10 minutes of downtown New Albany, Westerville, Easton Town Center and Columbus Airport.
description: The Classy Condo has 1900 square feet of living space. Updated for guests. Four designated parking spaces in additon to street parking. It is within 10 minutes of downtown New Albany, Westerville, Easton Town Center and Columbus Airport.
host_about: Thanks for checking out our Classy Condo. We are both teachers who enjoy our students during the school year and boating and golf in the summer. Our actual residence is in a lake community and we enjoy a slower pace of life because of it. Our condo is a Westerville, Ohio address but it is very close to New Albany, Ohio, the Columbus airport and The Easton Shopping Center. We are excited to share this condo through Airbnb. Between us we have five grown children. Each of them have lived in the condo at one time or another during natural life transitions. The spaciousness and layout of this condo is a favorite of all of them. We have added internet service to the condo. You will not be disappointed if you let us be your host.

name: 1BR Apt. on Clintonville Ravine
summary: Lovely  2-story, 1BR apartment located in the South Clintonville/North University District area, minutes from OSU or downtown.  It overlooks the Glen Echo Ravine, is comfortably furnished, and is ideal for a single or couple who are visiting Columbus
space: The apartment is located on a busy street (Indianola), but its entrance is behind a 2-car garage and has an entry deck and covered entry porch.  The space is on two levels, with an eat-in kitchen on the entry level, and a living room, bedroom, and bath on the upper level.  The kitchen space and the living room space both have wonderful views of the ravine greenery with its many birds and other wildlife.  The kitchen space has easy access to the entry deck that also overlooks the ravine and has seating so you can relax outdoors. neighborhood_overview: This is a wonderful neighborhood with a mix of rental units and private residences.  There is a ravine park within easy walking distance and an assortment of shops and restaurants on Indianola.  It’s a quick drive to High Street and its many shops (including a Giant Eagle supermarket and a CVS pharmacy), and access to either the I-71 or the 315 freeway is quite close.
notes: Minimum rental period is three nights at $85/night.  Maximum occupancy is two persons.  Longer rentals of 3 months or more are welcome at a reduced rate.  This is a pet-free, no smoking apartment, and it is not suitable for children.
transit: Indianola Avenue is a major roadway, and a city bus line runs in front of the building. access: There is one assigned off-street parking space on the driveway in front of the end garage door. interaction: I am retired from OSU and I live next door to this apartment, so I am available to solve any problems pretty quickly (unless I am out of town).

If you are returning to the apartment later than 11pm, please do so as quietly as possible and do not linger in the kitchen area.  Guest visitors (3 or 4 max) are permitted for short periods (e.g. for a meal, coffee, movie, conversation, etc.) and should depart by 11pm.  Guests' visitors should park on the street and should not smoke or bring pets or children to the apartment.
host_about: I have lived in Columbus off and on since coming here to attend Ohio State University in the 60's. My husband and I have 3 grandchildren - one in California and two in Michigan.  I recently retired from OSU after working there for 18 years.

name: Perfect Clintonville Pre-fabulous in 1950s Cottage
summary: Come stay with us in our charming 1950s pre-fab cottage in the heart of Columbus's quirky, peaceful Clintonville neighborhood. Just a short walk or ride away from High Street -- the city's central cultural artery -- and the no. 2 and 4 bus lines, and with lots of clean, mid-century and vintage charm. We offer plenty of street parking, nice sheets & blankets, a chemical-free home, filtered water, summertime garden views, and, best of all: free hangs w/ the world's cutest border collie, Isaly!
space: Our darling little cape cottage is a part of one of Columbus' original mid-century housing developments -- right smack-dab in the middle of Clintonville. Our house features three bedrooms, a centrally-located bathroom, spacious study, 1950s-style living room and loft bedroom upstairs. Your room is a clean, crisp bedroom that overlooks the backyard, with great morning sun and a mid-century-modern-meets-farm-country-chiq decor -- we're early to bed and early to rise, so your space will be quiet and cozy to meet your schedule. Wool blankets, a water carafe, a vintage dresser, a nightlight and lamp, and classic American lit are all provided to you for your use during your visit; just ask if you need anything else! NOTE: As of Summer 2016, The Cozy Room has now been upgraded to a super-comfy full-sized bed; and can comfortably sleep two people (who like each other)! Still includes green dresser as pictures, towels, linens & blankets; and a deluxe vintage banker's lamp for that cozy green gl

Just a short walk or ride away from High Street -- the city's central cultural artery -- and the no. 2 and 4 bus lines, and with lots of clean, mid-century and vintage charm.
