neighborhood_overview: Clintonville is a classic, progressive and activist Columbus neighborhood -- the closest North suburb to the Ohio State University campus, the Short North arts district, and downtown! You'll find the city's best co-ops, farmers' markets, coffee shops here; and, yeah: there's a bit of an old-school, 1960s, crystal-shoppe/yoga loft/Himalayan salt lamp New Age-y vibe here, as well! We're located smack-dab in the middle of a charming, diverse development built here in 1950, within a stone's throw of Clintonville's renowned Park of Roses, Whetstone Recreation Center and the Whetstone branch of the Columbus Public Library. We really have the best of all worlds -- crazy early-50s suburban charm (we're talking garage eagles, chain-link fences, giant cement yard statues of the Virgin Mary/cats, screened-in porches, shade trees and lemonade stands) with all the amenities of downtown right down the road. Restaurants and amazing local breweries abound, in both directions up High Street; and the Cl
notes: We have a lovely and very friendly pup named Isaly -- she's a border collie mix, and will probably not only request, but demand that you pet her and give her some belly rubs! We haven't heard any allergy complaints yet; but if you're seriously allergic to dogs, you may want to weigh that in your request. She'll stay in the main spaces of the house and sleep in our bedroom -- unless you let her into your room, in which case I'm sure she'd be happy to snuggle pro bono! She can be a bit shy around some folks, and has some funny fears (large flat circular shapes like manhole covers, etc.), so we'll want to introduce you all first. You'll fall in love, we swear -- we just ask, since we live not too far off the street, to ask us if you'd like to take her out to play in the backyard! We also have a very sweet matching cat, Nell, who's around some of the time; she's a pretty chill cat but might sit on your head if you want her to :) We're super-close to main bus-lines in the neighborhood; but
transit: We're right by major COTA bus-lines that head up and down both High Street (#2) and Indianola (#4) most times of day or night -- these will take you to campus, the Short North Arts district, downtown, and beyond! With big trees, sidewalks, and families all around, this is a restful and beautiful neighborhood, perfect for your Columbus stay --  it's beyond walkable; and bikes, COTA bus or even an Uber can take you to more distant locales. If you'll be traveling the freeways with your own (or a rented) vehicle during your stay, we're also conveniently located near I-71, to get you North and South of Columbus; we're happy to try to help provide road directions if you need 'em!
access: A stay with us, of course, includes  your beautiful room, and the cozy bathroom is right next door! You'll pass through the kitchen and living room to get to your space, but we maintain these and the rest of our house for our private use. Please respect that. There's WiFi in your room.  Please be mindful that guests will not have access to the kitchen. We allow light meal prep -- breads/cereals/dry goods (yours) and tea (we provide); and refrigeration is sometimes (but not always) available; please contact us in advance if you anticipate needing kitchen use and we can discuss (see House Rules for more details.) We hope you love our space as much as we do!
interaction: We're both extremely friendly and gregarious about all our lovely little city -- one of us was born & raised here, and the other's quickly become an adopted son. We'd be happy to tell you all about our favorite shops, restaurants, co-ops, farmers' markets and breweries -- can you tell we're big fans of the local food scene here? We'd love to interact as much as we're able -- we're graduate students and are often juggling quite a few projects at once with deadlines that follow us home from work, but we're usually down to go for a walk, exploring, or to grab some great food nearby!
house_rules: #NAME?
host_about:
hi there! i'm jess -- a folklorist, oral historian and  columbus, ohio native with a really amazing border collie pup, named isaly. 

my partner jeff & i are both currently grad students -- he studies the history of industrialization and labor in the u.s. south through a history of science & technology phd. program based in philly, and i'm a folklorist and oral historian who works on the history of sustainable agriculture, food & environmental justice, & everyday perceptions of environmental toxicity. that means i get to road-trip around this fine state alot, asking people questions about how they connect food and environment health, and how they've had their lives shaped  around those questions. 

as a folklorist and oral historian, i believe in the power of everyday people's embodied and lived knowledge and experience; and my work is in documenting, interpreting and helping to present these powerful perspectives to wider audiences, to create conversations for change. i try to bring these passions to everything in my life.

i'm interested in the ways people connect food, health and environmental concern; and movement histories and futures of activism around the stuff that makes us sick, and the stuff that makes us healthy. basically, if you wanna talk farm magazines from the 1950s or the poisons & boons of various audio recorders or just like food in general, i'm yr grrl! 

because of my own history of exposure and chemical sensitivity, we try to keep (as much as possible) a non-toxic home, free of meats, chemical cleaners, and scents. and, if you come in summer or fall, you're free to help harvest goodies from our bountiful yard garden! (the "yarden.") it can get a bit weedy this time of year; but it's all chem-free and very well loved.

columbus, ohio is my hometown (and my favorite city on earth), and we're so blessed to get to do cultural work in and around the good and environmental systems in this lovely place. we absolutely love showing people this city -- from cultural tours to the best nature spots to restaurants (even pokémon)! 

our wonderful brilliant border collie isaly will be your prime host -- she loves our guests and will happily throw you some tricks (her newest one is "step up and kisses") and some cuddles. we also have a lovely matching kitty named nella. 

we love meeting people from all around the world, and sharing our love for our little city and its wonderful culture. we can't wait to meet you!

summary: This room is the entire 2nd floor of our darling mid-century cape cod-style cottage in Clintonville. With original French windows, wall-to-wall wooden shelving, and charming farmhouse-meets-midcentury vintage decor, this place is a cozy retreat in the heart of our city!
space: Picture your cool aunt/grandma's amazing cozy finished attic space - but without any of those weird hand-me-downs. This space features a luxurious full-size bed, vintage lounge chair and ottoman, and several charming restored farmhouse pieces -- including repurposed orchard crates and even a roost from a 1850s chicken coop! The room also has storage galore for the weary traveler: built-in-wooden shelving all along the stairwell, a darling tiny closet-space, and all the pegboards yr heart could desire. Our loft is the perfect snug hideaway, summer or winter. With the large plush full-size bed, extra-long couch, comfy dad upholstered chair and ample wooden built-in shelving, this is the ideal suite for vintage-loving traveling folk who want a touch of local color -- whether you're visiting Columbus solo or in a small group. neighborhood_overview: We're located smack-dab in the heart of Clintonville -- a charming, quirky, progressive neighborhood just on the north side of the campus of The Ohio State University. Our street, like the streets surrounding us, runs between Indianola and High Street -- the main arts, culture and food vein of Columbus. The neighborhood is a mix of classic 1920s Clintonville Bungalows and Dutch revival houses, and a pattern-blend of darling 1950s salt-box houses and cape cods -- of which our place is one! Our street is a great strolling street, with huge shade trees closer to High Street; and we're just a hop skip and a jump away from some of the city's best amenities: coffee (Global Gallery); farmers' markets (the Clintonville Farmers' Market at Dunedin and High!); co-ops (the Clintonville Community Market at Crestview and Calumet); and delicious eats (Northstar at Beechwold; Harvest and Acre by Weber). Plus, we're ridiculously close to the Park of Roses/Whetstone Rec Center/Whetstone Library; there,
notes: PETS: We do have a lovely and gregarious pup, Isaly -- she's a border collie mix, and is the friendliest dog in the world, and will more than likely try to lure you into a game of fetch or a bellyrub at some point during your stay. Our cat, Nell, is also sometimes around. We're sure they'll love you and you'll love them, but when you come to stay, we'd love it if you'd just double-check to make sure you're not letting the animal hordes out with you when you come and go; and don't ever take the animals on a walk or outside without our express permission. We do that, not you. ****** NO A/C IN SUMMERTIME; we use box fans and windows to keep the house cool! Please don't book if you have a medical condition necessitating A/C or otherwise expect it. It doesn't make ecological or financial sense for us. Thanks for understanding! Yay fans!!! ************ We also ask guests to: -- Not eat/consume/bring meat into the house. We are all *all-vegetarian* house. What you do outside our home is up to
transit: We're SUPER close to the major COTA bus lines through Columbus -- the #2 and #4 buses have stops right on High Street and Indianola, on either end of our street; and we even have a stop for the 2L on High Street, which is the express line to OSU campus and downtown (very speedy)! These will take you to campus, downtown, or anywhere you'd like. High Street is also just a short stroll or bike-ride away; and the Global Gallery Coffee shop, Boline apothecary, and Broadway block of Clintonville businesses are all within walking distance. The bike path is also just right across High Street, and, if you've got a bike or borrow ours, can get you almost anyplace you'd like to go in Columbus, with gorgeous fall colors and scenic river sounds to boot!
access: Since this room is the entire second floor of the house, you'll have your own private stairwell entrance up from the main floor, with a door that shuts.  Please note, however, that unlike the "lockbox + condo" style AirBnB, this is actually our house. We live here; our stuff is here; our dog is here. So please come prepared to be respectful of us, and our home. A stay with us includes your access to your beautiful room, and the cozy bathroom is right down the stairs! You may pass through the kitchen and living room to get to your space, but we maintain these and the rest of our house for our private use. Please respect that -- and please ask before entering our spaces. There's WiFi in your room; and since your room is very spacious, we it's almost a whole apartment unto itself. Our kitchen is not available for guest use; please contact us in advance if you anticipate needing kitchen use and we can discuss potentially offering these services for an additional charge (see House Rules for
interaction: We love getting to know new folks from around the world, and sharing the love and our recommendations for our beloved city! That said, we are both in school and juggling projects that often follow us home from work -- & Jess is often out traveling for fieldwork -- but we'd be happy to hang out, chat, or even take you out for a drink or a bite to eat if we're available! This usually isn't during the semester, unfortunately. We've modeled our AirBNB guest philosophy on that of our own favorite host, Margie in Atlanta: we're committed to being around and hanging out if that's what you need, but we're also perfectly content -- as introverts ourselves! -- to just give you some much needed time to relax & recharge in your own space. So, as much or as little interaction as you'd like. Our pup, Isaly, and kitty Nell, however, may request cuddles from you with our without your permission! It is gorgeous with a variety of old homes--Queen Anne, Victorian--and tree lined streets. It is experiencing a renaissance and offers a tavern (very good food!), a café where a lot of people enjoy breakfast, a pizza shop that's a cut above chain pizza's, art galleries and more. These locations are a 5 minute walk from the house.
notes: The home has very close access to the bus pick-up locations--there are several. And with a car, it's easy to go to shows at any of the old Ohio Palaces!  There are many venues providing a variety of offerings for every taste.  And in the summer, there's the OHIO STATE FAIR!  And in the fall, there's OHIO STATE FOOTBALL!  Both are accessible by bus as well a car!

host_about: I am a friendly person who enjoys getting to know others.  I love to read, work in the yard, sing, sing, sing and snuggle with my dog--when he let's me. I really enjoy travelling and have been on package tours and well as trips where I hunt out hostels.  I appreciate having different people around!

name: Beautiful Upstairs Apt. in Olde Towne East
summary: Handsome apartment in the fashionable and up-and-coming Olde Towne East neighborhood.  One bedroom, plus a fold out couch, sleeps a total of four.  Edwardian character, eclectic art on the walls, and a funky mix of antique and modern furniture.
space: Second floor apartment in a century-old house in Olde Town East.
description: Handsome apartment in the fashionable and up-and-coming Olde Towne East neighborhood.  One bedroom, plus a fold out couch, sleeps a total of four.  Edwardian character, eclectic art on the walls, and a funky mix of antique and modern furniture. Second floor apartment in a century-old house in Olde Town East. This unit is an entire separate apartment, with its own separate entrance.  Access is by electronic combination lock. We live a few blocks away, so are generally available in the event of any issue that may arise.  We do travel frequently, however, so we always make sure to have someone available in our absence. Olde Towne East is one of the most up-and-coming neighborhoods in Columbus, popular with artists, hipsters, gays, young families, and other people drawn to its mix of cultural diversity, classy old housing stock, relatively low rents, and a laid-back slow pace of life. It's definitely an urban environment, and it's not the suburbs! There are gritty edges to Olde Towne East.
neighborhood_overview: Olde Towne East is one of the most up-and-coming neighborhoods in Columbus, popular with artists, hipsters, gays, young families, and other people drawn to its mix of cultural diversity, classy old housing stock, relatively low rents, and a laid-back slow pace of life. It's definitely an urban environment, and it's not the suburbs! There are gritty edges to Olde Towne East.  However it is absolutely a safe, quiet place where nothing much ever happens. Some of the houses on the block have been given full renovations; some are waiting their turn.  Latta Avenue is a diverse street; the neighbors are a mix of black, white, straight, gay, young and old. Franklin Park is two blocks away; Broad Street is half a block, and will take you to High Street, the Convention Center, and everything else. Not much dining or entertainment within walking distance yet, but the Short North is a short Uber ride away.
notes: TV has AppleTV with complimentary Netflix.
transit: The apartment has easy access to just about everything.  Half a block from Broad Street, one of Columbus's main thoroughfares; downtown is minutes away by car, as is the Short North, the Greater Columbus Convention Center, etc.  Franklin Park, with its beautiful Conservatory is a block away, and easy walk.
access: This unit is an entire separate apartment, with its own separate entrance.  Access is by electronic combination lock.

Jay and Michael are newly married, traveling through life and the world together.  Nice, respectable boys both of them.  

Interests include old things, good food and fine wine, dogs, Lana, art museums, history, video games, antique shops, fashion, second hand bookshops.  Priorities:  eating delicious things not eaten before, seeing beautiful places not seen before, meeting extraordinary people not met before.

You can walk to OSU and the convention center.
notes: This apartment has it’s own parking area out back that can hold 1-2 cars! Free street parking is also available. While this was previously my residence, it is now a dedicated Airbnb. There are some of my belongings stored in bins in the basement but other than that, it is all for guests.

Parking is pretty cheap and easy in Columbus, or you can Uber to downtown and the other neighborhoods pretty cheaply.

notes: I have two super friendly dogs named Tucker and Tim. Unfortunately, Tucker isn't friends with other dogs or small children. I also do not permit guests alone under the age of 18. I do permit children 16+ if traveling with a parent or guardian, and if they acknowledge and understand the lifestyle we live. Since we live in main areas, you may detect our presence. We share an entrance to the home. If you choose to alter your trip during your stay,  I do not refund but I do offer credit at the refund value for your next stay with me.  Thank you for understanding. Shabbas, 420 outside only, and LGBT Friendly! Everyone is welcome. Let us know if 420 bothers you and we will avoid it.
transit: Free On-Street parking. Convention Center, Downtown, Arena District, OSU all a 5 minute Uber ride. Expo Center/Crew Stadium/Airport are 10 minute Uber ride. Lock your vehicles. I am not responsible for any theft from your vehicle.
access: The main floor (which you will traverse when you enter the home) is generally our living space, but do not feel like an intruder! Chat with us, get to know your upstairs neighbors! When you reach the stairs for the basement, you will enter your domain: full bedroom, full large bathroom, washer and dryer, living room and tv with directv, Internet, telecommuting desk and kitchenette all on the same floor! Amazon Fire Stick, Apple TV and projector available upon request. Secure bike storage is accessible through my garage, but please coordinate with me. Aside for the fact the washer and dryer for the house are on the floor, it is your domain! The front door to the house is the entrance, so you will share some space with us upon entry. We generally do not open up our main floor kitchen to our guests. We have a kitchenette in the basement that contains a fridge, microwave, and coffee maker.  We have a large beverage fridge upstairs for large items that you are free to use.
interaction: As much as you would like. Since the rooms are in the lower level, you will have privacy and won't be sharing a floor with house residents. You have your own kitchenette, living room, full bath, and bedroom. We may come downstairs to do laundry, but we will seek consent. We are in our mid 20s, and reside in the non-basement portion of the house. We are professional, and enjoy living in our home. We will respect your visit in the basement suite, and we hope you enjoy our young and fun personalities. Guests are encouraged to interact with us and enjoy your stay.  The listing is suitable for those comfortable with our mid-20s lifestyle. For instance, there may be a few cheers about the football game once in a while, some 420, or a beer can cracking, so please be comfortable with that. Let us know beforehand if there are concerns.
house_rules: Read and acknowledge these rules as well as my detailed descriptions in my listing information. My listing 99% accurately represents what you are renting, so it is your responsibility to do your homework and read everything. I reserve the right to retain the security deposit if house rule conditions are not met. By reserving this listing, you acknowledge that you understand the type of space you are renting based on the descriptions outlined in this listing. If you are an instant booker, there is a distinct possibility I am not available immediately to prepare the space for your arrival. Please anticipate coordinating with me to get the space ready, your patience is greatly appreciated. **Please remove your shoes when you enter the home. I am not a neat freak; my carpet is getting destroyed from all of the shoes.** Keep door to kitchenette closed.. I use a pest control service for preventative measures, and there is chemical in there that will KILL my dog! Please leave the space as it
host_about:
Dog dad living in a 2-job world; welcome to the ball pit!

I thoroughly enjoy hosting on Airbnb. As a wanderlust myself, I am blessed to be able to provide my guests a place to stay when they pass through my proud city! Always happy to provide advice around town, and I am excited to meet and greet you as new friends. 

I strive for 5 stars; you can see that I am a 5 star listing. This is a means for me to make a living, and it is your home for the time you are staying with me. With that, PLEASE make sure you approach me with any issues during the stay so I can resolve them DURING your stay! I want you to have a 5 star experience, and communication is key--there is nothing worse than knowing your stay was less than satisfactory through a bad review.

summary: Enjoy a beautiful private room in this large house on historic Bryden Road.  Comfortable queen bed with plenty of storage in the room along with a fireplace and a tv with DVD player. Netflix, HBO, Hulu.
space: Nicely updated home in a quiet location close to downtown Columbus.   The bedroom:  Large private room with a comfortable queen bed with luxurious bedding, plenty of storage, TV and DVD player, Netflix, HBO, Hulu, fireplace and ceiling fan. Shared bathroom. The house:  All brick 2500 sq ft craftsman built in 1914 and had a major face-lift on its 100th birthday.  Gleaming hardwood floors throughout, living room, dining room, den and updated open kitchen with granite counters and stainless steel appliances. Sun-room and balcony overlook the back yard on the second floor. Laundry available in the basement. Large fenced in back yard and only two blocks from Franklin Park and the Conservatory.  Plenty of on street free parking.

neighborhood_overview: Olde Towne East, or as I like to call it... The East Village, is a charming residential neighborhood with history around every corner.  In the late 1800's and early 1900's some of Columbus' wealthiest and most influential citizens built beautiful homes on Bryden Road.  Technically we are located in the Franklin Park Neighborhood but everyone around Columbus usually refers to the entire area as Olde Towne.
notes: I encourage visitors to use the Broad Street Exit near downtown as an alternative to other exits (Miller/Kelton) that most GPS systems will route you on. It won't add any time on to your trip and you’ll get a more scenic drive into the neighborhood.  As you head east down Broad Street you'll see some amazingly restored historic mansions and get a glimpse of  Franklin Park with its tree lined paths and conservatory.
transit: Uber and Lyft are available and there is a Cota bus stop right in front of the house.  2.5 miles from downtown Columbus and close to the airport.
access: Guests will have access to the entire house except the other private bedrooms. Large fenced in back yard is ideal for four legged guests as well!
interaction: I'm available to help guests as much as needed since I live in the house.  Whether you're looking for total privacy or you are new to Airbnb and would like some more guidance during your trip I can accommodate you.
house_rules: I take a lot of pride in my home and I ask that you treat the property and people around you with respect. Please clean up after yourself and remember to lock the doors when you come and go. No smoking in the house. Please be LGBT friendly. Make yourself at home!
host_about:
I’ve been an Airbnb host since 2014 and since I love to travel I have also been a guest with other hosts in the US and internationally. People always ask if it’s weird to have strangers come and stay in my home with me and the answer has always been “not once!” I really love having the opportunity to share my home and city of Columbus Ohio with travelers from all over the world. The review system is a wonderful way to feel out a potential guest or host and I truly have never had a guest I didn’t enjoy.

When I bought my home in 2008 it had no plumbing, boarded up windows, and had been the ugly house on the block for a long time. I’m proud of the work I’ve done to bring a charming historic home back to life and update it in a way that kept much of the original character. Be careful asking questions about the process because I may not stop telling stories for a while.

We spend most of our time in Chicago, IL, and as much time as our schedule permits in our Columbus, OH vacation home (only 1/2 kidding.)  Our home is beautifully decorated by the owner. All furnishings from bedding, paintings, and furniture is from The Painted Lady, a high end furniture store in Chicago, IL. It's an excellent place for family and/or friends dinners, or just relax during a long weekend get away.  Our kitchen is right out of a French Villa with hardwood counter tops, white tile floor, and commercial grade stove. neighborhood_overview: German Village is THE Neighborhood in Columbus, OH. The best restaurants, bars, and shopping are all within blocks of our home. Try Lindy's or G. Michael's Bistro for a classy lunch or dinner. Katzinger's is one of the best deli's outside NYC IMO. Jenni's Ice Cream is local, delicious, and 4 blocks away. Full scale grocery store, Giant Eagle, is 3 blocks away. Hey Hey Bar & Grill is an A+ neighborhood bar "where everybody knows your name." Simply call us if you're looking for dining, shopping, and where/how to have fun suggestions.
transit: Parking is on street and plentiful. We offer 2 Schwin Cruiser bicycles (guy's & girls) for guests to explore or simply ride to the grocery store down the street.
access: Entire 2500 sq. ft home open to our guests.
interaction: We live in Chicago, IL 20 - 25 days of the month when not in Columbus, OH. Guest have our home 100% to yourself.
house_rules: After a few unfortunate stays, we ask any/all parties are limited to 10 guests. It's a quiet neighborhood, and we don't want our neighbors inconvenienced, or worse, from late night parties. Simply respect the our home and our neighbors as you would in your own house.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is pretty dynamic.  Archways of colored lights span High Street, the main drag through the Short North.  Originally a commercial warehouse district in the early 1900’s, the Short North experienced a renaissance driven by artists and gallery owners in the 1980’s.  Now full of galleries, shops and restaurants, murals, craft breweries and live theater it stays pretty lively day and night. It is THE most walkable district in the city and quite safe, although it is an urban neighborhood, where it is advisable to keep your eyes open and wits about you. We have always felt quite safe here the past 25 years including raising our 2 children. And if you tire of walking you can always jump on the “C-bus” (every few minutes along High street) a free city bus dedicated exclusively to downtown, the Short North and even German Village just to the south of downtown.  The Short North itself is flanked to the east and west by two older residential neighborhoods, Victorian Village and It
notes: You will be one block from the Kroger grocery store and the liquor store and North High Brewing, a craft micro-brewery and a little Russian bakery to the right a few store fronts on High Street.  Parking on the street in front of the house is free and not subject to permit.  Which means it can some times be tricky on weekends.  Let us know when you are arriving and we will do the best we can to insure you an available spot out front.
transit: Your “Pied a Terre” is less than one block from High Street which bisects the City of Columbus east and west.  It is also the street which serves as the main artery through the Short North. It’s a great place to walk, look around, duck into shops, cafes, restaurants, start walking again.  There are also buses running up and down High Street which will take you anywhere in the city, but the real delight is the “C-Bus” a FREE city bus dedicated to serving just downtown and areas immediately adjacent including the Short North, The Arena district, the Greater Columbus Convention Center, The North Market, Downtown Columbus, and German Village immediately south of Downtown.    There are also inexpensive CoGo bicycles at several rental kiosks up and down High Street to let you explore at greater speed.    And of course you can also walk or bus  up to the OSU campus, just 5 blocks away -- the OSU Horseshoe Stadium a mere 10 blocks.  50,000 + students and all the infrastructure to support a tee
access: Entry is gained by opening a combination lock box for the key to a breezeway entry door.  You will have your own private kitchen and full bath with large shower (no tub)  hanging space for clothes under the loft bed and dresser. Please note that you will need to climb the ladder to get to the loft bed. Be sure you will be comfortable with that. There is a small patio with table, umbrella and 4 chairs in the rear -  semi-separate but adjacent  to urban back yard.
interaction: We love hosting and meeting new people and are available for as much as you need from us to get you situated and oriented to the neighborhood and the city at large.   We live in the front of the house and are generally around and available to answer questions and make recommendations etc. We are generally never more than a text or call away.
house_rules: This is our home and we love sharing it with people who treat it like a home.  No Smoking please, as the air circulates throughout the house.  No pets please.  We generally go to sleep around midnight so things should quiet down about then.
host_about: Hello, I am a married  father of 2  recently grown sons. My wife, Julie, and I are now offering part of our overgrown Victorian house to Air BnB guests.  By day I am an attorney in general practice and landlord; Julie is a psychotherapist. By free time, we are musicians (mainly a cappella vocalists though with some harmonica, clarinet, a very little tuba and hand drums thrown in.  We  enjoy jamming and improvising with others). I am a motorcyclist and lover of small affordable British roadsters, a mechanical tinkerer. We  are rehabbers/restorers of old houses with avid interests in music of all kinds, art, books, film, food (the more local and authentic the better), all manner of whiskeys and especially conversation.  I am  French by birth, and still fluent. I would say we are  Midwestern/progressive  by long residence and disposition; usually gregarious, though sometimes quieter and observant. We like to travel fairly light, although we are probably  a little "long in the tooth" to be truly "spartan."  I suppose our  style of Air b&b hosting is to  provide a comfortable safe staging ground and general guidance from which guests can explore on their own.  Current life motto might be something like "The best revenge is living engaged!"

name: Country house on horse farm
summary: This country house is situated on a 20 acre horse farm. We have several well mannered pets so people with allergies will probably not be comfortable here. We live a simple, quiet life and welcome travelers with similar lifestyles. There is a box fan available and good windows but I rarely use the central air. The house stays naturally cool most of the time. There is reliable WIFI in the rooms. If you have trouble connecting please let me  know. We have limited band width it can cause problems.

summary: Spacious attic crow's nest 5 blocks from OSU and steps from Short North nightlife, public transport and city center. Comfy beds, high ceilings, private kitchen and bath - Cozy and roomy.
space: This is a very large 2 bedroom, 1 bath, attic apartment (about 1100 sq. ft.) nestled in the eaves of a monstrous 1880’s brick Queen Ann in the Short North arts district in Columbus Ohio.  It manages to be cozy despite nearly 10 foot ceilings because the entire attic is lined in unfinished poplar wood and floored with rustic wide plank pine.  The “Hangar” has 2 big bedrooms at opposite ends of the 70 foot long apartment; one with a Queen size real bed the other with a Full size real bed.  In addition, there are 2 twin trundle beds and the living room futon which unfolds into a full sized futon bed for sleeping.   There is a full-function kitchen with gas stove, 2 under-counter refrigerators and microwave.  No dishwasher.  The living room is outfitted with futon couch, armchairs, 42 inch flat screen TV with cable.  There is one bath with tub and shower.  The apartment is equipped with WIFI and central air conditioning

The real delight is the “C-Bus,” a FREE city bus dedicated to serving just downtown and areas immediately adjacent including the Short North, the Arena District, the Greater Columbus Convention Center, The North Market, Downtown Columbus, and German Village immediately south of Downtown.    There are also inexpensive CoGo bicycles at several rental kiosks up and down High Street to let you explore at greater speed. If you have a Car2Go membership in your city we have Car2Go smart cars all over the city center. Of course there also UBER cars available.   You ca
access: Upon arrival, you will access the Hangar through the entry foyer of our home.  You will have keys to the front door and entry to the foyer which is used by us only for entry and exit. You won't be coming through our living space.  Climb the staircase up to the 2nd floor landing where you will enter your keyed access to the attic staircase.  The 3rd floor is entirely yours.
interaction: We love hosting and meeting new people and are available for as much as you need from us to get you situated and oriented to the neighborhood and the city at large.   We live in the front of the house on the 1st and 2nd floors, and are generally around and available to answer questions and make recommendations etc. We are never more than a text or call away.  We will generally be home to properly greet you on arrival.  In the event we cannot be there you will still have unhindered access to your 3rd floor Hangar, and we will have a surrogate host nearby in the event you need or lack anything.  You may see us on the 1st and 2nd floor, but usually only in passing or up and down the stairs as you enter or exit your apartment.
house_rules: This is our home and we love sharing it with people who treat it like a home.  No Smoking please, as the air circulates throughout the house.  No pets please.  We generally go to sleep around midnight so things should quiet down about then.
host_about: Hello, I am a married  father of 2  recently grown sons. My wife, Julie, and I are now offering part of our overgrown Victorian house to Air BnB guests.  By day I am an attorney in general practice and landlord; Julie is a psychotherapist. By free time, we are musicians (mainly a cappella vocalists though with some harmonica, clarinet, a very little tuba and hand drums thrown in.  We  enjoy jamming and improvising with others). I am a motorcyclist and lover of small affordable British roadsters, a mechanical tinkerer. We  are rehabbers/restorers of old houses with avid interests in music of all kinds, art, books, film, food (the more local and authentic the better), all manner of whiskeys and especially conversation.  I am  French by birth, and still fluent. I would say we are  Midwestern/progressive  by long residence and disposition; usually gregarious, though sometimes quieter and observant. We like to travel fairly light, although we are probably  a little "long in the tooth" to be truly "spartan."  I suppose our  style of Air b&b hosting is to  provide a comfortable safe staging ground and general guidance from which guests can explore on their own.  Current life motto might be something like "The best revenge is living engaged!"

summary: Our clean and modern single family home is centrally located in historical Clintonville.  Two off-street parking spots are available for parking as well as a quaint patio and private back yard. Only a 10 minute drive to OSU, Short North, and downtown.
space: Our space is full of character with with a mixture of vintage and modern decor all throughout. Wood floors and classic architecture lend to the feel along with whimsical and colorful antiques. It is a very cozy space that you will feel right at home in. This home features a newly renovated kitchen and bathrooms, three bedrooms, and plenty of seating around our rustic kitchen table. Park in our garage and freeway access is right around the corner so you can easily access any part of the city.

neighborhood_overview: *Please note* While we are located on a busy street, the garage entrance and fenced in back yard provide privacy and we take every effort to block sound with new windows and fans in the home. Clintonville is a very family-friendly neighborhood. Our street corner connects to the lovely Olentangy Trail. It's a wonderful trail to bike, walk, or jog.
notes: You can feel comfortable accessing our home at any time after the check-in time with our lock box and park in the garage. We have worked to provide every amenity for short to long term stays.
transit: We recommend Uber as the best form of public transportation in Columbus. There is also a COTA bus stop in front of the home.
access: Guests will have high speed internet access and a flatscreen SmartTV with Apple TV (Netflix account available) and a Bluetooth sound bar. There will be a binder full of instructions on getting connected both inside and outside of the home.
interaction: We are happy to communicate over Airbnb messaging or through calls and texts. We encourage guests to reach out with any questions or concerns throughout the booking and hosting process.
house_rules: Please note our cancellation policy before booking. No smoking, parties, or unauthorized guests. Our home has many valuable items so we ask that no shoes are worn in the house.  We reserve the right to charge an extra fee if these house rules are not followed. *Due to demand & cleaning schedules, check in & out times are firm (check in any time after 4pm and check out any time before 11am). A fee of $50 will be charged if guests arrive before check in or stay past check out*
host_about: We are a married couple who love to travel the world and experience life to the fullest while showing love to others. This past year we have been airbnb guests in Chicago, IL, New York, NY, San Diego, CA, and were able to travel to The Bahamas, London, and Paris. We love to adventure together and meet new people around the globe!

name: Private Room Near Downtown
summary: All the comforts of home. Close to Downtown, German Village and Childrens Hospital. Scioto Mile, Columbus Commons, and the Short North are a stone throw away. Enjoy a peaceful turn of the century home that's a great place to relax. Comfy, Queen size bed, internet and street parking.
space: This cool American Four Square home, located in the Livingston Park neighborhood was built in the early part of the twentieth century and is part of the historical fabric on Columbus. This was one of the first neighborhoods to have garages, and is also formerly known as the streetcar district. I have completed several rehab projects already -- so the place is pretty comfortable.  You room has a queen-sized bed with plenty of pillows, a dresser and a comfy rocking chair.  Some nights you can see Rhodes Tower light up in different colors from the window which faces downtown. If you are a reader, I have plenty of books throughout the house, and in the room there are also several books on writing.

neighborhood_overview: Columbus has become an interesting city. I love living here because I'm so close to everything that's going on. It's an urban neighborhood and I've got some nice neighbors.
notes: I have shower gel, shampoo and conditioner in the shower that you can use, along with clean towels. I also have a basket of toiletry items if you should forget your toothpaste, toothbrush etc. so please help yourself. I also have an iron and ironing board.  Just let me know if you need to use it and I'll set it up in the hall outside of your room for you. Also, not noted in the kitchen photo is that I do have a microwave that you can use. I also have a blow dryer available upon request.  I have two yorkies and ask that you NOT let them outside when you come in and out.  A note of caution is that they can be a little barky at times but it doesn't last very long. It is usually the first bit of movement --  they will let you know that they are there but then they calm down.  For the most part they are pretty quiet, although they can get pretty rambunctious when they play.  I have completed several rehab projects already, but you'll see that there are a few things that still need to be don
transit: Children's Hospital is 4 blocks from here and there is bus service in and around there. There is also a COGO bike rack on Livingston in front of the hospital. Also, if you walk up to Main Street there is a bus service that is pretty fast.  There is street parking in front of my house and on Mooberry (there are no parking restrictions.) COFFEE/BREAKFAST spots include: Alchemy, Starbucks in German Village and Winans; which is also in German Village (best chai latte around). For a great bakery/coffee go to Fox in the Snow on 4th. Skillet in German Village is also recommended. GROCERIES - (for longer stays) there is a Kroger (grocery store) in the Brewery District @ 150 W. Sycamore Street that has a nice organic section.  If you're really in to eating organic, Trader Joes and Whole Food are at Easton.  Easton has a really nice shopping area with several places to eat.  I shop for groceries at the Whole Foods on Lane Avenue west of 315 in Upper Arlington.     NIGHT LIFE - there is an app ca
access: In addition to your private room, guests will have access to the bathroom (which is shared), the living room, dining room, and kitchen (hey -- you are welcome to cook but the dishes will be calling your name if you stay longer than a day - smile.) I don't mind sharing meals if I cook. If there are bagels on the island, you're welcome to one. I have plenty of coffee and tea to choose from. I also have an area in the fridge marked off that you are welcome to use while you're here including a drawer. You are welcome to work in the dining room or living room, whatever you prefer.   Please be CAREFUL when opening the door so my dogs don't get out.
interaction: I live in the house so you will see me here and there but I will respect your privacy if I sense that you would rather be alone.  I enjoy meeting new people and can be as chatty as you like.  My dogs are pretty friendly and like attention, so please let me know if they are being intrusive at all and I will take care of it.   I've lived in Columbus for 20 years and happy to direct you throughout the city.
house_rules: This is always a 'fun' topic and I do have a few things to mention. I'm not into anyone else coming over (meaning no guests). No illegal substances (I have friends in law enforcement). Don't mind light drinking but no drunkenness. No smoking inside the house. I do have an ashtray on the front porch that you are welcome to use.  No loud music please.  Pierre -- my dog is a runner.  Please be very careful when you open the front door as he is quick to run out. If he does get out, I have a squeaky toy nearby (in the dining room) to use that will encourage him to come back inside (if you chase him he will run...). Also -- when you arrive I will show you how to lock and unlock the front door. I have a code for one lock; which I will provide, a handle lock (on the inside wooden door), and a lock for the storm door.  I'll walk you through it -- once you do it it's easy peasy....
host_about: As a career management coach, I love helping individuals find careers that are rewarding and fulfilling.  I help people define their direction, package themselves and connect and sell themselves (yes, even those folks who DON"T like sales....).  In my spare time I love anything creative.  Dancing is a hobby and passion.

neighborhood_overview: Westgate is a beautiful neighborhood surrounded by charm,  character and lots of trees. No cookie cutter homes here, all the homes have their own personality.  People here are very friendly and down to earth. We also have great neighborhood watch program.  There are also paths to walk and parks nearby.
notes: We have 5 real beds and we use high-end bed sheets. All bedsheets are absolutely white with high thread count. Therefore we request you to NOT bring food, beverages in any of the bedrooms. We try our best to keep allergies and sensitive skin in mind so we DO NOT use harsh chemicals to clean the sheets. We request to remove the makeup before settling in the beds. Stained bedding will need to be replaced and could be  the reason for forfeited security deposit.
transit: There is plenty of parking on site and on the street. Getting around- Cota Bus Lines are close by (on Broad St) for greater access to Columbus.  Uber is always closer :) Also If I am in town, I'd be happy to give you a ride.
access: All guests will have access to the basement and main floor. We have TVs on main floor living room and in the basement (Netflix youtube etc available on both Smart Tvs). Guests may use the laundry facilities, if you are at the house for a longer period (over 4 days). Guests will also have kitchen privileges for light breakfast cooking. We do not have a range hood and to prevent lingering food odor, we want to limit the light cooking to 10-15 min. Please feel free to reach out to us if you have any questions regarding this.
interaction: Work keeps us away so there is a good chance we may not meet unless intentional however you are welcomed to call me at anytime of your stay and I'd be available to help. When we are in town, we can socialize or let you enjoy your vacation in peace...…it's totally your choice.  :)
house_rules: A. Washer and dryer to be used only if you are staying for 4 days and more.  B.  As mentioned before to prevent lingering food odor - limit cooking time for only 10 mins. Please NO extensive cooking. you are welcomed to bring pre packed food and heat it. C. There is a garage on the property but that is locked and not included in this listing. So please do not access the garage.
host_about:
Hello! I am Rue. I love early morning sunshine, travel experiences, aged wine, fresh coffee, nature and its beautiful endless skies.

After working with various corporates for more than a decade I decided to start my own business. Since we moved for business, I was able to use my home on AIRBNB.

While decorating this house we kept comfort and design in forefront of our mind. I open our home to Airbnb guests from all cultures, backgrounds, and nationalities. I look forward to building wonderful new friendships with people around the globe. Thank you for considering our place to stay, hope to talk to you soon. :)

summary: Quick walk to OSU or all Short North has to offer!  Whether you are visiting OSU or one of Columbus' many conventions, this is the perfect location.  There are many shops and restaurants within walking distance, as well as parks and trails.   This is in a duplex on a beautiful quiet street. The bedroom is simple and spacious and the kitchen is great! I primarily reside in the other half of the duplex. Check the getting around section for distances to OSU/convention center/bus stops.
space: Quiet street, yet close to everything. Spacious bedroom.

Quiet street, yet close to everything. Spacious bedroom. You will have access to the bedroom, living room, kitchen, bathroom, and front porch. Feel free to use fridge, sink, spices, oils, for cooking etc. Please just clean up after yourself and be respectful of pans, knives, etc. I've been a resident of Columbus for many years, so I know a lot about what it has to offer, though that is constantly changing - for the better!  I am more than happy to help you get around or to offer suggestions for dining or ac
neighborhood_overview: Great quiet street very close to all the action on High St.  Beautiful trees and beautiful homes will greet you as you turn on to my street.
notes: I have a two year old dog.  Though she is incredibly well behaved and on her way to being super trained...she still is an exuberant puppy.  So she may jump up on you or may try to steal your socks. I used to have a roommate, but she has since moved, so this room functions mainly as a closet and storage space and crafting area.
transit: If you are driving, there is plenty of free street parking out front (again, it is a quiet street, so you won't need to worry about your car.)   In addition, there is a great free shuttle bus with a stop just a couple minutes walk from my place.  It travels up and down high street between Short North and German Village, including stops at the Arena and Convention Center  (the convention center is 1.5 miles away). There is also a regular bus that will take you anywhere in and around Columbus for a fare and there are a few stops within 1/10th of a mile of my place. It is .6 miles to South Campus and further depending on where you are going. There are multiple transit options, including COTA's fare bus .1 miles away, COTA's free CBUS .3 miles, and OSUs free CABS bus is .6 miles away.
access: You will have access to the bedroom, living room, kitchen, bathroom, and front porch. Feel free to use fridge, sink, spices, oils, for cooking etc. Please just clean up after yourself and be respectful of pans, knives, etc.
interaction: I've been a resident of Columbus for many years, so I know a lot about what it has to offer, though that is constantly changing - for the better!  I am more than happy to help you get around or to offer suggestions for dining or activities.
house_rules: No smoking or partying in the house or on the porch please. There will be a charge if any smoking is discovered. Check Wireless Info section for WiFi network and password.  If you use the wireless network, you agree to use it only for legal purposes and promise not to use it for illegal uploading, downloading, or other illegal activities.
host_about: Low-key, clean, quiet. 33 years old.  Friendly.  Love travelling!  It is nice to be able to use shared space and have the comfort of a home and kitchen over the utilitarianism of a hotel.  Plus, I'd rather put money in the pocket of a real person than a hotel chain.  Non smoker...not a parter.  Love outdoors activities and love animals!

name: Clintonville Charmer That's Close to it All!
summary: This Clintonville charmer has everything you need during your Columbus stay. Our house is in the heart of the city & a short 5-min drive to Mapfre Stadium, Ohio State Fairgrounds, Ohio Stadium or the Wexner Medical Center. It's a 10-min drive downtown or to the Short North! You can catch multiple busses in less than a block's walk. Stroll in any direction to hit restaurants, a movie theater, or a grocery store. I trust you'll love your stay here just as much as we love living here.
space: We are Columbus-lovers who decided to venture out west to enjoy mountain-living in Colorado for awhile; so we're opening up our home to guests like you! This neighborhood and this house are so special to us and we hope you feel as cozy as we do here. The yard (weather pending) is one of my favorite things about the house, whether kicking back on the deck, or roasting marshmallows around the fire pit, you'll find your own little piece of zen while spending time back there.

name: Library Park Guesthouse
summary: Our guesthouse is in a separate building behind our residence in the East Town Street Historic District. Within a ten minute walk are the Main Library; Topiary Park; Grant Hospital; Columbus Museum of Art; Columbus College of Art and Design; Franklin University; Capital University Law School; Columbus Commons with outdoor concernts and events; the Columbus Riverfront; the historic Ohio, Palace and Southern Theaters; restaurants; and CBus, the free circulator bus on High Street.
space: We are historic preservation consultants and are delighted to have this newly-built space to offer to travelers. It is located in a downtown historic district. It is a well-designed, comfortable and well-equipped one bedroom apartment. Special features include a private outdoor balcony with table and chairs, new pillowtop mattress, a kitchen designed for gourmet cooking, wireless internet, 43" smart tv in living room and 24" tv with cable in the bedroom. Large closet, plenty of storage for longer stays. Single inflatable mattress is available at no extra charge for an additional guest.

neighborhood_overview: The East Town Street Historic District is located in downtown Columbus. It is known for the Topiary Park, which was modeled after artist Georges Seurat's painting "A Sunday in the Park on the Isle of La Grand Jatte." Other nearby amenities are the Columbus Metropolitan Library, rated #1 in the nation on a consistent basis; the newly-expanded Columbus Museum of Art; Grant Hospital; Franklin University, Columbus College of Art and Design, Capital Law School and Columbus State University. Our neighborhood is walking distance to Columbus Commons Park and the Scioto Mile along the Scioto River. Rental bikes are available across the street, if you want to explore the city on two wheels. Other great neighborhoods are nearby, including German Village, Olde Towne East, the Short North, the North Market, Italian Village, Victorian Village and the Arena District.
notes: Columbus is cool, creative and fun, with vibrant arts, top-ranked cultural attractions, innovative culinary offerings, lively entertainment districts, exciting sports, and an open, welcoming spirit.
transit: Many options for getting around -- walking, CoGo rental bikes, CBUS (free circulator bus), regular bus stop a few steps away and off-street parking so you can leave your car behind and experience the city in other ways. Of course, Uber, is always an option, too.
access: Guests will have full use of the apartment. There is one off-street parking space available. Access is flexible with a pass code for the front door lock.
interaction: Owners have lived downtown for 30 years, they can provide advice about the city and its distinctive neighborhoods, cultural facilities, and places to eat, shop and have fun.
house_rules: This is a brand new apartment. We expect guests to treat it with care and respect. No animals, no smoking, no drugs or unlawful activities allowed. We want you to enjoy your stay and we want to welcome you back again in the future. Events or parties may be allowed upon approval of host in advance.
host_about: My husband and I are historic preservation consultants. We love history, architecture, art, vibrant urban areas, interesting places, local foods, and travel. We also love to share our city with others.

name: Historic Townhome in Heart of German Village
summary: Historic 3 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom end-unit townhome in the heart of German Village, a one-of-a-kind neighborhood featured on the National Register of Historic Places.  Located less than 1 block from Schiller Park!
space: This townhome has all of the charm and architectural character you'd expect from a German Village home including rustic, original pine floors, beautiful unpainted woodwork and moldings, newly renovated bathrooms, tall ceilings, and comfy yet elegant decor to make you feel right at home.  In fact, it was featured on the 2017 German Village Haus Und Garten Tour! There is about 1200 sq. ft of living space inside the unit, which includes a living room, dining room, kitchen, 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms.  Each room was designed and decorated by the owners with a mix of high-end furnishings from Crate & Barrel + Restoration Hardware, antique/vintage finds, and fun artwork. Fully stocked kitchen with granite counters, shaker style cabinets, and simple black appliances.  Private fenced-in backyard with patio and gas grill is an urban oasis, perfect for enjoying outdoor time with friends and family.  The local grocery store, Giant Eagle, is less than 3 blocks from the house, making it easy to r

Fully stocked kitchen with granite counters, shaker style cabinets, and simple black appliances.  Private fence
neighborhood_overview: German Village is a vibrant place to stay, shop, and play.  Walking the brick sidewalks, you'll discover a neighborhood full of urban gardens, beautiful historic homes built over 100 years ago, and carefully dispersed small businesses.  As said on the German Village visitor's website, “What we have can't be replicated. We live this way — and protect it with great passion — because we understand that what we have is a neighborhood like no other."  We couldn't agree more. Schiller Park is the main park in the neighborhood and is located less than one block from the property, making it easy to go for a walk/run, have a picnic, bring the kids to the playground, and enjoy free performances of Shakespeare in the Park in the summertime.  The park also has basketball courts and tennis courts.   This Townhome is a short walk to coffee shops, restaurants, bars, grocery stores, and the famous Jeni's Ice Cream.  It is also less than 5 miles of the most popular attractions in Columbus: 1 mile to Do
notes: 1 - This is an end-unit townhome, which means that there is one shared wall with our neighbor.  Our guests must be conscious of this during their stay and keep noise to a minimum at all times.  As always, we DO NOT allow loud, disruptive behavior and ask that all guests observe quiet hours between 10pm - 8am.  This is not the house for you if you are looking to have a party or bring the party back with you.  Registered, paying guests only. 2 - On-street parking only (usually available in front or within a few houses of the property). There is NO off-street parking available. 3 - While the bathrooms are newly designed and renovated, they are small.  One bathroom has an antique clawfoot tub, which is about 30” off the floor and requires a step up.  The other bathroom has a walk-in shower. 4 - All bedrooms and full bathrooms are located on the 2nd floor.  There is one small powder room located on the 1st floor, off the dining room. 5 - This home is over 100 years old.  The walls are plast
transit: Grocery/pharmacy, coffee shops (including Starbucks), and restaurants/bars are all located within a short walk of the townhome.  There are buses that run throughout German Village, but we'd recommend having a car if you're looking to travel around the city, as they aren't always reliable. The one bus that we'd suggest is a free CBUS circulator bus that runs from High & Sycamore (.8 miles away - 15 min walk through the Village) up through Downtown and into the Short North. Lots of people take this bus (more than the standard bus service in Columbus), it's on time (usually!), and runs every 10-15 min 7 days a week. For more info & route map, search the web for "COTA CBUS Columbus." Or, ask us and we'll send it to you ;) Taxi's and Ubers are also available to bring you where you need to go if you'd like to avoid having a car.
access: Guests have access to the whole home (except for the basement) and private backyard, as described in the listing.
interaction: We have keyless locks on our doors, so guests can check-in late as needed.   We encourage guests to ask us questions and communicate w/us throughout their stay if they need anything at all.  We're always happy to help!
house_rules: We expect guests to treat our home as if they were staying at their best friend's home. Please treat it with respect and know that a lot of work went into it. Smoking, house parties, and rowdy behavior are not permitted on the property.  This is not the house for you if you are looking to have a party or bring the party back with you. Guests are expected to be respectful of the neighbors by keeping noise levels to a minimum, especially between the hours of 10pm and 8am. Guests must leave the property in the same condition as it was when Guests arrived.  The house is available to registered, paying Guests only. No additional guests are allowed inside the house without consent from the Homeowner.  Homeowner is not responsible for any accidents, injuries or illness that occurs while on the premises of this property or its facilities. host_about: We're Bryan & Catherine, a married couple with a love for entrepreneurship, interior design, travel, and QT with family & friends.  We moved to Columbus from NYC in 2012 in search of a better quality of life, and purchased our first home as a part of our move.  We spent a few years updating it and adding special touches to it, and through that process realized our mutual passion for design, renovation, and working together.  We have been hosting for over 4 years now and have welcomed more than 1500 guests into our properties.  You can find out more about us, our businesses and our work on Instagram @beginninginthemiddle and on our blog, Beginning in the Middle.

neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is one of the Midwest’s best kept secrets. There is a huge variety of unique shops, bars and restaurants, and art galleries along High Street and a number of annual events that take place year-round. We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Weinland Park, a cool, urban area on the East side of High St above 5th Ave.   Is the neighborhood safe? We live nearby and feel the neighborhood is relatively safe.  Please note this is the city- we do have petty crime in the Short North and University area, and always advise to practice common sense such as not leaving valuables in your car (we have not had any issues at our apartments, I state this because we are in the city) and walk with a buddy at night on well-lit, busy roads such as High Street, Summit, and 5th Ave. Near the following: • Restaurants- The Table, Condados
notes: • Housekeeping service is per stay, not per night. Additional cleaning visits can be arranged for longer stays if needed.  Visits must be paid in advance and are non-refundable if visits are cancelled. Please inquire when booking. • Pack n Play, high chair, and/or Queen air bed available upon request- please let us know your needs prior so we can prepare all the necessary items. • Please be courteous to neighbors- Noise must be keep to a minimum after 10 p.m. This is one of two units with a shared wall.   • There is no handicap access. There are two steps to enter the front of the house.  • Guests with allergies and related medical issues and/or sensitivities- cleanliness is one of our top priorities, however we cannot 100% guarantee that the apartment is free of pet dander, cigarette smoke, air fresheners/cleaning product scents, or any other elements that may trigger a medical problem or sensitivity. Please note we cannot issue refunds due to the reasons above. •  Street Sweeping on
transit: We are super close to High Street (two blocks East). You can easily walk to dozens of restaurants and shopping. All other locations can be easily reached a number of ways: Taxis --- Uber -- COTA (Central Ohio Transit Authority) bus --- CoGo (Rental Bikes) --- Car 2 Go (Car Rentals) --- CBUS circulator About the CBUS circulator- It's FREE transportation from the Short North through downtown, all the way to German Village. Bus stops are at many points along High Street.  The closest stop is just a few blocks South from the apartment on 3rd Ave. It's about a $5-10 Uber ride to downtown. PARKING This apartment has 2 off-street parking spots.  It is accessible by alleyway off of Summit St. or 5th Ave. Directions will be given upon reservation. There is also permit-free street parking available on both sides of Summit St. in front of the house. It’s usually easy to find a spot. It can get a little busy during the evenings but you can still find parking close by. Our guests have had no issues
access: You will have access to the entire apartment, shared fence-in backyard, and rear parking area (see Getting Around section below for parking details) Hours of Access: Check-in is 3 p.m.  Checkout is 11 a.m. NOTE: Early check-in and/or late check-out is $35 and must be approved by host *prior* to check-in.
interaction: We are available to guests by email, phone, or text. We know our neighborhood very well (!) and care about our community- let us know when you need something or have questions!
house_rules: Please note that all rules stem from previous experience & are strictly enforced. Property has exterior surveillance. • Check-in is 3 p.m.  • Checkout is 11 A.M. • Please do not turn off the heat during the winter or air conditioning during summer at any time. Always keep the thermostat set between 65 F/ 18.3 C to 75F/ 24 C.   • Throw away all excessive garbage in any large green exterior trash cans located in the rear alley. Excessive garbage is anything that does not fit into the kitchen and/or bedroom garbage cans. • If the apartment is left trashed (beyond normal use), we will request some or all of the security deposit.  In other words, treat this home with respect. • No parties, this is strictly enforced.  You will be asked to leave, no refunds. • All guests must be paying registered guests.  No additional guests allowed without prior written consent of the homeowner.  • Any evidence or smell of cigarette, marijuana, etc. will be AUTOMATIC loss of deposit. No burning of anything

For graduate students or lovers of MCM furniture, or those wanting a room that features a whole lot of amenities and the privacy of chair/desk/sofa/closet/bed all in one retro space, this is your room! neighborhood_overview: We're located smack-dab in the heart of Clintonville -- a charming, quirky, progressive neighborhood just on the north side of the campus of The Ohio State University. Our street, like the streets surrounding us, runs between Indianola and High Street -- the main arts, culture and food vein of Columbus. The neighborhood is a mix of classic 1920s Clintonville Bungalows and Dutch revival houses, and a pattern-blend of darling 1950s salt-box houses and cape cods -- of which our place is one! Our street is a great strolling street, with huge shade trees closer to High Street; and we're just a hop skip and a jump away from some of the city's best amenities: coffee (Global Gallery); farmers' markets (the Clintonville Farmers' Market at Dunedin and High!); co-ops (the Clintonville Community Market at Crestview and Calumet); and delicious eats (Northstar at Beechwold; Harvest and Acre by Weber). Plus, we're ridiculously close to the Park of Roses/Whetstone Rec Center/Whetstone Library; there,
notes: We have a lovely and very friendly pup named Isaly -- she's a border collie mix, and will probably not only request, but demand that you pet her and give her some belly rubs! We haven't heard any allergy complaints yet; but if you're seriously allergic to dogs, you may want to weigh that in your request. She'll stay in the main spaces of the house and sleep in our bedroom -- unless you let her into your room, in which case I'm sure she'd be happy to snuggle pro bono! She can be a bit shy around some folks, and has some funny fears (large flat circular shapes like manhole covers, etc.), so we'll want to introduce you all first. You'll fall in love, we swear -- we just ask, since we live not too far off the street, to ask us if you'd like to take her out to play in the backyard! We also have a very sweet matching cat, Nell, who's around some of the time; she's a pretty chill cat but might sit on your head if you want her to :) We're super-close to main bus-lines in the neighborhood; but
transit: We're SUPER close to the major COTA bus lines through Columbus -- the #2 and #4 buses have stops right on High Street and Indianola, on either end of our street! These will take you to campus, downtown, or anywhere you'd like. High Street is also just a short stroll or bike-ride away; and the Global Gallery Coffee shop, Boline apothecary, and Broadway block of Clintonville businesses are all within walking distance. The bike path is also just right across High Street, and, if you've got a bike or borrow ours, can get you almost anyplace you'd like to go in Columbus, with gorgeous fall colors and scenic river sounds to boot!
access: Your room is a cozy, all-inclusive retro den -- you'll have a swell couch, comfy bed, desk, retro sittin' chair, bedside table ... the works! We provide linens, extra blankets and a set of guest towels. You'll have full access to the bathroom (please do see House Rules for details on fragrances/chemicals), but we do not allow kitchen or living room access (only for getting water) or fridge storage, unless you specifically arrange with us in advance (and a fee will apply).  We also provide filtered water and lots of free cuddles from our pup Isaly! :) Parking is available on-street across the street from our home.
interaction: We love getting to know new folks from around the world, and sharing the love and our recommendations for our beloved city! That said, we are both in school and juggling projects that often follow us home from work; but we'd be happy to hang out, chat, or even come out for a drink or a bite to eat if we're available! We've modeled our AirBNB guest philosophy on that of our own favorite host, Margie in Atlanta: we're committed to being around and hanging out if that's what you need, but we're also perfectly content -- as introverts ourselves! -- to just give you some much needed time to relax & recharge in your own space. So, as much or as little interaction as you'd like.
house_rules: SHORT RULES: -- NO perfume, cologne, hairspray, aerosols or chemicals in the house: hosts have Multiple Chemical Sensitivity. Guests in violation will be asked to leave. This is also for the safety of other Chemical & Fragrance-free guests. We provide all-natural guest bar soap. -- No smoking -- We don't use A/C and *we* control the temperature. Feel free to make a request; but this is a small shared home, and we try to keep things moderate. -- Shoes off by front door, please! -- NO friends or outside visitors who aren't on your reservation. -- NO kitchen or fridge use, sorry. It's for us only. -- Be respectful! Treat your hosts and any other guests with kindness and respect. We demand & expect that. This isn't a hotel; it's our home. -- Please don't shout or yell. Quiet hours after 10pm. -- Inform us in advance if you plan to come back in after midnight. Add'l fees may apply, esp. on work/school nights. Send us a message BEFORE you book if you'll be driving Uber/Lyft all night, or out
host_about:
hi there! i'm jess -- a folklorist, oral historian and  columbus, ohio native with a really amazing border collie pup, named isaly. 

my partner jeff & i are both currently grad students -- he studies the history of industrialization and labor in the u.s. south through a history of science & technology phd. program based in philly, and i'm a folklorist and oral historian who works on the history of sustainable agriculture, food & environmental justice, & everyday perceptions of environmental toxicity. that means i get to road-trip around this fine state alot, asking people questions about how they connect food and environment health, and how they've had their lives shaped  around those questions. 

as a folklorist and oral historian, i believe in the power of everyday people's embodied and lived knowledge and experience; and my work is in documenting, interpreting and helping to present these powerful perspectives to wider audiences, to create conversations for change. i try to bring these passions to everything in my life.

i'm interested in the ways people connect food, health and environmental concern; and movement histories and futures of activism around the stuff that makes us sick, and the stuff that makes us healthy. basically, if you wanna talk farm magazines from the 1950s or the poisons & boons of various audio recorders or just like food in general, i'm yr grrl! 

because of my own history of exposure and chemical sensitivity, we try to keep (as much as possible) a non-toxic home, free of meats, chemical cleaners, and scents. and, if you come in summer or fall, you're free to help harvest goodies from our bountiful yard garden! (the "yarden.") it can get a bit weedy this time of year; but it's all chem-free and very well loved.

columbus, ohio is my hometown (and my favorite city on earth), and we're so blessed to get to do cultural work in and around the good and environmental systems in this lovely place. we absolutely love showing people this city -- from cultural tours to the best nature spots to restaurants (even pokémon)! 

our wonderful brilliant border collie isaly will be your prime host -- she loves our guests and will happily throw you some tricks (her newest one is "step up and kisses") and some cuddles. we also have a lovely matching kitty named nella. 

we love meeting people from all around the world, and sharing our love for our little city and its wonderful culture. we can't wait to meet you!

name: Quaint 1920's Townhouse
summary: Comfortable living space in historic Merion Village, with 800 sqft it's the perfect get away for two.  Within walking distance to several bars and Schiller Park, and a quick drive to Downtown, Brewery District, Arena District and Short North. Located just around the corner from the bus stop.  There are two Kroger locations, one Giant Eagle, and a CVS are available for groceries.
space: This is an older home dating back to the 1920s.  Ceilings are tall, rooms are quaint, stairs are steep.  Please respect the dated property, and enjoy it's character.   There is no garbage disposal in the kitchen sink, please dispose of food in trash.   New HVAC has been installed, temperature should be acceptable as set.  There is a fan/heater in the upstairs landing for possible use while in the bedroom, as temperatures vary in the home.   Plumbing is fragile given the age of the home.  Please do not flush feminine products in the toilet.

host_about:
I'm hosting on Airbnb because I am only at my space for half the month usually, sharing time at my boyfriends house.  I enjoy all kinds of art, music, dance and food.  Wine, shoes, and dessert are my weaknesses.  I love traveling of all kinds, short road trips or long vacations.

name: 1BR 1-person Clintonville Apt, (5-day min rental)
summary: This is a pleasant 2-level apartment that is perfect for a single tenant. The minimum stay is 5 nights at $60/night.  Longer stays (28 days or more) are $38/night.  It's an ideal place to stay if you are traveling alone, and a great option if your planned visit to Columbus is a bit longer than the typical "vacation".
space: This is an attractive and comfortable apartment for a single person who is in Columbus for an extended but relatively short period of time, or is in the process of moving to Columbus and needs short-term housing while searching for a long-term rental.  There's no long-term lease to sign, no roommates, your own private bath, kitchen and laundry, and utilities are set up and included in the rental fee.   The apartment has a bedroom, bath, and a small closet on the entry level; and the living room, dining room, kitchen and laundry space are on the basement level.  It is attractively furnished, and includes linens, dishes, a TV, washer, dryer, and small appliances.   The bedroom and hall have hardwood floors, the kitchen and bath have tile floors, and the stairs and the living/dining room space have carpet. It has a beautiful kitchen, and there is a washer, a dryer, a small laundry sink and a large closet in the space adjacent to the kitchen. One off-street parking space is provided, and h

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is very solid.  It's quite popular with young professionals, families, and seniors.  It's mostly residential, but has a number of restaurants and shops within easy reach, and is conveniently located near freeway access points.  It's about 8 minutes drive southwest to OSU, 12 minutes drive south to downtown or the Convention Center, and 5 minutes drive south to the State Fairgrounds.
notes: The apartment is relatively quiet, but you may hear footsteps from above from time to time.  There is one adjacent short-term rental apartment above and behind this one.  You may also hear traffic noise from the bedroom.  Guests may visit you in the apartment during reasonable hours, but should leave by 11pm.  Guests are not permitted to stay overnight.
transit: There is a Columbus City bus route that runs in front of the house, and an OSU campus bus route that has a stop about 3 blocks south of the house.
access: This is a private apartment with a private direct entrance.  Parking is on a driveway space just north of the apartment's entry door.
interaction: I live next door and am usually able to answer questions or solve any issues within a short period of time.  I do however travel out of state for a week or less each month to spend time with grandchildren.
house_rules: There should not be any loud or boisterous behavior inside the apartment.  Guests are welcome to visit you within reasonable hours, but no overnight guests are permitted.  No exceptions.
host_about: I have lived in Columbus off and on since coming here to attend Ohio State University in the 60's.  I have a degree in Architecture from OSU, but my real interest has always been in renovations. I have a son who lives in San Francisco and I love to visit there several times a year.  My husband and I have 3 grandchildren - one in California and two in Michigan.  I recently retired from OSU after working there for 18 years.
