neighborhood_overview: There are SO many things to do in the neighborhood as well as downtown. Most of which are in walking distance.  To name a few: Schiller Park Jeni's Ice Creams Brown Bag Deli Autobahn Park & Obstacle course High Beck Bar Chipotle Club 185 (bar/restaurant) Lindey's (fine dining) Curio (cocktails) Harvest Pizzeria Skillet (a unique breakfast experience) Katzingers Deli The Kitchen Alchemy (healthy eats) 16 Bit Bar (arcade/bar) Dirty Franks Hot Dogs/Bar (next to 16 Bit Bar) El Camino (mexican food/bar) Mikeys Late Night Slice (pizza/bar) North Market (a must do (food & such)) Seventh Son Brewery Hoof Hearted Brewery Northstar Cafe Third & Hollywood The list goes on....
notes: WEDDING PARTIES: our locations is right behind High Line Car House so we get a lot of wedding party reservations. Our place is pretty small and we usually try to discourage groups larger than 4 from staying with our $65/night charge for extra guests. We have hosted a lot of wedding parties in the past and it usually ends with us cleaning up a lot of makeup, nail polish, hair spray, party supplies, ect. There is only one small bathroom which might be stressful for wedding parties. It will definitely be cozy. It pains us to be so discouraging to our guests but at the same time we want you to enjoy your wedding day and offer a convenient location. Please let us know if you will be booking for a wedding.  Fruit, coffee, tea, oatmeal, cereal, granola bars, and other snack/breakfast items may be stocked in the kitchen. In this modern age, so many people have dietary restrictions. For this reason, we can only stock the kitchen with a variety options for you to choose from. But, with so many g
transit: There is a great "Cbus Free-bus" service that travels up and down high street allowing people to get places without driving/parking downtown. There is a stop 1 block away. There are bike rental stations all over the city if you are so inclined. There is a station at Schiller park in German Village as well. Car-to-Go is everywhere in Columbus as well. We have never used it but it seems to be pretty popular.
access: There is keyless entry to the house. A lockbox with keys is also available for other circumstances. Enjoy the entire space including the backyard. There will be a pass for parking on the kitchen island when you arrive. PLEASE remember to return them as we only get a couple per year. ** $200 fee per misplaced visitor passes**
interaction: Please do not hesitate to contact us via Airbnb message if there are any needs or questions that you may have throught your stay. We are just next door if you'd like to stop and say "hi" =)
house_rules: - Check-in is after 3pm - For best results, please use AirBnb's message feature to communicate. - We want you to enjoy yourself in our home but we ask that you keep the noise to a minimum. ABSOLUTELY NO PARTIES. Any noise complaints will result in a minim
host_about:
We are a couple living in the historic German Village of Columbus, Ohio. A few things we love: art, design, architecture, photography, real estate, playing host,  laughing, local food & drink, the great outdoors, camping, exploring new places, meeting new people, Game of Thrones, and some good R&R with friends and family. Chelsey is a copywriter and Sonny is a graphic designer/developer.

We love our gem of a city. The Columbus scene offers more than you might expect, with awesome people, local food, unique craft breweries and funky small businesses around every corner. We are always excited to share the all that Columbus has to offer with others. 

Our perfect date night (recommended):
1. Stop by Curio for some seriously unique and delicious cocktails.
2. Visit Third & Hollywood in Grandview for amazing seasonal cuisine. 
3. walk to Jeni's Ice Creams for dessert
4. Hop over to Seventh Son Brewing for some of our favorite adult beverages.
5. Uber down to 16 Bit Bar (BARxARCADE) and meet friends for games.
6. Jump next door to Dirty Franks for some late night snacks.
7. Walk home 
8. Sleep =)

summary: Welcome to our Buckeye Retreat! A beautiful, well kept, newly remodeled and decorated split level home.  Enjoy total privacy, no shared spaces, in a great location, in a safe residential neighborhood.  Off HWY 315, adjacent to Upper Arlington, Clintonville & OSU. A few miles to Short North, Arena District, Easton & Brewery District.  About 11 miles from the Columbus Zoo & Water Park. Walk to Riverside Hospital & OSU golf course.
space: Tired of cramped hotel rooms?  Tired of sharing space & closets?  Looking for a comfortable, private, roomy place to stay?  Our spacious split-level home is ideal for Columbus visitors, Convention Center activities, sports fans, business travelers and families.  Our home is dedicated 100% to you. No shared spaces. We offer hotel quality space and furnishings at a reasonable price.  We have 4 bedrooms with 2 king size beds, 1 queen size bed, 2 twin beds, 1 crib,  plus a queen size air mattress.  We have a crib and baby supplies available upon request.  Free WIFI Cable TV with ESPN Several  distinct areas for guests to relax:  MAIN LEVEL *Eat in fully equipped kitchen; with pots, pans, baking pans, toaster, utensils, microwave & Keurig coffee maker. Tableware: dishes, silverware, glasses, stemware. *Refreshment center (mini bar) with fridge & stemware *Large living room with sofa and chairs. We have a Queen size air mattress for the Living Room for 2 guests.  *4 season sun-room *Outdoor

neighborhood_overview: Our quiet residential neighborhood is in a highly desirable area, with a spacious yard and off street parking.  You are staying in a safe neighborhood ... just a few minutes from downtown.  We are 2 miles or less from the OSU Stadiums and Arenas.  We are conveniently nestled between Upper Arlington, Clintonville, the Short North, Ohio State University and Downtown Columbus. We have numerous shops & restaurants just around the corner on Olentangy River Rd. Uber, Lyft, UberEATS, Amazon Prime Now, Kroger Click list, Panera Delivery, Grubhub and BiteSquad service this area
notes: We provide everything you need to enjoy your stay in our home and in our beautiful city.  Basic necessities: Towels, bedding, pillows, toiletries, dish soap, garbage bags, cleaning supplies, hair dryer, iron & ironing board.  Basic kitchen supplies: tableware, stemware & utensils. Pots, pans, baking sheets etc. Toaster, Keurig Coffee maker, coffee, tea, snacks and bottled water. Desk/work station with office supplies and USB charging station Uber and Lyft are both available, for those times you prefer not to drive.  UberEATS, Amazon Prime Now, Panera Delivery, Kroger Clicklist and Bite Squared service this area.
transit: Walk to OSU Golf Club or Riverside Hospital For those that enjoy walking we are 2 miles or less to  the OSU sports stadiums and arenas. A short walk to the COTA bus stop to catch a ride to OSU or Downtown Columbus. (bus route schedule in house manual) Give Über or Lyft a call for a quick inexpensive ride  to most of Columbus Ride your bike or jog to the Olentangy hiking/biking trails
access: Guests have a key and the entire home to themselves ... outdoor deck, fenced yard & private driveway.  Ample closet, cabinet & storage space.  Off street parking Free WIFI
interaction: We will meet with you upon check in and check out.  You have complete privacy and use of the entire home.
house_rules: Welcome to Buckeye Retreat, please see the House Manual on the family room desk for additional information & house rules.  In consideration of those with allergies and asthma, we use unscented laundry detergents ... NO PETS & NO SMOKING. thank you for your consideration in these matters.  * Our home is in a quiet residential neighborhood, and we love our neighbors so ... We do not rent to college students or sports teams, please do not hold events in our home, no showers, parties or bachelor/bachelorette type groups.  No smoking, drugs or underage drinking We allow a maximum of 10 people on the premises at all times.  Please see the house manual on the desk for check out procedures.  Please do not order pay per view Check-in: 3:00 pm      Check-out: 11:00 am If our check-in & out times do not work for you ... We will try to accommodate your needs for different check-in & check-out times. Please follow the rules for checkout found in the house manual and return the key to the lockbox be
host_about:
Welcome to my Buckeye Retreat. As a frequent traveler I understand the complexities of traveling both for work and pleasure. 

Traveling with children and staying in a hotel was always complicated and staying in hotels for work can become monotonous. 

So .... I decided to start an airbnb to make traveling easier and more comfortable for others. 

I am proud to be able to provide safe, clean and reasonably priced lodging for people visiting my beautiful city. 

I hope you enjoy my house and Columbus as much as I do.

Franklin park and Conservatory ( a must see) is just 3 blocks away.
notes: New to Airbnb? No reviews in the Airbnb System? Please do the following before you submit a reservation request. I have gathered theses suggestions from other successful AirBnB host. 1. Use your real name and include your correct information in your Airbnb profile. Also, fully verify your personal information through the Airbnb verification process. (email address, social site information, twit, Lnkdin, phone number, etc.). I read every profile in detail so don't skip anything. This is how you build trust with potential hosts. 2. Provide a current and accurate picture as your Airbnb profile picture. This way, hosts can verify your identity when you check in. Most will ask to see ID as well) 3. Complete the "Describe Yourself" section in your Airbnb profile. This helps to build trust with potential hosts by letting them learn a little about you as a person; your interests, likes and dislikes, travel preferences, your family, etc. 4. Be thorough and completely honest in the actual reserv

access: You will have access to the kitchen, dining room, living room, bath and front room.
interaction: I work from home so I am usually available.  If I can help with directions or suggestions just ask.

Also provide the names of any other guest traveling with you and be ready to present your ID(s) for verification upon check in.  If you need to check-in outside of this window please arrange for this prior to your arrival.  I can usually be flexible. Be Respectful. Treat this home as you would your own. As this is a shared space, be courteous to other house guest and Host. Many guest will be sleep after 11 pm please keep this in mind. No Shoes beyond the Entry Room.  You may use socks or slippers if you have them but no outdoor shoes.  I suggest non-skid socks. No Outside Bedding - Why?- It creates a health risk. - I have clean bed linens, blankets and pillows for your use. host_about: I'm a down to earth, kindhearted person that is intrigued by unique ideas, people, places etc.  Respectable, responsible and reasonable.  I enjoy conversing about science especially "Space time".  I spend much of my free time learning or reading about new technology or improving my current skills. I enjoy the outdoors when possible, travel and portrait photography.  Check out my web comic th (Website hidden by Airbnb) or my Instagram #thefotographiclife. name: Clintonville Home
summary: Two bedroom house near OSU campus - situated between two parks - along the river and biking trail that runs north and south through Columbus.  Next door park has a playground, tennis and basketball courts, sledding hill and shelter house.  5 minute walk to bus route. 5 minute drive to OSU and 15 minute bike ride to OSU.  Perfect location for downtown or campus commute.  Fenced in yard.  Pets are negotiable. If you plan to stay with a pet. please send an inquiry first so we can discuss specifics.
space: This is a cozy house, which has been described as a cottage or cabin in the city woods.  Because I am a biology professor, the house is sprinkled with biology and other science-themed artwork.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is quiet and safe.  Because the house splits two parks, there is a lot of walking traffic on the street with people exercising or walking their dogs.  It is a dead end street that ends at the Olentangy River (100 yards from the house).
notes: Parking is plentiful in front or behind the house.
transit: The "#2" COTA bus is $2.00 each way and runs north and south on High St to campus and downtown (south) and Worthington (north).  There is a bike trail that runs north and south to the same locations along the river.  Many restaurant and grocery options are nearby.
access: The house is a single level with two bedrooms and a kitchen. The basement has full laundry (washer and dryer).
interaction: We are available to answer questions, but are not invasive hosts.  Although I don t live in the neighborhood, I used to live there and know all of the neighbors pretty well.
house_rules: Pets must be house-trained and owners must agree to a 10$ per pet per night cleaning fee. Smoking is allowed outside the home as long as trash is properly disposed
host_about: I am a biology/chemistry professor at The Ohio State University.  I love nature and travel.  I am hosting with my daughter, Shannon, a student at OSU.  We appreciate affordable, no frills, but clean, comfortable and safe travel for our guests.

There is something for everyone: great restaurants, bars, boutique shops, art galleries, festivals, and theater-  all within blocks of the home.  Also close to Ohio State University,  Convention Center, Downtown, and other great neighborhoods including Grandview and German Village.

Car2go is available and there are usually available cars within several blocks. CoGo bike sharing is available with the nearest pick up location 2 blocks away.

neighborhood_overview: We're about a 15 minute drive to downtown, an $18 uber ride to downtown. I'm about a mile from 2 major highways, restaurants and shopping. Everything you need is super close! Fairly quiet neighborhood.
notes: There is an Australian Shepherd that lives here (Gigi). She's 9, completely house broken, can be leery of strangers, but LOVES having our airbnb guests! She barks when people enter but is very sweet once she's established you aren't a threat :) Fair warning: If you like to leave your door open when you're home, she WILL walk right in to visit and might even jump on the bed; she'll immediately get down if told. Dog lovers preferable, for the above mentioned reasons. :) Additionally, I do work full-time. I keep my place neat & clean, but we ARE actively living here.  The airbnb experience here is that of a third roommate and we clean up after ourselves. I prefer my guests, as well as myself, to be able to come home, relax and unwind after a long day.
transit: There is a parking spot available directly in front of the front door OR to the left side in front of the 2 car garage.  I'm unsure how close the nearest bus stop is? There is always Uber though :) An Uber ride downtown is typically around $18-$20.

There are a few bars, a convenience store, Subway, a coffee shop and a brunch place on 3rd avenue within a few blocks. It's a half mile walk to High St and about a mile to the convention center and Nationwide Arena. It's also a mile south of The Ohio State University.
notes: I've mostly moved out. There are some book shelves with books, some miscellaneous things in the back of the closet and maybe some tools in the basement to move still. There are a lot of major routes that run on High St. You can usually find a taxi to hail on Neil Avenue within a few minutes. I can't wait to meet you!

neighborhood_overview: You will be located in the heart of the Downtown Columbus in Victorian Village. This neighborhood is part of the Short North Arts District which hosts Gallery Hop the first Saturday of every month and includes some of the best restaurants and nightlife in the city, all within a couple blocks. Goodale Park is a half a block away and includes a fountain park and 33 acres of beautiful tree-lined walkways. It was donated to the city in 1851 and is bordered by historic Victorian mansions on original brick streets. Within eyesight of the front stoop, you're close to a CVS, ATM, deli, and coffee shop on Neil Ave. You can also catch the best concerts at EXPRESS LIVE!, Columbus Clippers minor league baseball at Huntington Field, and Columbus Blue Jackets hockey in the Arena District at Nationwide Arena.
notes: There is some minor renovation currently; the front door is being replaced soon so a couple walls are getting prepped for that and in the bedroom, the original windows are being replaced but storm windows are in place and sealed.
transit: Most things are an easy walk! An Uber or Lyft is never more than 5 min away. The COTA Circulator bus (CBUS) is free and runs up and down High St making a loop from the Short North, Downtown, German Village and back. COTA AirConnect also runs a $2.75/trip airport shuttle bus with stops next to the convention center, right across the the park from my place. Walk Score gives my place a rating of 83 out of 100. This location is very walkable so most errands and activities can be accomplished on foot. CoGo Bike Share operates a station right across Neil Ave., just around the block. You will have one dedicated off-street parking spot next to my place. Please take note of where your spot is in your reservation details, all other off-street spots are for neighbors and my street is permit-only parking. Neil Ave. is non-permit and free to park if you need extra parking.
access: Listing includes guestroom, private bathroom, and one reserved off-street parking spot. Second floor hallway bathroom is reserved for the resident & other guest room. First floor (living room, kitchen & laundry room) and third floor are for resident use.
interaction: I try to greet each guest in person; if I am not able to, please let me know if you have any questions or issues when checking in! I generally give guests their space during their stay but am available if anything is needed.
house_rules: - Quiet hours between midnight & 7:00am are appreciated - Kitchen, laundry room, and living room are generally for resident use only - Please let me know your approximate arrival time and if you'll need parking
host_about: I grew up in southwest Ohio and moved to Columbus in 2009 after finishing Army officer candidate school. I often tell folks that if it wasn't for Columbus I wouldn't have stayed in Ohio. Columbus is truly a great city, 15th in the nation in population and a little big city that exudes charm and a vibrant, progressive culture that I'm grateful to live in. I work for a great company that I'm able to have a walking commute through historic Victorian Village and am always looking for opportunities to find undiscovered gems around town and around central Ohio. I love spending time with my chosen family of friends whether it be traveling on vacation, wine nights, movies, or happy hours. Between work and being a puppy parent to my chocolate Lab, Jonas, I'm working on finishing my degree in Public Administration with a follow-on masters degree. It's been exciting and rewarding meeting people from all over the country and beyond that I've been fortunate to host. I look forward to welcoming you for your stay in my home and in the heart of a great city like Columbus. https://www.airbnb.com/users/26073351/listings?user_id=26073351&s=50

However, please do not dispose of food in the garbage in the bedroom, the bathroom, or in the laundry basket. Use the kitchen garbage can to dispose of food. There will be NO SMOKING at all in the room. There is a very comfortable porch on the back of the house, with a butt pot; you are more than welcome to smoke there. My co-host and I would love to make your stay as comfortable as possible. We are always open to suggestions.  Thanks for coming!
transit: The house sits in the middle of everything. The bus stop is a five minute walk down the street. Plenty of restaurants within 5-10 minutes from the house. The airport is 10 minutes away. There are two malls close by. The home is two minutes from highway 70, and 10-15 minutes from downtown.
access: Guest are welcome to use the kitchen,  living room and the back patio.
interaction: Most of the time my co-host will be available if anything is needed. However, if someone would like to contact me, texting or calling is fine.

host_about: I am a very busy and outgoing person. I am a Military Veteran; I work for the Department of Homeland Security, and a full-time student. I have been in the Ohio area for five years now, by way of Illinois. I enjoy meeting new people. Because of my travels with the military and DHS, I have met people from all across the county, and other countries as well. Airbnb allows me to meet even more. Therefore, I am so looking forward to meeting you! ;-)

Short drive or bike ride to Hoover Reservoir to enjoy nature. Plenty of restaurants, bars, and small wine shops to chose from within the surrounding areas. Starbucks less than 5 minutes away!
notes: Close to CMH, Easton, Polaris, and Otterbein University. 20 minute drive to Downtown. interaction: Available any time by phone or text!
house_rules: NO smoking. We would prefer non smokers, but if you must, please smoke outside and be sure there is no odor on your clothing when using our furniture. Thank you.  We ask that you be respectful of our home by taking your shoes off when walking on the carpet and leaving our home as you found it. Additional guests (outside of guests staying here) are not permitted to visit or be at the pool and these rules are strictly enforced. No glass allowed at the pool. No parties or get togethers. Our neighbors live in very close proximity and we share a fence so noise must be kept to a minimum on the patio.

neighborhood_overview: At the beginning of this century, people chose to live in Olde Towne East for social status. Today, the residents choose to live here for the unique styling of the houses and their appreciation of the diverse community. The varied cultural and racial backgrounds and economic levels that are present create a unique environment not found in any other Columbus neighborhood. Olde Towne East is a pedestrian-friendly neighborhood in a grid layout. The Columbus Metropolitan Library, The Columbus Museum of Art, Franklin University, Capitol University Law School, and Columbus College of Art and Design are all within a 15 minute walk. The entire downtown of Columbus is easily accessible by bicycle or public transportation. City, county, state and federal government agencies (including the Capitol Building of the State of Ohio), several regional and national banks, insurance companies, and major corporate headquarters are all accessible without need for an automobile. neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is one of the Midwest’s best kept secrets. There is a huge variety of unique shops, bars and restaurants, and art galleries along High Street and a number of annual events that take place year-round. We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Dennison Place on Dennison Ave., between King Ave and 5th Ave. (only 1 block away from High Street).  It’s a quiet street tucked in from High Street and home to an eclectic mix of young professionals, artists, foodies, musicians, families. There are beautiful, Victorian and Italianate historic homes along Smith Place, Dennison, and Hunter, take a walk if you can- it's a great area! Near the following: • Restaurants- The Table, Basil, Condados, Mikey's Late Night Slice • Bars & breweries- North High Brewing, Brother Drakes, Seventh Son Brewing Co. • Grocery stores- Kroger & Gian
notes: • Housekeeping service is per stay, not per night. Additional cleaning visits can be arranged for longer stays if needed.  Visits must be paid in advance and are non-refundable if visits are cancelled. Please inquire when booking. • Pack n Play, high chair, and/or Queen air bed available upon request- please let us know your needs prior so we can prepare all the necessary items. • Noise must be keep to a minimum, this is one of two units.   • There is no handicap access. There are two steps to enter the front of the house.  • Guests with allergies and related medical issues and/or sensitivities- cleanliness is one of our top priorities, however we cannot 100% guarantee that the apartment is free of pet dander, cigarette smoke, air fresheners/cleaning product scents, or any other elements that may trigger a medical problem or sensitivity. neighborhood_overview: At the beginning of this century, people chose to live in Olde Towne East for social status. Today, the residents choose to live here for the unique styling of the houses and their appreciation of the diverse community. The varied cultural and racial backgrounds and economic levels that are present create a unique environment not found in any other Columbus neighborhood. Olde Towne East is a pedestrian-friendly neighborhood in a grid layout. The Columbus Metropolitan Library, The Columbus Museum of Art, Franklin University, Capitol University Law School, and Columbus College of Art and Design are all within a 15 minute walk. The entire downtown of Columbus is easily accessible by bicycle or public transportation. City, county, state and federal government agencies (including the Capitol Building of the State of Ohio), several regional and national banks, insurance companies, and major corporate headquarters are all accessible without need for an automobile. neighborhood_overview: Franklinton was the first settlement in central Ohio, settled at the confluence of two rivers, which means great farm land. Columbus was developed later, across the river. Over the centuries, Franklinton flooded twice and so the neighborhood went into decline, along with other inner city neighborhoods nation wide.  Now protected by a flood wall and enjoying the renaissance of many inner city neighborhoods, it is on its way back. Very close to down town and freeway access to everywhere,  Franklinton boasts a vibrant new arts district and cute bars and breweries. It is a  mixed neighborhood in every respect. We do still have some boarded up houses next to very nice places selling for $210,000.  I have lived in this neighborhood for 10 years and love it here.
notes: Minimum stay is 4 days but if there are intervals, not booked, of less than 4 days, message me and I can approve a shorter stay.
transit: We are surrounded by freeways so automobile travel is easy and the drive to the airport is freeway all the way. Buses crisscross the neighborhood and bicycle travel is fairly easy. A bike path runs along the north edge of Franklinton and goes for many, many miles in many directions. Down town is 1 1/2 miles east so that is even walkable or take the bus. A bus to OSU takes less than 15 minutes, drive time is 8 minutes and parking may take up longer than riding the bus! These times do get longer in peak times.
access: Guests have use of the whole building, The entrance is from the alley, with parking at the door, or you can come in from the front of the house and walk through the garden. Check in time can be very flexible depending only on the time needed for cleaning between guests. We are convenient to museums, libraries, art galleries, COSI and much more. The location is fabulous and Uber is wonderful to get you anywhere.
interaction: I live in the house on the same lot and work from home so I am available. Plus, I am a good cook and can help out occasionally with home cooked meals. This might be especially nice for business travelers tired of eating out. There is a coffee pot, kettle and tea pot plus tea and coffee. Sugar, creamer and salt and pepper are also provided.
house_rules: - "events or parties" require advanced approval.
host_about:
Bruce and I recently married after some time as a widow/widower, in our 70's and enjoying time together and with family.  I like gardening and cooking and having friends over. We are very active in the community and  own and manage a number of rentals. 

Airbnb is now familiar and it's all good after our first year - we hope to expand to more units.  We can be about as involved as hosts as guests would like - from "here you are, have a nice stay" - to cooking dinner. We live on the other side of the patio which you are free to use. 

We really try to host folk who need longer stays - weeks to months, hence the 4 day minimum,  but that sometimes leaves a few days between bookings - often  on weekends. So feel free to inquire about shorter stays at short notice. 
 
We travel quite a lot and usually stay at Airbnb sites - so much nicer than fancy hotels. 

This asks for languages I speak but does not allow me to claim American and English/Australian as different.

summary: beautifully secluded private room with in-suite private bath. cleanly styled two person room includes spacious walk-in closet, refrigerator freezer, desk workspace, AC/heater, and privacy lock. full size mattress made with premium memory foam. press a button on the smart tv remote for plenty of free entertainment options. we recommend "what the health" and "13th" on netflix.
space: we design co-living spaces for young adults interested in developing positive connections with other humans. our spaces are always clean and offer plenty of free street parking. this quiet yet vibrant spacious home is a few blocks walk from children's hospital, and a 5-10 minute uber to downtown or short north. meet columbus locals and easily explore art, food, and nightlife in one the great midwest cities.
description: beautifully secluded private room with in-suite private bath. cleanly styled two person room includes spacious walk-in closet, refrigerator freezer, desk workspace, AC/heater, and privacy lock. full size mattress made with premium memory foam. press a button on the smart tv remote for plenty of free entertainment options. we recommend "what the health" and "13th" on netflix. we design co-living spaces for young adults interested in developing positive connections with other humans. our spaces are always clean and offer plenty of free street parking. this quiet yet vibrant spacious home is a few blocks walk from children's hospital, and a 5-10 minute uber to downtown or short north. meet columbus locals and easily explore art, food, and nightlife in one the great midwest cities. fully stocked bathroom, grassy fenced yard with gardens, free on-site laundry, community iron and steam cleaner, minimalist kitchen, community table for workspace and gathering, book library, front porch with se
neighborhood_overview: the neighborhood has been recently renovated to support the expansion of nationwide children's hospital. we don't recommend leaving valuables in your car in any neighborhood, but we keep video surveillance around the property. the street is generally quiet and our neighbors are all friendly. the most impressive green spaces nearby are the franklin park conservatory and schiller park in german village. you can get free entry to columbus museum of modern art every sunday.
notes: we are a minimalist home. our kitchen has moderate storage, with 24 hour refrigerated storage. instead of a full range stove, our cook station boasts a premium induction stovetop with an air fryer toaster oven. there is also a refrigerator freezer unit in each private room. we do our best to live small, buy small, and share with others.
transit: uber is the easiest option if you don’t want to drive. the city has a bus stop a block from our house. the experience columbus website is a great resource for city information. if you’re a hungry vegan, don’t leave without visiting dirty franks hot dogs or one of the angry baker locations nearby. downtown, pins mechanical has mini duckpin bowling and great cocktails, or you can test your skills at the 16-bit arcade bar. the short north is a popular neighborhood for walking around with restaurant bars, art galleries, and the beautiful goodale park.
access: fully stocked bathroom, grassy fenced yard with gardens, free on-site laundry, community iron and steam cleaner, minimalist kitchen, community table for workspace and gathering, book library, front porch with seating, excellent fast premium wifi.
interaction: we’ve designed our airbnb to be socially flexible. you'll have the opportunity to meet a diverse group of roommates and friends that mostly hang out in their own rooms. common areas can be used by all to socialize in any way that doesn't conflict with the needs of other guests. sleep is important for all our guests. bed time sound levels go into effect at 10pm each evening. feel free to relax with a glass of wine, but we appreciate a liquor-free experience.

host_about: I love Paris, books, movies, shows, music, and sustainable food.

summary: Private apt! OSU friendly! Private parking and entrance, 2 bedrooms w/sitting areas, shower and kitchen. Close to restaurants/activities in Clintonville/Worthington.  Close to OSU (8 mi)/Short North/Downtown Columbus (9 mi) - MAPFRE Stadium (5 mi), Nationwide Arena (9 mi), Schott Center (6 mi), Ohio Expo Center (6 mi). space: My space is a beautifully renovated downstairs basement apartment adjoining my home with your own driveway and private, remote keyless entry.  Check in is 4:00 PM EST unless otherwise requested at time of booking.  Check out is 11:00 AM unless otherwise requested by 10:30 AM.  No exceptions please. I do all the cleaning and am not a hotel that can accommodate surprise arrivals or hung-over departures. It has 2 bedrooms each with a sitting option, a full bathroom and a full kitchen and eating space with a table that has leaves for business working.  Laundry facilities are available for your use as well. Breakfast and snack foods are stocked for a Continental breakfast for you to prepare when you are hungry.

Check in is 4:00 PM EST unless otherwise requested at time of booking.  Check out is 11:00 AM unless otherwise requested by 10:30 AM.  No exceptions please. I do all the cleaning and am not a hotel that can accommodate surprise arrivals or hung-over departures. It has 2 bedrooms each with a sitting option, a full bathroom and a full kitchen and eating space
neighborhood_overview: My neighborhood is literally one block from the beginning of Clintonville and only 3 blocks from the beginning of Worthington.  Both are wonderful communities specializing in arts, retail shops and noteworthy restaurants. We have several churches, 2 pizza shops, 2 neighborhood taverns, and 3 small convenient stores, one in a gas station, all within walking distance.  You will not have to drive far for anything you need. I am close to several small Worthington parks and only a few minutes from Sharon Woods Metro Park where there are hiking and biking trails, shelter houses and a fishing pond.
notes: Extra guests - $15 each per night. When you book please indicate the true number of people for your stay. The price is for 2 people only - if more than 2 show up I shall ask for additional charges through Airbnb. I have 2 cats in the main house only but have installed register filters to keep allergens to a minimum.  I also have a  Cocker Spaniel and she is friendly and absolutely loves people so if you wish to meet her just let me know.
transit: The COTA bus services my street  and we also have a Park and Ride about a mile away that will go downtown.  We are only 1 mile from the main High Street bus and there is also a Park and Ride by Morse Road and High Street. Columbus uses a lot of Uber and Lyft rides as well as taxicabs.
access: There are no shared spaces when you book.  You should be sent a remote lock access code when you booked from Lockstate via email.  Please contact me through the contact for the host if this did not happen or if access does not work and I will respond as quickly as possible.
interaction: I am usually in close proximity either at home or close by and reachable at all times if you have any questions or concerns or if you need a commodity (within reason) that I have not provided. If I can help in any way by providing extra information about where you want or need to go please do not hesitate to contact me.  I have a door between the apartment and the main house with a doorbell if you need me or you can email me through Airbnb or text or call me directly.
house_rules: - Check out time is 11 AM EST. If you are from another time zone, please adjust your check out time to EST only. - Smoking allowed on outside patio station.  All butts to be contained in provided receptacle. - Only 2 guests per booking - extra guests $15/
host_about:
I am a retired lady enjoying pursuing my own interests now - and running an Airbnb space is one I've really been looking forward to doing.  I used to house hearing impaired students from all over Ohio in years past and have had several friends renting this space and they all loved it!  Now that my daughter and her husband have moved out it is time to share once again.

I have 3 wonderful little animals in the main house - 2 cats and 1 dog.

The cats are never in the basement area of the rooms I am offering up for use, but Janey occasionally goes down with me to do the laundry and clean, but she is never allowed when I have guests.

My home and life is non-judgmental and open to all races, religions and genders.  

I hope you will enjoy your visit should you choose to do so!  Have a wonderful day!

name: Classic & Convenient in German Village
summary: Classic & Convenient - 884 Macon is a charming single family home located in the heart of German Village!! Minutes to the Convention Center and home of the Buckeyes-The Horseshoe & the Schottenstien Center, a stone's throw from Schiller Park. The house is ready for any of your plans: Dishes & cookware for a family meal? Check.  Speakers throughout to enjoy & relax? Check.  Strong WiFi & desk to crank some work out? Check.  Ultra comfy beds for ZZZs? Check Whatever you need - we're on it!
space: 884 Macon, known to us as "The Treehouse", is a piece of continuing history for German Village and our family. The house was built in the 1860's and the layout has remained true sans a sunroom added in the 80's. Thomases have lived here since the 60's and each of us has several stories that are close to the heart; from a first listen of a Simon & Garfunkel album to annual Christmas parties packed to the gills to an indelible late night conversation. It's German Village, Thomas style. The house stands as a representation of both. Art from well known locals like my great Uncle Hank Russell, and his contemporaries Hans Reitenbach and Ralph Williams. Pieces from two generations of world travel. An entire barnwood wall from a structure we reclaimed in Southern OH. Original hardwood floors and windows.  Come join the story.

neighborhood_overview: There's an energy and excitement in Columbus that's going to hit you as soon as you arrive. Big things are happening here, and you're invited to join in. The city is booming, and not just in population. The Columbus Museum of Art added a spectacular new wing, and the Scioto Mile puts 33 acres of new riverfront parkland in the heart of downtown. The innovative food scene melds artisan food producers with imaginative chefs to create meals that are far greater than the sum of their parts. Nationally acclaimed distilleries work together with brewers, coffee roasters and high-end cocktail bars, black box stages, music halls and dive bars to deliver unforgettable nightlife. Neighborhoods on all sides of downtown are bursting with new places to eat and shop, and artists are shaping new areas of the city into dynamic spaces to explore. It's time to get to know the Columbus that grew up when you weren't looking. -Walkable  -Entertainment  -Short North Art & Dining  -Columbus Clippers (Baseball)
notes: I work from home as a full time Realtor so often times I'm in and out throughout the day however you can always reach me via text or call if needed. host_about:
Greetings! 

Thanks for taking a moment to learn a little bit more about me. I'm a young professional who works in the Real Estate business - often times it consumes my days and nights; weekends too! However, I wouldn't have it any other way and I'm very passionate about what it do. 

Five things that I can't live without: 

1. My iphone! It's on your top 5 too! ;) 
2. My dog Tyson (Sheltie) - 5 years old & 18lbs 
3. Coffee - it's the first thing I do in the morning! 
4. Laptop - Personally/Professionally 
5. Toothbrush/Toothpaste - clean and nice teeth are a priority to me. 

I enjoy having Air BnB guest because Columbus is my roots and I get to share that with someone visiting. However, it does not stop there; it's a two-way street I get to meet people from all over the world, with stories, culture, viewpoints that I have never been exposed to in my lifetime. It's fun! I like to entertain! Of course, the few extra bucks is nice too. 

I'm Not Your Average Joe!  Look forward to meeting you in person. 

Be well & talk soon, 

Joseph

There are bus stops nearby and a nice park, the ravine, down the hill (about a one minute walking distance) from the house. summary: Based in the heart of the historic and vibrant Short North Arts District, this urban loft allows you to experience all Columbus has to offer with ease.  Grab brunch at Fox in the Snow Cafe, explore the North Market and its merchants, and polish it off with a fine dinner at The Rossi.  If nightlife is your jam, check out Standard Hall for a beer or tasty cocktail.  Otherwise, grab a scoop of some of the best ice cream you’ll ever have at the famous Jeni’s Splendid Ice Creams on High St.
space: This spot is located minutes from the Convention Center, Nationwide Arena and numerous diverse restaurants, making everything readily accessible for you and/or your group.  The loft comfortably sleeps four, comes with a full kitchen to make cooking a breeze, and has a washer and dryer if you need to do a quick load of laundry.  Getting around is made super easy by Uber or walking (if it’s nice out!), but if you prefer to drive yourself parking is included at the unit.

host_about:
Hello! My name is Brandon and I am a young professional living in Columbus, Ohio. I'm an Ohio native, born and raised in Northwest Ohio. I graduated undergrad from THE Ohio State University, moved to Chicago where I lived and worked for a few years, and have now happily settled back down in Columbus. I work for L Brands, the parent company of Victoria's Secret and Bath & Body Works, one of the many retail companies headquartered here in Columbus. I am currently pursuing my Masters of Business Administration at Purdue University via a hybrid on-campus/online program. 
I enjoy traveling whenever and wherever I can, though I definitely prefer someplace warmer when given the option :) Though I love traveling, I am a Columbus fanboy at heart and am always happy to talk about all of the great things to experience here. I'm a very easy going guy, so feel free to ask me any questions that may be on your mind! Happy traveling!

summary: Renovated 2,000 sq ft, 4 bed, 2.5 bath home with hints of its pre-1890s history. Prime area of Italian Village in the Short North. If you want the luxury of a home within walking distance to restaurants and beautiful Goodale Park-- this is the place for you! Distance to: Columbus Convention Center- 0.6 mi OSU Stadium- 1.8 mi Downtown- all areas of interest are within 2.2 mi radius Ohio Expo Center/ Fairgrounds/Maphre Crew Stadium- 2.2 mi Schottenstein Center- 3.2 mi Easton Mall- 10 mi
space: This home was re-designed for entertaining. The first floor includes includes the kitchen/dining/living room in one connected space- perfect for dinner parties, bridal showers, and gatherings. Please inquire directly if you would like to host a special event; an additional fee applies starting at $100 and will vary depending on the event. All special event details must be approved prior to stay. The first floor has an eat-in kitchen with heated floors, granite countertops, and stainless-steel appliances. Kitchen has all things needed to cook a decent meal (pots, pans, plates, etc.) and has some basic cooking staples (ketchup, oil and vinegar, salt and pepper, sugar, coffee, tea, etc.)  The adjoining dining table can seat 8 guests in addition to the seating for 4 people at the kitchen island. neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is one of the Midwest’s best kept secrets. There is a huge variety of unique shops, bars and restaurants, and art galleries along High Street and a number of annual events that take place year-round. We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Italian Village on Summit St., between First Ave and Warren St. Just two blocks away from High Street! Near the following: • Restaurants- Union Café, The Eagle, Hubbard Grille, PhilCo, etc.  • Bars & breweries- The Pint House, Union Café, Bernards, etc. • Banks- Huntington & Chase • Grocery stores- Kroger & Giant Eagle Market Fresh (Third Ave, Grandview) • Downtown- all areas of interest are within 2.2 mile radius!
notes: • Housekeeping service is per stay, not per night. Additional cleaning visits can be arranged for longer stays if needed.  Visits must be paid in advance and are non-refundable if visits are cancelled. Please inquire when booking. • Pack n Play, high chair, and/or Queen air bed available upon request- please let us know your needs prior so we can prepare all the necessary items. • Please be courteous to neighbors- Noise must be keep to a minimum after 10 p.m. • There is no handicap access. There are two steps to enter the front of the house.  • Guests with allergies and related medical issues and/or sensitivities- cleanliness is one of our top priorities, however we cannot 100% guarantee that the apartment is free of pet dander, cigarette smoke, air fresheners/cleaning product scents, or any other elements that may trigger a medical problem or sensitivity. Please note we cannot issue refunds due to the reasons above.
transit: We are right in the middle of High Street and the up-and-coming N. 4th Street. You can easily walk to dozens of restaurants and shopping. All other locations can be easily reached a number of ways: Taxis --- Uber -- COTA (Central Ohio Transit Authority) bus --- CoGo (Rental Bikes) --- Car 2 Go (Car Rentals) --- CBUS circulator About the CBUS circulator- It's FREE transportation from the Short North through downtown, all the way to German Village. Bus stops are at many points along High Street. PARKING We are in the heart of the city so sometimes parking requires a little planning. We can assist if you have any issues. Street parking is available permit-free right in front of the house on both sides of Summit Street and N. 4th Street. All other neighborhood streets are by permit only however. Local Tip: Columbus meter maids love to give tickets- read the parking street signs in the downtown area! OFF STREET PARKING- There is a 11 x 29ft concrete pad available that can fit 1 large vehicl
access: You will have access to the entire home, private backyard, and parking pad in front of the garage. Garage is not included. Hours of Access: Check-in is 3 p.m.  Checkout is 11 a.m.
interaction: We are available to guests by email, phone, or text. We know our neighborhood very well (!) and care about our community- let us know when you need something or have questions!
house_rules: Please note that all house rules stem from previous experience & are strictly enforced. Property has exterior surveillance. • Check-in is 3 p.m.  • Checkout is 11 A.M.   • No parties, strictly enforced.  You will be asked to leave, no refunds. • All guests must be paying registered guests.  No additional guests allowed without prior written consent of the homeowner.  • Any evidence or smell of cigarette, marijuana, etc. inside the house will be AUTOMATIC loss of deposit. No burning of anything in the house to include candles, incense, etc. • Throw away all excessive garbage in green exterior trash can located on the side of the house. Excessive garbage is anything that does not fit into the kitchen and/or bedroom garbage cans. • If the apartment is left trashed (beyond normal use), we will request some or all of the security deposit. In other words, treat this home with respect. • Please do not turn off the heat during the winter or air conditioning during summer at any time. Always ke
host_about:
We met in Japan, moved to Columbus in 2009, and have been loving it ever since!  We are both experienced travelers (25+ countries on 5 continents between us) & enjoy renovating historic homes and building new homes.

We love being hosts- providing a comfy home and delivering a unique experience when visiting our city. We know quite a lot about Short North entertainment & food establishments- there is so much to do here, feel free to ask!

Our life motto- Live like someone left the gate open!

name: Sweet Suite in Historic Woodland Park, downtown
summary: 3rd floor suite includes updated kitchen, a beautiful spacious bathroom and large living space. Comfortable Queen-size bed, lots of light and great views of the park and gardens are my favorite highlights of this space. New HE washer and dryer in your private laundry room. Fun history happened here, Jazz greats jammed in this space, and many books that belonged to the judge who built the house and later left to work in the White House are in the library downstairs.
space: This is a 3rd floor suite with newly remodeled kitchen, spacious bathroom and laundry room. We can offer free on-street parking, a YMCA only a one block walk away, and a two block walk to Franklin Park Conservatory.  You have the option of a private entry through the side gate and up the butler's staircase if you don't wish to enter through the house.  There is generous space for a Queen size blow up mattress which  I can provide with notice including bedding and pillows. (It is a very nice one with a headboard)

notes: The pink bin in the pantry is intended for recyclables. Trash and recyclables can left in the solarium and I will take them to the outside dumpsters.
transit: Bus stops are a block from the house, and Uber is very established here. I have never had a guest wait more than a few minutes for a ride, all hours of the week.
access: You are welcome to explore the home, especially the paneled library which retains books from the original owners as well as owners since.  Please enjoy the gardens if you are interested, the fish like to be fed twice a day in warmer weather, which is next to  the screened porch. It is a great place to drink your coffee or enjoy a beverage in the evening.
interaction: Kitchen is stocked with dishes, utensils, cookware, etc.  Toaster oven and food processor are in the pantry.  Happy to lend ingredients from my kitchen, or any other kitchen needs that that aren't already in yours.
house_rules: We are early risers, even on weekends. We greatly appreciate your keeping the noise level down after 10pm.  We prefer you do not put linens in the washer as you leave. (They tend to have fewer wrinkles if they spend less time sitting in the washer). Please Leave any trash or recyclables in the solarium, which is just inside the door to your left as you exit. It’s easy for me to collect them there and the dogs won’t get into them.
host_about: I am a garden consultant and arborist I love dogs, and all kinds of plants.

name: 2 Bedroom house- Central Columbus! Housepitality.
summary: My place is close to nightlife, public transport, MAPFRE stadium, parks, OSU, downtown, and the Short North. You’ll love my place because of the kitchen, the coziness, the front and back yard, the front porch with grill, and the hardwood floors. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and groups. The house has a total of 2 queen beds, one sofa bed, and an air mattress upstairs. A 3rd queen bed is in our un-finished basement. Hi-speed WiFi!
space: This is a cozy smaller house being just under 700 sq. ft. The house is fully equipped everything to make yourself feel at home. There is a TV in every room, front and back porch, a stocked kitchen, and a basement with an extra bed, washer and dryer. The in-finished basement also has an extra queen bed. There are no egress windows, but it is clean and painted. The versatile living room can be arranged with a table in the middle for meals or a card game. Or the living room can be set up as a bedroom.

I have a chill cat who may even greet you. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers.

neighborhood_overview: German Village in known for its narrow, euro-style brick streets. It's a historical neighborhood with incredible houses, one of the best book stores to get lost in, a handful of restaurants, and a killer bakery called: Kitties Cakes that you MUST TRY!
notes: I make a pretty good cup of french press in the mornings. I require all guests to remove their shoes once they enter. I'm a gay-friendly host.
transit: Access to COTA's #8 is a few blocks away, off the park. This line takes you directly into downtown. There is also the free CBUS Circulator that COTA provides. I love this bus b/c it's ALWAYS on time! It only hits certain neighborhoods along High St. so make sure to look up the route and see if it fits. We have two CoGo Bike Share Stations; one off Schiller Park and the other is on 3rd St. These are half less than 1/2 mile from my house.   (Website hidden by Airbnb)   (Website hidden by Airbnb)

name: Your OWN private Victorian Village room.
summary: Located close to the area called the Short North, with parks, restaurants and dining, art and culture, and the Arena District, you’ll love my place because of the historic Victorian Village neighborhood, and all of  the activities within walking distance: Comfest, Pride Parade, Doo Dah Parade, Highball, Columbus Marathon, Red, White and Boom, and Gallery Hops. You can walk or take the bus to The Ohio State University or downtown. My place is perfect for couples, singles and business travelers.
space: Your spacious room is on the 3rd floor, at the back of the house which makes street noise minimal. You have a closet, baseboard heat, window air conditioner and plenty of light. We, the hosts, share the 2nd floor bathroom with our guests.
description: Located close to the area called the Short North, with parks, restaurants and dining, art and culture, and the Arena District, you’ll love my place because of the historic Victorian Village neighborhood, and all of  the activities within walking distance: Comfest, Pride Parade, Doo Dah Parade, Highball, Columbus Marathon, Red, White and Boom, and Gallery Hops. You can walk or take the bus to The Ohio State University or downtown. My place is perfect for couples, singles and business travelers. Your spacious room is on the 3rd floor, at the back of the house which makes street noise minimal. You have a closet, baseboard heat, window air conditioner and plenty of light. We, the hosts, share the 2nd floor bathroom with our guests. You may use the kitchen, 2nd floor laundry, TV room, front and back porches, dining room, front parlor and back yard. Any and all petting of the dogs is highly encouraged. We enjoy conversations with our guests if they have time and the inclination. Victorian Vi
neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village is halfway between The Ohio State University and downtown Columbus.  Our house is just 3 blocks from the lively Short North, which features galleries, restaurants and unique shopping.  Also, 4 blocks away is beautiful Goodale Park.  On July 4th, you can watch the infamous Doo Dah Parade from our front porch.  You can walk down the street to watch Red, White and Boom. In the fall, the Columbus Marathon passes by our house (mile 25).  Every 1st Saturday is Gallery Hop in the Short North.  Goodale Park is the location for Pride festivities and Comfest.
notes: We are currently working on renovating rooms on the second floor.  While this will only affect the use of the TV room, there may be some plaster dust settling around the house even after clean up. The shower is clean, wiped down after every use, but the old grout makes it appear otherwise.  Redoing the shower is a future project.
transit: A bus line passes both directions down Neil Ave., with stops on our block. We have an off street parking space beside our garage, off the alley that runs behind our house. For some strange reason, Uber sometimes tries to let guests out in the back behind the garage.
access: You may use the kitchen, 2nd floor laundry, TV room, front and back porches, dining room, front parlor and back yard.
interaction: Any and all petting of the dogs is highly encouraged. We enjoy conversations with our guests if they have time and the inclination.
house_rules: Street shoes should not be worn in the room because of white carpet. Also no food or drinks, except water, in the room because of the carpet.
host_about: I enjoy traveling, quilting, gardening, reading and sometimes cooking.

host_about:
Greetings! 

Thanks for taking a moment to learn a little bit more about me. I'm a young professional who works in the Real Estate business - often times it consumes my days and nights; weekends too! However, I wouldn't have it any other way and I'm very passionate about what it do. 

Five things that I can't live without: 

1. My iphone! It's on your top 5 too! ;) 
2. My dog Tyson (Sheltie) - 5 years old & 18lbs 
3. Coffee - it's the first thing I do in the morning! 
4. Laptop - Personally/Professionally 
5. Toothbrush/Toothpaste - clean and nice teeth are a priority to me. 

I enjoy having Air BnB guest because Columbus is my roots and I get to share that with someone visiting. However, it does not stop there; it's a two-way street I get to meet people from all over the world, with stories, culture, viewpoints that I have never been exposed to in my lifetime. It's fun! I like to entertain! Of course, the few extra bucks is nice too. 

I'm Not Your Average Joe!  Look forward to meeting you in person. 

Be well & talk soon, 

Joseph

neighborhood_overview: German Village is on the National Register of Historic Places, and the German Village Commission oversees the protection of the historic architecture that is the core identity of the neighborhood.   German Village has all sorts of unique experiences in restaurants, wine stores, book stores, parks, bars and coffee shops.  It is very walkable although public transit comes right through the village, making it easy and worry free to get to hot-spots like Ohio State, the Arena District and the Short North. Downtown Columbus is steps away, with theater, concerts, art and world-class sports including the Columbus Blue Jackets, the Crew S.C., the Clippers, and a little known college football team that go by "The Buckeyes".
notes: This is a quiet neighborhood consisting mostly of owner-occupied homes.  There is tolerance for outdoor festivities with a basic regard for other people.
transit: There are COTA bus stops close by, including the FREE Downtown Circulator.  There are also COGO rental bicycles all over downtown and a nearby rack for rental.  Lyft and Uber service Columbus as does Car2Go.
access: Guests have free use of both primary living floors, plus the attic office space with printer, and the fenced back yard with seating areas and gas grill.  The entire home and outdoor area has great wireless coverage.  Guests are given a code to use on the front door, eliminating keys.
interaction: Host lives on the same street and can respond quickly if you have questions about the home, the area, or need a spare toothbrush.
house_rules: Fireplace will not be left on,  faucets off, when away from the residence. Heat will not be set below/above 55/78 in Winter or below 73 in Summer. Guests will not attempt to access or view any space - physical or digital, that is secured via physical lock, digital password or PIN. Wipe up major spills or splatters in kitchen before they dry, please :) Notify host immediately of problems with appliances, devices, WiFi, plumbing or mechanicals. Use coasters, wipe up spills, keep bathroom sanitary. No smoking indoors, use ashtrays outdoors. Respect the neighbors, follow reasonable quiet hours 10pm -8am.
host_about:
I work in technology but technology hates me.  I persevere.

I've lived in the neighborhood for 20 years, so I obviously think it is THE BEST part of Columbus to live and play in.  After your reservation is confirmed I provide a (Hidden by Airbnb) map of some great destinations that are within walking distance of the BnB, and I live within shouting distance so I'll be there to assist you.

neighborhood_overview: You will be located in the heart of the Downtown Columbus in Victorian Village. This neighborhood is part of the Short North Arts District which hosts Gallery Hop the first Saturday of every month and includes some of the best restaurants and nightlife in the city, all within a couple blocks. Goodale Park is a half a block away and includes a fountain park and 33 acres of beautiful tree-lined walkways. It was donated to the city in 1851 and is bordered by historic Victorian mansions on original brick streets. Within eyesight of the front stoop, you're close to a CVS, ATM, deli, and coffee shop on Neil Ave. You can also catch the best concerts at EXPRESS LIVE!, Columbus Clippers minor league baseball at Huntington Field, and Columbus Blue Jackets hockey in the Arena District at Nationwide Arena.
notes: There is some minor renovation currently; the front door is being replaced soon so a couple walls are getting prepped for that.
transit: Most things are an easy walk! An Uber or Lyft is never more than 5 min away. The COTA Circulator bus (CBUS) is free and runs up and down High St making a loop from the Short North, Downtown, German Village and back. COTA AirConnect also runs a $2.75/trip airport shuttle bus with stops next to the convention center, right across the the park from my place. Walk Score gives my place a rating of 83 out of 100. This location is very walkable so most errands and activities can be accomplished on foot. CoGo Bike Share operates a station right across Neil Ave., just around the block. You will have one dedicated off-street parking spot next to my place. Please take note of where your spot is in your reservation details, all other off-street spots are for neighbors and my street is permit-only parking. Neil Ave. is non-permit and free to park if you need extra parking.
access: Listing includes guestroom and second floor hallway bathroom which is shared with the resident, please do not leave personal belongings. Guests are welcome to use the half bath on the first floor as well. Kitchen, laundry room, and living room are for resident use.
house_rules: - Quiet hours between midnight & 7:00am are appreciated - Kitchen & Laundry room are generally for resident use only. - Please let me know your approximate arrival time and if you'll need parking
host_about: I grew up in southwest Ohio and moved to Columbus in 2009 after finishing Army officer candidate school. I often tell folks that if it wasn't for Columbus I wouldn't have stayed in Ohio. Columbus is truly a great city, 15th in the nation in population and a little big city that exudes charm and a vibrant, progressive culture that I'm grateful to live in. I work for a great company that I'm able to have a walking commute through historic Victorian Village and am always looking for opportunities to find undiscovered gems around town and around central Ohio. I love spending time with my chosen family of friends whether it be traveling on vacation, wine nights, movies, or happy hours. Between work and being a puppy parent to my chocolate Lab, Jonas, I'm working on finishing my degree in Public Administration with a follow-on masters degree. It's been exciting and rewarding meeting people from all over the country and beyond that I've been fortunate to host. I look forward to welcoming you for your stay in my home and in the heart of a great city like Columbus. https://www.airbnb.com/users/26073351/listings?user_id=26073351&s=50

The neighborhood is filled with so much character and charm with several different designs of architecture being seen over several City blocks.  Over the years some of that charm has been lost, but it's on a rebound and Woodland Park is once again an exciting neighborhood.
notes: Additional Info I have two cats, one male and one female. Their names are Diesel and Sophie.  They are more like dogs and are very well behaved, extremely lovable and super clean. They do enjoy going in the back yard, but I would prefer them not to be left out if I'm not present.
transit: Easy access to I-670, and Broad Street.  Uber is available as well as Taxi service. COTA bus stops are within walking distance from the home. Easton Town Center is a quick 10 minute drive (8 miles) away for some afternoon shopping and for a night out, the Short North is only 4 miles away..

The front porch is screened in- for you to enjoy early morning sunshine while you have your coffee & still have privacy. Decent size living room comfortably seats 8-9. Basement: has one studio bedroom, with full bath and a wet bar with beautiful wood tree trunk countertop.  Attic: Wooden staircase takes you to this cosy space upstairs. There are two beds in the attic. One queen bed sleeps right under a skylight. The other is next to a window in a nook. neighborhood_overview: Westgate is a beautiful neighbourhood surrounded by charm,  character and lots of trees. No cookie cutter homes here, all the homes have their own personality.  People here are very friendly and down to earth. There are also paths to walk and parks nearby. The Westgate park Camp Chase bike trail is only 1 mile away!
notes: We have 5 real beds and we use high-end bed sheets. All bedsheets are absolutely white with high thread count. Therefore we request you to NOT bring food, beverages in any of the bedrooms. We understand that some guests may have extra sensitive skin so we DO NOT use harsh chemicals to clean the bedsheets. We request ask to remove the makeup before settling in the beds. Stained bedding will need to be replaced and is the reason for forfeited security deposit.
transit: There is plenty of parking on site and on the street. Getting around- Cota Bus Lines are close by (on Broad St) for greater access to Columbus.  Uber is always closer :)
access: All guests will have access to the entire house. We have TVs on main floor living room and in the basement (Netflix youtube etc available on both Smart TVs). Guests may use the laundry facilities if you are at the house for a longer period (over 4 days). Guests will also have kitchen privileges for light breakfast cooking. We do not have a range hood and to prevent lingering food odour, we want to limit the light cooking to 10-15 min. Please feel free to reach out to us if you have any questions regarding this.
interaction: Work keeps us away so we may not meet unless intentional however you are welcomed to call me at any time of your stay and I'd be happy to help.
house_rules: A. Washer and dryer to be used only if you are staying for 4 days and more.  B.  As mentioned before we do not have a range hood yet (coming soon) and to prevent lingering food odour, we try to limit it to 15-20 mins. We request you the same. Thank you for your cooperation and patience.  C. There is a garage on the property but that is not included in this listing and is inaccesible.
host_about:
Hello! I am Rue. I love early morning sunshine, travel experiences, aged wine, fresh coffee, nature and its beautiful endless skies.

After working with various corporates for more than a decade I decided to start my own business. Since we moved for business, I was able to use my home on AIRBNB.

While decorating this house we kept comfort and design in forefront of our mind. I open our home to Airbnb guests from all cultures, backgrounds, and nationalities. I look forward to building wonderful new friendships with people around the globe. Thank you for considering our place to stay, hope to talk to you soon. :)

space: Second Flight is a light-filled, airy one bedroom apartment nestled on the second story in the back of our overgrown Victorian home.  Formerly servant's quarters overlooking the back yards tucked behind historic brick Italianate and Queen Ann houses, it offers a completely private entrance, large bedroom, kitchen, full bath, and living room with full convertible futon couch as a second bed.  It has a large desk for work surface, WIFI, and a 40 inch TV with Cable and HDMI inputs.  Head to the OSU game or out into the Short North for coffee or bites and drinks --  on foot or by bus 1/2 a block away in THE most walkable district in the city. Then come home and curl up.  You'll find groceries at the nearby Kroger (1/2 a block) or goodies and ethnic foods at the North Market next to the Columbus Convention Center.
description: Roost in the "Second Flight" apartment minutes from downtown in the Short North arts district, 5 blocks from OSU and 1/2 a block from grocery store,  public transport, while exploring the city and its nightlife. Comfy Queen bed, high ceilings, hardwood floors, WIFI and Cable, with full functioning kitchen make for a cozy walkable getaway. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is pretty dynamic.  Archways of colored lights span High Street, the main drag through the Short North.  Originally a commercial warehouse district in the early 1900’s, the short North experienced a renaissance driven by artists and gallery owners in the 1980’s.  Now full of galleries, shops and restaurants, craft breweries and live theatre it stays pretty lively day and night. It is THE most walkable district in the city and quite safe, although it is an urban neighborhood, where it is advisable to keep your eyes open and wits about you. We have always felt quite safe here the past 25 years including raising our 2 children. And if you tire of walking you can always jump on the “C-bus” (every few minutes along High street) a free city bus dedicated exclusively to downtown, the short north and even German Village just south of downtown.  The short north and its rebirth has spawned other downtown development including the historical residential “Victorian Village”, a hos
notes: For short stays, one of the great things about the house is its location. It is in THE most walkable district in the city with its unique mix of shops, galleries, restaurants theater etc. it isn't like everywhere else. There are remarkably few of the big chain stores you'll find in most "shopping"/entertainment destinations. It is in keeping with the Short North's organic rebirth led by artists and gallery owners in the 1980's. And of course, there is the Ohio State University just a 5 block walk up High Street. It is perhaps the largest campus in the U.S. with 55,000+ students and home to the Buckeyes at a stadium holding nearly twice that number. The neighborhood is quite safe, although it is urban, and it is advisable to keep your eyes open and wits about you. We have always felt quite safe here the past 25 years including raising our 2 children. Also very convenient; less than one block from an updated Kroger Supermarket and liquor store, not to mention the High Street Brewing craf
transit: Your “2nd Flight” is less than one block from High Street which bisects the City of Columbus east and west.  It is also the street which serves as the main artery through the Short North. It’s a great place to walk, look around, duck into shops, cafes, restaurants, start walking again.  There are also buses running up and down High Street which will take you anywhere in the city, but the real delight is the “C-Bus” a free city bus dedicated to serving just downtown and areas immediately adjacent including the Short North, The Arena district, the Greater Columbus Convention Center, The North Market, Downtown Columbus, and German Village immediately south of Downtown.    There are also inexpensive CoGo bicycles at several rental kiosks up and down High Street to let you explore at greater speed.
access: Access to Second Flight is along the walkway on the left side of the house and around back to the second flight of steps (the wooden ones) to an entrance door marked "76 D Second Flight."  Find the key inside the wall mounted lock box for both deadbolt and lock-set.  The light-switch is on the left wall of stairwell.  Then climb the covered wooden steps up to the second story landing.  The second key turns the deadbolt 1/4 turn to the left, and you're inside.
interaction: You can find us in the front of the house behind the large double doors on the front porch.  Please twist the door bell ringer or text us.  We are here for as much or as little as you need us to orient you to the apartment and the neighborhood.  We love meeting new people -- it's one of the best things about AirBnB, but we are very conscious of your privacy, and we are always just a call or text away.
host_about: Hello, I am a married  father of 2  recently grown sons. My wife, Julie, and I are now offering part of our overgrown Victorian house to Air BnB guests.  By day I am an attorney in general practice and landlord; Julie is a psychotherapist. By free time, we are musicians (mainly a cappella vocalists though with some harmonica, clarinet, a very little tuba and hand drums thrown in.  We  enjoy jamming and improvising with others). I am a motorcyclist and lover of small affordable British roadsters, a mechanical tinkerer. We  are rehabbers/restorers of old houses with avid interests in music of all kinds, art, books, film, food (the more local and authentic the better), all manner of whiskeys and especially conversation.  I am  French by birth, and still fluent. I would say we are  Midwestern/progressive  by long residence and disposition; usually gregarious, though sometimes quieter and observant. We like to travel fairly light, although we are probably  a little "long in the tooth" to be truly "spartan."  I suppose our  style of Air b&b hosting is to  provide a comfortable safe staging ground and general guidance from which guests can explore on their own.  Current life motto might be something like "The best revenge is living engaged!"

neighborhood_overview: Olde Towne East is a great old neighborhood.  100 years ago, it was the most fashionable part of town.  Today, it is one of the most diverse, up and coming places in Columbus: one by one, the old houses around us have been renovated and restored to their former grandeur.   That said, Olde Towne is definitely an urban environment.  Parts of it are still gritty around the edges.  A few houses remain boarded up.  But it is absolutely a safe, diverse neighborhood, full of diverse folks: black and white, straight and gay, old and young, rich and poor.
transit: Columbus is definitely a driving town.  A car will always make things easier.  Still, you can catch a COTA bus on Broad Street, and bike rental kiosks (Gogo bikeshare) are scattered around town.
access: The whole apartment is yours.
interaction: We live nearby, and are [almost] always available to be of assistance.
house_rules: No smoking in the unit.  Use the patio, please!  Please leave the place in approximately the same condition you found it.  People live in the apartment above this unit, so please keep things relatively quiet.  No parties.
host_about:
Jay and Michael are newly married, traveling through life and the world together.  Nice, respectable boys both of them.  

Interests include old things, good food and fine wine, dogs, Lana, art museums, history, video games, antique shops, fashion, second hand bookshops.  Priorities:  eating delicious things not eaten before, seeing beautiful places not seen before, meeting extraordinary people not met before.

summary: Hello travelers!  Going to OSU or the Short North?  Don't need a full kitchen, but want a entire place to yourself with a private entrance?  This is it! This is a unique guest suite in the first floor of a vintage building on a quiet street, right between OSU and the popular Short North Arts District - walk to campus, shops, night life, and restaurants!  Part of this building is currently being renovated - please read all the details before booking.  Ask about reserved parking if you need it.
space: The Airbnb space is set up in the front part of the first floor of a multi-unit building, in what was originally a living room and dining room, with beautiful original hardwood floors, two chandeliers, and stained glass windows.  We are doing some renovations in this building and there may be some construction noise from 9a to 5p.  If you need quiet during those hours, this is not the best place for you. The suite is closed off from the construction areas and there is no access to the rest of the building at this time. There are other people living in the building, but the suite has a private exterior entrance and all doors can be locked from the inside. neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is in the perfect location between Ohio State and the Short North. Our street and the nearby ones have some beautiful grand Victorian homes. This neighborhood draws a healthy blend of graduate students, young professionals, and families. Many of the grand Victorian homes have been split up into multiple units, like this one!
