transit: Here are just a few of the places you can easily get to on foot: ~3 minutes to Junior's Tacos (food truck at 5th and Highland) ~3 minutes to Angry Baker (coffee shop), the Bottle Shop (bar), and Hamptons on King (bar) ~5 minutes to High Street (North High Brewing, Condado Tacos, Paulie Gee's Pizza, Kroger grocery store, and more bars, shopping, and restaurants) ~10 minutes to Ohio State's central campus ~15 minutes to Wexner Medical Center ~20 minutes to Ohio Stadium ~30 minutes to Express Live ~30 minutes to Columbus Convention Center ~30 minutes to Nationwide Arena
access: On the day of your arrival, if you have not heard from us by 4:00 pm, please send us a message on Airbnb and we'll get back to you quickly.  Please send this message through Airbnb (instead of texting or calling directly) so that we will all see the message. We'll provide lockbox details as soon as the place is ready.
interaction: We'll send you the lockbox info as soon as the place is ready. There's a guestbook inside with some details on the neighborhood and other recommendations. We are nearby if you need anything!
house_rules: It's very important to us that you have a great stay and that you take good care of our house. If you have any issues during your stay, please let us know right away so we can address them! We live nearby and we want to make sure your stay is excellent.  Here are a few rules that you can follow to make us happy hosts. Rule 1: be respectful and leave the space as clean as you found it. We reserve the right to assess additional fees for cleaning or damages if these rules are not followed. Hopefully this is pretty basic stuff, but we want to be clear about how we expect our space to be used. This is not a hotel or a place to throw a party. Trash: Use the bins provided throughout the apartment. Do not leave any trash around the space. If you generate more trash than will fit in the bins, throw it away in the big green trash bins in the alley behind the house. Recycling: Use the metal bin inside the unit. As with the trash, if it fills up, take it to the alley behind the house and empty it
host_about: Hi, I'm Nat!  I'm a long time Columbus resident - raised in the Short North (between downtown and campus) graduated from Ohio State, and settled in the Short North after living in Indianapolis and Chicago for a while. I care very much about the neighborhood and the properties that I manage. For my day job, I'm an IT consultant, but on the weekends I like to spend my free time renovating and managing properties.  I live with my wife Kate in the Short North, between Ohio State's campus and downtown Columbus.

name: Sleeping in the City
summary: Microliving is in heart of the city and walking distance to art, theater, music, and dining.  Our location overlooks a hot entertainment district with a wall of windows allowing you to experience everything the city has to offer without leaving your cozy bed!  Take in the beauty of the Columbus Commons Holiday lighting while sipping wine in your pj's.  Enjoy the onsite dining of Hadley's Kitchen and Bar.  We welcome all, but our micro unit is best for singles, couples and business travelers!
space: The space is a private apartment with all the amenities to enjoy your stay in the city.  The building is residential with full time property management on staff to assist for the duration of your stay.  The building is secure and safe and in a walking neighborhood.

neighborhood_overview: Sometimes referred to as the 4th and Main district or the Gallery District, our neighborhood is home to bars, restaurants, salons, galleries and green spaces. Pamper yourself across the street at Square One, an Aveda Salon before you head out to an upscale dinner at Side Bar.  Whatever you need, its right here!
notes: Our listing is located on one of the major thoroughfares in the city.  There is a direct route to OSU Campus, Columbus School of Art and Design and Columbus Community College.  We are a short drive from Otterbein and Ohio Dominican University.
transit: Just two blocks from the C-bus, you can ride for free all night and all day.  The C-bus is public transportation with stops in all the entertainment districts that border the city.  The Short North, The Arena District, Nationwide, German Village and Italian Village.

name: Beautiful Brewery District Apartment
summary: Located in the Brewery District, next to the iconic brick-lined German Village, this apartment is a short walk from many bars & restaurants. It's a block from a Cbus stop, a free shuttle connecting the Brewery District, Downtown, the Arena District & the Short North. The OSU campus is a short drive (<$10 with Uber) & the Columbus airport is a 15 min drive. With the skyline visible from the balcony, this stylish, centrally-located apartment is the perfect place to host your Columbus adventure.
space: Whether you're getting your morning started enjoying a fresh cup of coffee on our balcony bistro table, or relaxing on the couch in front of the TV after a long day of exploring Columbus's many treasures, this chic apartment is the perfect place to start and end each day during your time in the "Arch City!"
description: Located in the Brewery District, next to the iconic brick-lined German Village, this apartment is a short walk from many bars & restaurants. It's a block from a Cbus stop, a free shuttle connecting the Brewery District, Downtown, the Arena District & the Short North. The OSU campus is a short drive ( is a free bus service offered by COTA that connects the Brewery District to the Short North, making stops downtown and in the Arena District along the way.
neighborhood_overview: There are a number of parks and walkways throughout the Brewery District/German Village neighborhood. Our favorite is the Scioto Audubon Metro Park, located just behind our apartment complex. This park offers spectacular views of the Columbus skyline and also has a rock climbing, volleyball courts and much more. There is also a Kroger grocery store located next door to our complex, offering a convenient place to pick up food, drink, etc.
transit: Both Uber and Lyft are available in Columbus, and the city also has a great bus system known as the COTA. As mentioned before, the "Cbus" is a free bus service offered by COTA that connects the Brewery District to the Short North, making stops downtown and in the Arena District along the way.
access: While you're staying at our apartment, feel free to embrace the convenience of having a full-kitchen and entire apartment to yourself! There is also a 24-hour gym within the complex that you're welcome to use, in addition to a yoga room if starting your morning off with a little meditation is up your alley. We will also leave a parking pass for you to use throughout your stay so you don't need to stress about finding a place on the street.
interaction: We are always available via text or email to answer any questions you may have during your stay. Whether you're having technical difficulties in our apartment, or are just hoping to get a recommendation for a great dinner spot, don't hesitate to shoot us a message!
house_rules: - Complex quiet hours begin at 11pm on weekdays, midnight on the weekends - 24 hour gym - Free parking - Please inform us if you're a Michigan fan so we can properly decorate with OSU things beforehand ;)
host_about:
"Carpe Diem, Vita Brevis" Seize the Day, Life is Short.

Traveling is an essential part to getting the most out of what life has to offer. We've been fortunate enough to be able to travel all of the east, south and Midwestern portions of the United States, Eastern Canada, as well as Western Europe. We love museums and sights, but the best part of traveling is soaking up the culture of a different region of the world, and learning from others. 

When traveling, we hate to be in a hotel, hostel, or house; we want to be out enjoying all of the wonders that each city and country has to offer! Whether visiting a new city, or hosting others at our own apartment in Columbus, it's always our goal for ourselves and our guests to able to explore as much of the city as possible.

name: A Zen Art Oasis - Private Guest Room
summary: Featured in Columbus Monthly, our Victorian Village Neil Avenue metropolitan home with wood floors on the first floor and classic architecture lend to the feel along with local artists artwork throughout. It is a very inviting zen space where you will feel right at home.
space: Private zen like space with a queen size Baronet bed and night stand.  The space includes all the necessary amenities.
description: Featured in Columbus Monthly, our Victorian Village Neil Avenue metropolitan home with wood floors on the first floor and classic architecture lend to the feel along with local artists artwork throughout. It is a very inviting zen space where you will feel right at home. Private zen like space with a queen size Baronet bed and night stand.  The space includes all the necessary amenities. Guests are able to let themselves in at their convenience via a smart lock. You will have access to the main house only, not the third floor attic or basement.  Guests will have high speed internet access and a flatscreen TV with basic channels, a DVD player, and AppleTV. There will be an instructional binder on connecting both inside and outside of the home. My partner Stephanie and I along with our two indoor cats, Jordan and Bella are live in hosts, but not in the way.  We are happy to communicate over Airbnb messaging or through calls and texts. We encourage guests to contact us with any questions
neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village is halfway between The Ohio State University and downtown Columbus. Our house is just 3 blocks from the lively Short North, which features galleries, restaurants and unique shopping. Also, 4 blocks away is beautiful Goodale Park. On July 4th, you can watch the infamous Doo Dah Parade just down the street. You can walk down the street to watch Red, White and Boom. In the fall, the Columbus Marathon passes by our house (mile 25). Every 1st Saturday is Gallery Hop in the Short North. In June, Goodale Park is the location for Pride festivities and Comfest.  A full service grocery story is just down the street as well as many universities including CCAD, Capital, and Columbus State. Just a short drive (or 30 minute walk) to downtown Columbus!
notes: The patio offers a relaxing respite and the front porch has a teak glider to partake in the Neil happenings.  A Workout Room is attached to your bedroom with an E82 SportsArt Fitness elliptical, weight bench with weights, a hyper bench, and a stability exercise ball.
transit: Within walking distance to the Short North, OSU, and Goodale Park. Less than 50 yards to #7 &  #18 COTA bus line.  The city has Car2Go and bike shares available. Cabs and Uber car service are both plentiful. Parking is also available on the street in front of the house at no cost.

The unit is furnished with a queen size bed, night stands, elegant wrought iron vanity, bench, and luggage shelf, dining room table and chair set.

neighborhood_overview: This apartment is located in Olde Towne East, a neighborhood located in the historic Near East Side of Columbus. It is nestled between Downtown, Franklin Park, Old Oaks, and King-Lincoln. The area has over 1,000 homes, some as old as the 1830s, and more than 50 architectural styles including Italianate, Queen Anne and Victorian. These homes were built by many of the famous individuals of Columbus including industrialists, lawyers, judges, teachers, architects, mayors, governors, and legislators, many of whom shaped the city.
notes: Maximum 2 guests. No visitors are permitted (other than the guests). This is an apartment in a house with other occupants, on a quiet residential street. Absolutely no parties or group events.
transit: The apartment is on Bryden Rd, which features regular bus stops up and down the street leading into downtown and other areas. Uber and Car2Go also service this neighborhood extensively.

Branden & Diana

The Old North/Clintonville is a great neighborhood to explore. Just 2 blocks from my house is a bluegrass/soda bar, within 10 min walk there are many live music venues, and loads of great restaurants! Where to go? : One thing I love about this house is you are central to the city, and a close walk to many great places. This location is a great place to explore Columbus by foot or by car, being a close drive to anywhere via only a 2 min. to the I/71 freeway. Here are a few of the places I walk to often: Grocery and Carry out: There is a grocery store and many restaurants and bars within a short walk of my house. Luckey’s Market is my go-to place for groceries, and take out. Acre farm to table is great for a quick meal, or take out. One other recommendation I must give is the taco truck Exotic Latino Grill that parks outside the 14 – 0 on Hudsont and Indianola

My house is just 3 minutes drive from the I/71 freeway, and 10 minutes from downtown/short north. Uber and Lyft are great ways to get around in Columbus.

I believe that there are more good hearted, interesting people in the world than bad, and I want to meet them!!
I love to hike and explore the outdoors, travel to new places, and try different foods. I love my job as a nurse and taking care of people facing unfortunate events makes me appreciate my life and health. I don't want to take that for granted.
Thanks for visiting my listing. I look forward to meeting you, whoever you are. Take care of yourself:)

name: The Gallery (Short North/OSU/Downtown)
summary: This 2nd-story private apt. is at the back of my circa 1880 home. This cheerful cozy aerie provides the comforts of home (kitchen, wifi, & cable TV). Its prime location in the Short North is in easy reach of OSU and DT on foot or by bus. I expect guests to read my entire listing before booking & printed manual upon arrival, so that expectations are clear, most especially about the vintage bath & housekeeping. This is my home--not a hotel. I welcome all who know how to be good house guests.
space: The "Gallery" is a very small (300 sq. ft.), private 1-BR apartment attached to the back of my Victorian home on the second floor. The space consists of a fully furnished eat-in kitchen, bedroom with queen-sized bed, and bathroom sporting a vintage English-style bath (deep clawfoot tub fitted with a handheld shower head). It's extremely important for guests to realize that the bath setup does not allow for taking a shower standing up. The apartment gets wonderful light and has the feeling of an aerie. The walls are adorned with art--most of it with an Ohio bent. After you check in, you can leave your car parked out front and walk, bike, or bus the short distance to sports or music venues, galleries, restaurants, and shops.

neighborhood_overview: Whatever your reason for traveling to Columbus, you couldn't choose a better neighborhood to stay in if you want to get acquainted quickly with this happening city. This apartment is located at the beginning of the lively strip called The Short North Arts District. From here, you can walk or bike or take a COTA bus to the OSU campus or downtown ($2 per leg). There's also a FREE bus--the CBus--that will take you up and down High Street from the Short North to the edge of German Village. But there's plenty to see and do immediately nearby in walking distance.
notes: (1) Because of its size and other factors, the space is best suited for only 2 adults or 1 adult and older child, which is why I advertise the space as not suitable for children. I am flexible about that, depending on circumstances, and I have and do entertain requests from people with children.  (2) Free on-street parking is available for guests, but guests should be aware that it gets scarcer during evenings and weekends. If a guest finds it impossible to park, I am willing to take measures to assist upon request. (3) Guests are asked to please close both iron gates on the property when entering and exiting.
transit: Your host will provide you with information about getting around. Just know that just about everything is easily accessible from this location--by foot, bike, and bus as well as by car.
access: To get to the apartment from the curb, look for the stained glass house number above the front door, then enter the front gate and walk toward the bay windows to the side of the house. Enter a second gate and continue walking through a patio to the end of the house. IMPORTANT: to operate this gate, depress the latch and swing it toward the patio, not in the direction of the window. If you hit the stone windowsill, you are swinging the gate in the wrong direction. Once in the backyard, ,you will see the stairs leading up to the apartment. (The house was built in 1880 and is thus very tall, so it's important to note that there are quite a few steps to climb--see photo.) The key will be in a lockbox hanging on the apartment door, which requires a code to open. The code will be provided to guests before check-in. After entering the code, the compartment below it will reveal the key with a flip of fingers on the sides of the compartment. Guests are asked to please close both iron gates on t
interaction: I live in the main residence and am pseudo-retired, so I am likely to be on or near the premises most of the time. I like to think of myself as friendly and helpful, but I look to my guests to set the tone for how much interaction they prefer. That is, if you'd like to chat, I'm happy to oblige. If you just want to zoom in and out under the radar without making contact, that's fine, too. Do know that I will happily provide, upon request, any information or guidance you may need during your stay.
house_rules: Quiet time is 10 pm - 7 am.
host_about: I was born in Kentucky but bred and educated mostly in Ohio. After 30+ years living in the Washington, DC, area, this single 61-year-old youngster is back in Columbus, OH, renovating an ancient house (not something I saw happening, LOL) and getting very interested in homesteading. I was drawn back primarily for family reasons, but also because of the enormous riches this amazing big little city has to offer. I couldn't live without art, music, books, or travel (after family, of course). My life motto, if I have one, is "Barn's burnt down. Now I can see the moon."

name: COMMONS STUDIO DOWNTOWN - Blanket Forts Encouraged
summary: Experience the uncommon quality of Commons Studio. Located in the heart of downtown, the unique 2800 sq/ft loft space is steeped with rich, creative history. Originally a photography studio as far back as the late 1800s, many artists and prominent figures have spent time here. Today it again serves that same purpose. We are close to public transport, restaurants, theaters, nightlife, and the airport. Great for couples, solo adventurers, celebrities, business travelers, and furry friends (pets).
space: Commons Studio is a live/ work space occupied by myself, my lady Adrianne, and Namaskar -- our tiny lion. There is absolutely nothing like it to be found in Central Ohio. By day it serves as my photography studio and I generally start booking clients by 10am during the week. Upon arrival you will enter through the wrought-iron gate at street level, continue up the stairs, and then take a stroll through the hallway (regularly curated with local art) until you reach our unit in the back of the building.

transit: We are located conveniently along the CBUS line, our city's FREE downtown bus circulating from German Village, Brewery District, Arena District, Short North, and downtown. access: Enjoy access to the studio's lounge, sectional couch, air-mattress, entertainment center (HDMI projector w/9'x9' screen, Blu-ray player, turn-table), kitchen, awesome balcony, and ENORMOUS bathroom. Please note: Professional photoshoots, access to grip & lighting tools, and parties are not permitted without a signed rental agreement separate from the terms of your AirBnB booking. Inquire for more information.
house_rules: - Clean up after yourself - Close ALL DOORS behind you (including gate) - Check-in is after 5PM - Check-out is 10AM - NO COMMERCIAL PHOTOSHOOTS (if interested, please inquire about separate rental agreement)
host_about: Matt Reese is a commercial photographer with a mind for entrepreneurship and innovation. Proudly based in Columbus, Ohio, Matt has quickly built a career for himself in the the Midwest. His award-winning work has been featured in several gallery exhibitions, local and national publications, and thousands of (Hidden by Airbnb) profile photos through social marketing campaigns. With a background in both Fine Art and Marketing, his approach to photography attempts to blur the lines between art and commerce. In addition to his freelance work, he co-founded and produces motive., a networking event/ filmed program dedicated to the creative community (operating as a 501c3 nonprofit organization), serves as Chief Photographer & Producer at the Commons Studio, and is an active member of both the American Society of Media Photographers and American Advertising Federation.

summary: Enjoy a 1500 sq.ft. modern 2nd floor apartment in a historic home just steps off of High Street in the Short North. Relax on the front porch. Cook in the high end kitchen. Gather in the large living and dining area. Ten foot ceilings w/fans, bamboo floors, and open layout give this space an airy feel. Walk to the convention center, or The Ohio State University. Check out the fantastic restaurants, and shops. Perfect for an event weekend, or a great base of operations for a longer stay.
space: Master suite with king size bed, en suite master bath, laundry room, and sun room.  The second bedroom features a queen size bed and easy access to the second bathroom.  Kitchen includes granite counter tops, microwave, dishwasher, and coffee maker in addition to the refrigerator and electric stove. Fully stocked with dishes and cooking equipment. Dining room table comfortably seats six, and can be expanded to accommodate eight to ten.  It's a lovely place to have a meeting.   Open living area features two leather sofas, and smart TV for connecting to your preferred streaming services. Work at the desk in the office with natural light streaming in the windows. Off-street parking is available in a parking lot behind the building. Just let us know how many cars your group will have. This unit has a large, private, covered balcony.i

neighborhood_overview: Enjoy Northstar Cafe just around the corner for breakfast, brunch, lunch, or dinner. If you're into tacos, Condado is a fun spot. Mouton is a lovely choice for craft cocktails, and if caffeine is your need One Line Coffee shop is a great choice. The Short North has it all - from great events in Goodale Park and at the Convention Center, to restaurants, bars, coffee shops, galleries, and local shops. This apartment puts you in the heart of the neighborhood.
notes: This is a second floor apartment. Although the entire apartment is on one level, you do need to climb a flight of stairs at the entrance.
transit: The Short North is conveniently located between Ohio State University and Downtown Columbus. You're within easy walking distance of the Convention Center, Goodale Park (which hosts ComFest and other festivals), and many of the city's best restaurants, shops, and galleries. A longer walk takes you to Ohio State University to the north or Downtown to the south.  In addition to walking, the free Circulator Bus stops just around the corner and takes you to Downtown and German Village. CoGo bike rental stations dot the neighborhood.  Of course Lyft and Uber are popular options for getting around.  The apartment also features reserved off-street parking behind the house for guests who have cars.
access: You'll have the apartment to yourself. The apartment comes with high speed internet access - 100mbps. Each of the four apartments in the building has its own exterior door, so if you encounter other guests it will be in the shared yard or the parking lot.
interaction: We live nearby, and can be available if needed for maintenance issues or other concerns. We may briefly come by to greet you and make sure everything is going well with your stay.
house_rules: As a guest, please be aware that our other guests and tenants live in the downstairs apartments. Be respectful of them by keeping noise levels reasonable. especially from 11pm-7am.
host_about:
I dig psychology, gardening, cycling, being a gym rat, and cooking. I have volunteered at a kids camp every summer since 1999 that teaches critical thinking and a love for nature. 

I have lived in Columbus most of my life and I love it here and I love sharing it with other people. 

My career in the non-profit sector has let me travel all over the country. I love the Bay Area, NYC, Washington state, and the Rockies.

neighborhood_overview: My house is on the edge of campus and Clintonville. A number of restaurants serving anything from Asian to Mediterranean to organic fare just 5-10 minutes away. We also have some Columbus landmarks (Blue Danube and Dick's Den) with American diner/pub food even closer. The Wexnar Arts Center is nearby. Of course, you can walk to OSU in 10 minutes. In four minutes, you can walk to the Olentangy River and the path that runs along it. Quiet, lots of trees, nice.
notes: I do not have air-conditioning. The bedroom has two tall windows and comes with a fan, but no air-conditioning. I don't mind it, but then again, I lived in Cambodia with A/C -- and loved it. So, yes, this house can get hot. Please be aware of that when summer temperatures are on the rise before making a reservation.
transit: The High Street bus is at the end of my street (a 2 minute walk). This is a major thoroughfare in Columbus so High Street buses easily give you access to OSU, the Short North Area, Downtown, shopping areas, and grocery stores.

name: Blue Cat Cottage - Near the Airport and Easton!
summary: The Blue Cat Cottage is perfect for families or business travelers wanting a quiet, cozy place to themselves. Located near the airport, 670, Easton and only 15 minutes to Downtown, it's a great location for exploring Columbus.  The freshly renovated house comes with two bedrooms with queen beds, a fully equipped kitchen, WiFi, Roku TV with Netflix and off street parking for two cars.
space: The living room has one of the most comfy sofas I've tried, with the Columbus skyline above it.  It faces the TV which offers both local channels and a ton of channels on Roku.  The living room also includes a large desk and comfortable office chair for travelers needing space to work.   The kitchen includes a large dining table with four chairs.  It also has almost everything you need to make light meals with basic pots and pans.  A microwave, toaster, coffeemaker and electric kettle are there to help.  Some snacks are also provided :) Both bedrooms have brand new queen-sized beds with soft linens. There are dressers and the closets include hangers.   The bathroom includes new, fluffy towels, shampoo, conditioner and body wash and plenty of hot water.

summary: This 1200 sq ft, 3 Bed, 1 Bath duplex is part of a renovated historic 1900s duplex. Located in Weinland Park, 2 blocks from High St. and the Short North, it is a short walk to many popular bars and restaurants nearby.   Conveniently located: 1.3 mi - Columbus Convention Center 2 mi - OSU stadium 2.3 mi - Schottenstein Center 2.5 mi - Crew Stadium/Expo Center/Fair grounds 3 mi radius - all areas of interest in Downtown Please be sure to check out our other listings nearby for larger groups!
space: The apartment can easily accommodate both small and large groups. If you have an especially large group, we have 3 other listings nearby on Airbnb called Comfy, Cozy, and Urban I (see listings under our profile). The first floor level has a nice size kitchen fully equipped for cooking meals.  The kitchen is separated from the open living room and dining area. There is WIFI throughout and cable TV in the living room.  The couches are EXTREMELY COMFY. The second floor has three (3) bedrooms and a small one shower-only bathroom.  Each bedroom has a comfortable queen bed and plenty of closet and drawer space. Two of the bedrooms are a decent size and can fit a pack-n-play.  The third bedroom is on the smaller side. Plenty of towels, washcloths, a hair dryer, and shampoo/conditioner/body wash are provided. Apartment has central A/C and a fenced backyard with two private decks for each side. neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is one of the Midwest’s best kept secrets. There is a huge variety of unique shops, bars and restaurants, and art galleries along High Street and a number of annual events that take place year-round. We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Weinland Park, a cool, urban area on the East side of High St above 5th Ave.   Is the neighborhood safe? We live nearby and feel the neighborhood is relatively safe.  Please note this is the city- we do have petty crime in the Short North and University area, and always advise to practice common sense such as not leaving valuables in your car (we have not had any issues at our apartments, I state this because we are in the city) and walk with a buddy at night on well-lit, busy roads such as High Street, Summit, and 5th Ave. Near the following: • Restaurants- The Table, Condados
notes: • Housekeeping service is per stay, not per night. Additional cleaning visits can be arranged for longer stays if needed.  Visits must be paid in advance and are non-refundable if visits are cancelled. Please inquire when booking. • Pack n Play, high chair, and/or Queen air bed available upon request- please let us know your needs prior so we can prepare all the necessary items. • Please be courteous to neighbors- Noise must be keep to a minimum after 10 p.m. This is one of two units with a shared wall.   • There is no handicap access. There are two steps to enter the front of the house.  • Guests with allergies and related medical issues and/or sensitivities- cleanliness is one of our top priorities, however we cannot 100% guarantee that the apartment is free of pet dander, cigarette smoke, air fresheners/cleaning product scents, or any other elements that may trigger a medical problem or sensitivity. Please note we cannot issue refunds due to the reasons above. •  Street Sweeping on

All other locations can be easily reached a number of ways: Taxis --- Uber -- COTA (Central Ohio Transit Authority) bus --- CoGo (Rental Bikes) --- Car 2 Go (Car Rentals) --- CBUS circulator About the CBUS circulator- It's FREE transportation from the Short North through downtown, all the way to German Village. Bus stops are at many points along High Street.  The closest stop is just a few blocks South from the apartment on 3rd Ave. It's about a $5-10 Uber ride to downtown. PARKING This apartment has 2 off-street parking spots.  It is accessible by alleyway off of Summit St. or 5th Ave.  There is also permit-free street parking available on both sides of Summit St. in front of the house. It’s usually easy to find a spot. It can get a little busy during the evenings but you can still find parking close by. Our guests have had no issues with parking. Please never leave valuable

name: Historic Circus House on Goodale Park
summary: Come stay in the historic Circus House carriage house on Goodale Park in the heart of Shorth North!  2 free parking spaces!!!! 2 blocks from High Street and private 2 car parking driveway. Beautiful 2 bedroom and 2 1/2 bath spacious and gorgeously appointed
space: Share a part of the great history of the famed Sells Family/Frank Packard design. Constructed as the "carriage" house in 1895 this was the servants quarters for Peter Sells Family, who at the time had one of the largest traveling Circuses in the United States.  The home is on the historic registry as well.. perfectly maintained with Chic decor, coupled with high-end, comfortable furnishings, creates a truly unique feel in this updated late 19th century historic two-story home. Ceiling fans, central air/heat, directTV, and WiFi are just a few conveniences you will enjoy during your stay.  both  bedrooms have pine oak hardwood which is original, the bathrooms have  custom tile original from 1895 ,. All bedrooms are located on the 2nd floor of the home. Kitchen has appliances, subzero fridge, minimal pots and pans, dishes and utensils, and a Keurig coffee maker. . neighborhood_overview: ABOUT GERMAN VILLAGE You are in one of the best parts of Columbus, Ohio—beautiful and historic German Village. There is so much to see and do and most of the area is pedestrian friendly. We have our favorite eateries including Barcelona, Sycamore Café, Brown Bag Deli, Pistachio Vera, Taco Tuesday at The Kitchen, Lindey’s, Katzinger’s, G Michaels, Harvest….. Check out German Village Society for details.  For fitness options, there is a Snap Fitness facility on Third Ave and Schiller Rec Center in the Park (both are fee-based). Laundromat is a block away.
notes: *The apt is on the second floor accessible by one flight of stairs. Please note there is no elevator. **Allergy alert: while we don't allow guest's pets we sometimes bring our dog when we clean the apt. ***Please note this a one bedroom apt with one queen bed. Second bed is a sleeper sofa in the LR (limited privacy as LR is a pass through room from bedroom to kitchen/bath).
transit: Schiller Park is just a block south. Programming includes Actors’ Theatre Shakespeare in the Park Thursdays-Sundays throughout the summer.  The closest rental bike (CoGo) station is by the Giant Eagle grocery store a block east of the apt (corner of Whittier and Jaeger). CoGo allows you to rent bikes and return to either this or any CoGo station in the city.  There is a free bus service—COTA’s Cbus that offers continuous service between German Village, Brewery District and the Short North.
access: Guests are given check in instructions and key codes evening before arrival.  They have full access to the entire apartment. No areas are off-limits.

neighborhood_overview: You will be located in the heart of the Downtown Columbus in Victorian Village. This neighborhood is part of the Short North Arts District which hosts Gallery Hop the first Saturday of every month and the best restaurants and nightlife in the city, all within a couple blocks. Goodale Park is a half a block away and includes a fountain park and 33 acres of beautiful tree-lined walkways. It was donated to the city in 1851 and is bordered by historic Victorian mansions on original brick streets. Goodale Park is home to Columbus's Pride Festival and Community Festival (Comfest) in June and numerous other musical and performance events throughout the year. Within eyesight of the front stoop, you're close to a Giant Eagle grocery store and a CVS on Neil Ave. Additionally, you can catch the best concerts at EXPRESS LIVE!, Columbus Clippers minor league baseball games, and Columbus Blue Jackets hockey in the Arena District. Check Columbus Underground for the scoop on area places and events!
notes: Both beds are full beds. A queen size air mattress is available in the front guestroom closet. The front guestroom original windows are currently being rehabbed but are sealed and storm windows are in place.
transit: Most things are an easy walk! An Uber or Lyft is never more than 5 min away. The Columbus Circulator bus (CBUS) is free and runs up and down High St making a loop from the Short North, Downtown, German Village and back. My place has a Walk Score of 83 out of 100. This location is Very Walkable so most errands can be accomplished on foot. There is Good Transit nearby and it is Very Bikeable.
access: Listing includes front guestroom with private bathroom, rear guestroom shares second floor hallway bath with resident. Guests are welcome to use the half bath on the first floor as well. Entry & exit through main front door with personal keypad code. Please do not leave any belongings in the hallway bathroom. First floor (living room, kitchen & laundry room) are generally for resident use only.
house_rules: - Quiet hours between midnight & 7:00am are appreciated - Kitchen, laundry room, and living room are generally for resident use only - Please let me know your approximate arrival time and if you'll need parking
host_about: I grew up in southwest Ohio and moved to Columbus in 2009 after finishing Army officer candidate school. I often tell folks that if it wasn't for Columbus I wouldn't have stayed in Ohio. Columbus is truly a great city, 15th in the nation in population and a little big city that exudes charm and a vibrant, progressive culture that I'm grateful to live in. I work for a great company that I'm able to have a walking commute through historic Victorian Village and am always looking for opportunities to find undiscovered gems around town and around central Ohio. I love spending time with my chosen family of friends whether it be traveling on vacation, wine nights, movies, or happy hours. Between work and being a puppy parent to my chocolate Lab, Jonas, I'm working on finishing my degree in Public Administration with a follow-on masters degree. It's been exciting and rewarding meeting people from all over the country and beyond that I've been fortunate to host. I look forward to welcoming you for your stay in my home and in the heart of a great city like Columbus. https://www.airbnb.com/users/26073351/listings?user_id=26073351&s=50

This is not the house for you if you are looking to have a party or bring the party back with you. Guests are expected to be respectfu
host_about:
Howdy! I’m Jake. I’m originally from New York, and while I miss my friends and family back home (not to mention the beach!), I absolutely love my mid-west home here in Columbus, Ohio!
By day I’m a real estate investor and by night I’m a social butterfly with my friends. I'm also an Airbnb cohost where I mentor aspiring local hosts. I earned my Superhost status because I have high standards for value, cleanliness, and communication.
I enjoy travelling and creating new experiences. My favorite country is Guatemala. The people, the food and the historical sites are breathtaking. My favorite city is Chicago. Through these travels and coupled with my 12 years landlording, I’ve been fortunate to learn what makes a great host: a great home, with a friendly host, in an awesome neighborhood, and the ability to do the things you love! I try to ensure that each and every guest I host walks away with all of that and hopefully more.
My life motto is, well, really my grandmother’s advice, “Jakey, live with NO REGRETS” (I can hear her thick NYer accent now). Sometimes I guess we just need a little reminder of that… And so, I invite you to travel more and see the big, beautiful world we live in.

From a small town in NW Ohio, now living in Columbus.  I enjoy staying active playing sports and other outdoor activities. Staying in hotels is mundane.  Air bnb presents a unique opportunity to interact with other people and learn more about the area I'm staying.  And a best case scenario is make a new friend that I can visit my next time around in that area.

name: Stylish & Spacious Townhouse Right By OSU Campus
summary: My place is a brand new townhouse minutes away from everywhere you want to be in Columbus! It's the perfect location to walk to OSU Campus and the renowned Wexner Medical Center. You can also visit the Short North Arts District, Uber to downtown Columbus for shows, restaurants, and an awesome night life, or visit Grandview for eclectic bars and eats. My townhouse is within walking distance from some great local bars, coffee shops, and a grocery store for anything you might need during your stay.
space: Fully furnished townhouse with kitchen supplies, comfy beds, and soft towels, plus a Keurig with a selection of K-Cups to fuel your mornings! This place is perfect for extended stay since there is a washer and dryer in the home as well.

summary: You will definitely feel cozy and relaxed during your stay here.  Great for travelers who are looking for a clean and safe location.  Good for solo travelers, business travelers, and couples.  Lots of amenities like wifi, pool, gym, and netflix.  You will have a private bedroom and en suite bathroom in a two story condo.  Conveniently located near the freeway and many stores and restaurants.
space: Cozy and airy. Queen size bed. Freshly washed towels and sheets will be provided along with essential toiletry's such as shampoo, conditioner and soap.  The room has a tv and computer desk.  You will have access to everything in the kitchen (which has everything and a Keurig) and common areas.  Dunkin donuts is a short walk away and grocery store is literally minutes away.  Washer and dryer is available to you as well, if needed, for a small added charge.

notes: Ask that guests not wear shoes in the house, no loud parties or music, and no food in the living area. access: You will have your own private bedroom with en suite bathroom.  You will have access to the common areas of the condo as well as the pool, work out room and there is plenty of free parking.
interaction: I am a pretty hands off host that will give you your privacy.  If there is anything you need or have questions, let me know and I can gladly assist you and/or make recommendations.  During your stay, if you have a problem, I'd appreciate if you let me know as soon as possible so I can try to make it better for you and have an enjoyable stay. :)

host_about: I love to travel, get to know the locals, experience different cultures and explore new places.  Interior design is one of my hobbies and I find delight in hosting others and knowing that they had a great stay in my home.

name: The Roost
summary: Conveniently located in the SE area of Columbus, The Roost (supposedly used long ago as a chicken coop) has easy access to I-70 and I-270 making it a perfect spot convenient to the airport, downtown, football games, conferences or any of the many colleges in the area.  Your space is a self-contained building, which offers privacy and cooking facilities. The studio set-up means that only the bathroom is an enclosed space. Ideal space for artist's retreat or girlfriend getaway.
space: The Roost is part of a property that we are slowly renovating. This guesthouse is small and compact, but offers everything for a comfortable stay.  The kitchen has a full-sized stove, microwave, refrigerator and dishwasher, dinnerware and utensils. A small deck with table and chairs is just outside the kitchen, making it a perfect place to enjoy a cup of coffee or glass of wine. The living area is open, with an alcove for a queen sized and single bed.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is quiet with easy access to I-70/I270, the airport, shopping, restaurants and other retail establishments. There is a hiking/biking path right around the corner and also a park across the street. Please note that although we have a Canal Winchester mailing address, we are in SE Columbus and not the village of Canal Winchester. Pickerington is very close to us.
notes: Guests have the entire first floor of the cottage as well as use of the deck to themselves. The loft of the cottage is a private area, off-limits to guests. The fireplace in the cottage is decorative only and no fires are permitted.  Please do note that we have focused our renovation efforts on the buildings on property and that the landscaping has taken a back seat to the home renovations. We also have a well and septic, so ask guests to take this into consideration. The water is filtered and we provide filtered water, but the pressure is definitely not what a city water system provides. We try to be environmentally friendly and have upcycled or recycled as much as we could for the cottage. We do ask that you use the designated bin for recycling and that you don't use the toilet as a garbage disposal. Being on a septic system, The Roost does not have a garbage disposal in the kitchen sink. While we do have internet, the signal can range from weak to excellent. The bathroom has a showe
transit: Car is the best way to get around, but there are city buses within walking distance of The Roost.
access: Parking is on-street.
interaction: We may or may not be available to meet guests, but rest assured that you will have all instructions prior to your stay.

neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is one of the Midwest’s best kept secrets. There is a huge variety of unique shops, bars and restaurants, and art galleries along High Street and a number of annual events that take place year-round. We have a thorough list of recommendations in the house to local bakeries, cafes, and restaurants.  The Short North is made up of several historic neighborhoods; this home is located in Dennison Place on Dennison Ave., between King Ave and 5th Ave. (only 1 block away from High Street).  It’s a quiet street tucked in from High Street and home to an eclectic mix of young professionals, artists, foodies, musicians, families.  There are beautiful, Victorian and Italianate historic homes along Smith Place, Dennison, and Hunter, take a walk if you can- it's a great area! Near the following: • Restaurants- The Table, Basil, Condados, Mikey's Late Night Slice, Paulie Gee's Pizza, Standard Hall...  • Bars & breweries- North High Brewing, Brother Drakes, Seventh Son Bre
notes: • Housekeeping service is per stay, not per night. Additional cleaning visits can be arranged for longer stays if needed.  Visits must be paid in advance and are non-refundable if visits are cancelled. Please inquire when booking. • Pack n Play, high chair, and/or Queen air bed available upon request- please let us know your needs prior so we can prepare all the necessary items. • Noise must be keep to a minimum, this is one of two units.   • There is no handicap access. There are two steps to enter the front of the house.  • Guests with allergies and related medical issues and/or sensitivities- cleanliness is one of our top priorities, however we cannot 100% guarantee that the apartment is free of pet dander, cigarette smoke, air fresheners/cleaning product scents, or any other elements that may trigger a medical problem or sensitivity. Please note we cannot issue refunds due to the reasons above.
transit: We are super close to High Street (one block). You can easily walk to dozens of restaurants and shopping. All other locations can be easily reached a number of ways: Taxis --- Uber -- COTA (Central Ohio Transit Authority) bus --- CoGo (Rental Bikes) --- Car 2 Go (Car Rentals) --- CBUS circulator About the CBUS circulator- It's FREE transportation from the Short North through downtown, all the way to German Village. Bus stops are at many points along High Street.  The closest stop is just a few blocks South from the apartment on 3rd Ave. It's about a $5-10 Uber ride to downtown. PARKING We are in the heart of the city so sometimes parking requires a little planning. We can assist if you have any issues. This apartment does not have off-street parking (unless you have a Mini Cooper or a Smart Car then there is a parking pad next to the garage).  Good news is street parking is available permit-free in front of the house on both sides of Dennison Ave and neighboring streets. It’s usually e
access: You will have access to the entire 1st floor apartment and private backyard. Garage is not included (see Getting Around Section for parking details). Hours of Access: Check-in is 3 p.m.  Checkout is 11 a.m. NOTE: Early check-in and/or late check-out is $35 and must be approved by host *prior* to check-in.
interaction: We are available to guests by email, phone, or text. We know our neighborhood very well (!) and care about our community- let us know when you need something or have questions!
house_rules: Please note that all rules stem from previous experience & are enforced: • Check-in is 3 p.m.  • Checkout is 11 A.M. • Early check-in and/or late check-out is $35 and must be approved by host *prior* to check-in. • Please do not turn off the heat during the winter or air conditioning during summer at any time. Always keep the thermostat set between 65 F/ 18.3 C to 75F/ 24 C.   • Throw away all excessive garbage in any large green exterior trash cans located in the rear alley. Excessive garbage is anything that does not fit into the kitchen and/or bedroom garbage cans. • If the apartment is left trashed (beyond normal use), we will request some or all of the security deposit. In other words, treat this home with respect. • No parties, this is strictly enforced.  You will be asked to leave, no refunds. • All guests must be paying registered guests.  No additional guests allowed without prior written consent of the homeowner.  • Any evidence or smell of cigarette, marijuana, etc. will be
host_about:
We met in Japan, moved to Columbus in 2009, and have been loving it ever since!  We are both experienced travelers (25+ countries on 5 continents between us) & enjoy renovating historic homes and building new homes.

We love being hosts- providing a comfy home and delivering a unique experience when visiting our city. We know quite a lot about Short North entertainment & food establishments- there is so much to do here, feel free to ask!

Our life motto- Live like someone left the gate open!

summary: Modern, contemporary home full of great napping couches and tons of natural light.
space: Enjoy a spacious, airy bedroom and en suite bathroom during your stay in addition to a private living room. There is a full bed in the bedroom as well as a full closet and chest of drawers available for your things. In the living room, there is, arguably, the best nap couch in the world. The TV in the bedroom is connected to an Apple TV, so don't hesitate to binge watch your favorite shows. The attached full bathroom is right off the bedroom with a locking door. This bathroom is completely private and will not be used by the hosts during your stay. There is ample free street parking available in front of the house, but there is also one off street spot if needed.

neighborhood_overview: Our house is situated between The Ohio State University and just at the beginning of the Short North, a very lively neighborhood. The area is very walkable and bikeable, so prepare to explore! Condado's, Brothers Drake Meadery, and Fox in the Snow (and many other bars and restaurants) are all a quick five minute walk from the front door.
notes: We have an adorable golden doodle puppy in our home. He is hypoallergenic and doesn't shed; allergy sufferers, rejoice! His name is Bumble, and he will be so excited to meet a new friend.
transit: There are protected bike lanes that run right in front of our home, so you can easily and safely bike anywhere you need to. The CBUS, a free, downtown circulator bus, picks up one block south of the house and has many stops all the way to German Village on the south end of downtown. The CBUS is a great option for getting anywhere you need for no cost and without the hassle of worrying about parking. Almost any attraction is a minimum fare Uber/Lyft ride away.

summary: Studio apartment in Downtown Columbus with lots of natural light. Big windows, wood floors, one twin bed, one couch. Centrally located next to the Topiary Park and Columbus Public Library.

name: Cozy Townhome Next to OSU and Short North
summary: Whether you've come for a Buckeye game, the OSU Medical Center, a business trip, or coming to see why foodies and beer lovers are talking about Columbus, this apartment puts you in the middle of it all. You can walk to the Short North arts district (0.5 mile), OSU (less than a mile), a full-service supermarket (600 feet), and a COTA bus line with direct service to the convention center, downtown, OSU north campus and beyond (460 feet). It's urban living without the parking headache!
space: The ground floor has a living room, dining table and kitchen. You can hang out in front of the TV on the sofa, or move the dinnerware and work at the dining table. Upstairs, there are two bedrooms (one queen bed, one twin bed) and a shared full bathroom. Downstairs, there is a bedroom (queen bed) with full bathroom. The washer/dryer is next to the downstairs full bathroom. We have tried to decorate the unit so that it can be your home away from home. Hope you like it!

neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is a mixture of OSU students and long-term residents. If the neighbors are having loud fun after 10pm, please let me know and I will contact the relevant landlord and/or police.
notes: The TV is connected to the WiFi and has an HDMI cable for connecting to your mobile device (e.g., for your Netflix). For traditional TV-watchers, there is a rabbit ear antenna... so some channels come in better than others. Just like the old days!
transit: This apartment is 1.5 blocks west of Columbus' main north-south road, High St. This road goes right through downtown, the Short North, past OSU, through Clintonville and Worthington, and is US highway 23 outside of Columbus.  It is a 15-minute walk north to OSU and a 5-minute walk south to the Short North from the apartment. A supermarket is 1.5 blocks away, at the intersection of King and High. The #2 COTA public bus runs up and down High St., connecting with many other COTA routes, making it very easy to get around without a car.  This location is also about four blocks east of Neil Ave., the north-south artery through Victorian Village that connects OSU and downtown. You can take the COTA on Neil Ave., too.

name: Short North Studio Apt. w/Off-street Parking
summary: A 500 sq.ft. studio apartment with 10 foot ceilings and hardwood floors steps from High Street in the Short North. This is a great apartment for access to events at Ohio State, Express Live, Nationwide Arena, the Convention Center, or Goodale Park. When you come home, enjoy relaxing on the front porch. Inside work at a desk by the window, or sprawl on the couch or queen bed and watch TV.
space: Large studio features main room with queen bed, sofa (that converts to double bed), and desk area. A decorative fireplace, 10 foot ceilings, and hardwood floors give this space a great feel. Enjoy high speed internet, and a smart TV that you can watch from the bed or the sofa. Newly upgraded kitchen includes a full sized refrigerator, gas range, microwave, small dishwasher, coffee maker, and wall-mounted two-seat table. Parking is available in a parking lot behind the building. Just let us know how many cars your group will have.

neighborhood_overview: Enjoy Northstar Cafe just around the corner for breakfast, brunch, lunch, or dinner. If you're into tacos, Condado is a fun spot. Mouton is a lovely choice for craft cocktails, and if caffeine is your need One Line Coffee shop is a great choice. The Short North has it all - from great events in Goodale Park and at the Convention Center, to restaurants, bars, coffee shops, galleries, and local shops. This apartment puts you in the heart of the neighborhood.
notes: This studio apartment is on the first floor, and is accessed through a door on the front porch, which is three steps up from street level.
transit: The Short North is conveniently located between Ohio State University and Downtown Columbus. You're within easy walking distance of the Convention Center, Express Live, Nationwide Arena, and Goodale Park (which hosts ComFest and the Pride Festival), plus many of the city's best restaurants, shops, and galleries. A longer walk takes you to Ohio State University to the north or Downtown to the south.  In addition to walking, the free Circulator Bus stops just around the corner and takes you to Downtown and German Village. CoGo bike rental stations dot the neighborhood.  Of course Lyft and Uber are popular options for getting around.  The apartment also features a reserved off-street parking space behind the house for guests who have a car.
access: You'll have the apartment to yourself. The apartment comes with high speed internet access - 100mbps. Each of the four apartments in the building has its own exterior door, so if you encounter other guests it will be in the shared yard or the parking lot.
interaction: We live nearby, and can be available if needed for maintenance issues or other concerns. We may briefly come by to greet you and make sure everything is going well with your stay.
house_rules: As a guest, please be aware that our other guests and tenants live in the downstairs apartments. Be respectful of them by keeping noise levels reasonable, especially from 11pm-7am.
host_about:
I dig psychology, gardening, cycling, being a gym rat, and cooking. I have volunteered at a kids camp every summer since 1999 that teaches critical thinking and a love for nature. 

I have lived in Columbus most of my life and I love it here and I love sharing it with other people. 

My career in the non-profit sector has let me travel all over the country. I love the Bay Area, NYC, Washington state, and the Rockies.

Located just two blocks from High Street and less than a mile from OSU and Downtown, the apartment is walking distance to the Convention Center, the North Market, restaurants, nightlife, shopping and more! Also conveniently located near the FREE C-Bus Circulator for easy access around the city. Large 1bd/1ba luxury suite, w/ private bathroom. space: The small, boutique apartment building is historic and the recent remodel has kept its rich history intact.  Enjoy a beautiful rooftop experience unlike any other in the city, complete with a fireplace, dining tables and awesome views of a popular park.  It’s the perfect place to sip your morning coffee or have a workout session with the sunrise—and in the evening, share a meal under the covered pavilion or an evening cocktail under the stars. You’ll also be walking distance to High Street, the historic North Market and the best food and drink the city has to offer. Relax in solitude or enjoy a refreshing jog in Goodale Park or take part in some of the city’s most famous events, like summer concerts at the charming pavilion.  I'm flexible on check-in and check-out times, depending on bookings by other guests prior or post your visit.

notes: Park right in front of the building using my visitor parking permit or park on Hubbard Street, between Neil and Dennison Avenues (no parking permit required).  Hubbard Street is less than one block away from the building.
transit: Most everything is within walking distance of my apartment and the C-Bus (a free inter-city bus) is less than two blocks from the apartment.
access: You have access to the entire home and rooftop terrace - the only exception is the master suite where I reside.  Please feel free to use the kitchen to store items in the refrigerator or to prepare a meal or two during your visit.
interaction: I will be in and out of the apartment during your stay, but I will be available to answer any questions you may have, so if you need something and I'm away from the apartment, please call or text me. house_rules: * Owner is a clean, quiet, takes pride in his home, and is respectful of his neighbors. Guests should be the same.  * No smoking or drugs on the premises.   * No additional visitors and no additional overnight guests allowed.
host_about:
I am an IT professional and I work for a large global retail organization.  I was born in Elmira, NY and raised in Troy, PA.  I have lived all over the country, including San Francisco for 16 years where I met my partner Michael of 20+ years.  We then moved to Palm Springs for six years and where we both fell in love with the desert. 
 
Michael passed away in December 2015 due to brain cancer, so I moved back to Columbus, OH for work.  I will return to the desert once I retire, but until then, Columbus is home and it's a city that happens to be growing by leaps and bounds and quite an exciting place to call home for the time being.

name: Urban Castle
summary: Enjoy the entire 2nd floor (3500 sf) of this former candy factory!
space: Built in 1904 by The Purity Candy Company, this four story, 14,000 sf building underwent a +$1 million renovation/conversion in 2004. Your host, Mark, purchased the building in 2016 and lives primarily on the 3rd and 4th floors. An architecture firm occupies part of the 1st floor. Easily one of the largest (and certainly most unique) residential properties in Columbus, this Urban Caste features entirely new and modern electrical, HVAC, plumbing, and windows, while maintaining the original wood floors and brick. Two 75 gallon water heaters ensure as much hot water as you need. Each floor has its own HVAC unit with separate Ecobee thermostat. The 2nd floor features original industrial wood floors, tall ceilings, huge windows, and 3500 sf of open loft living space. A massive bedroom and full bath are at the east end of the floor. The bedroom features 2 King beds, which are separated by a large sitting/dressing area. An additional Full bed is situated in an alcove off the main living area.

name: Goodale Park Carriage House - heart of Short North
summary: Welcome to the Goodale Park Carriage House located on beautiful Goodale Park, a 33 acre urban oasis steps away from the Short North. The apartment is a comfortable 2nd floor, one bedroom walk-up with cathedral ceilings and large windows for natural light. The carriage house is conveniently located 2 blocks from High Street with all of its shopping, restaurants, and nightlife, as well as a short walk to the Greater Columbus Convention Center, North Market, and Arena District.
space: The carriage house is a 2nd floor, one bedroom walk-up with a queen bed and sleeper sofa (see floor plan in the pictures). The fully-equipped kitchen has stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher, granite counter tops, ice maker, pots/pans, dishes, and utensils as well as a Keurig coffee machine and washer/dryer.  There is a 43" television with Roku and complimentary Netflix, Amazon Prime Video, and DirecTV Now.  A bluetooth speaker and bottled water are also provided. The fully air conditioned apartment has a lot windows for natural light and ventilation on nice days.  There are also ceiling fans in the living room and bedroom.  The carriage house is 2 blocks from High Street and a short 10 minute walk (1/2 mile) to the Greater Columbus Convention Center and the North Market. The Arena District, Nationwide Arena, and Express Live are a 15 minute walk. The Ohio State University and Downtown Columbus can be reached by car in 5 minutes, and the airport in 10 minutes.

neighborhood_overview: The Italian Village neighborhood is an eclectic combination of new and old homes, and businesses.  Although our neighborhood is safe, it is part of an urban area, so we encourage removing anything valuable from your vehicle and locking doors.  We are an easy walk (0.2 miles/5 minutes) to the Short North Neighborhood, which is Columbus' trendy, hip district full of restaurants, art galleries, shops, and businesses for you to explore!
notes: Non-metered street parking is available around the house, however, it is on a first come first serve basis. Parking is easier and more available earlier in the day. We have two cameras on the property, one on the main level of the home and one outback. Tampering with the security features of the home will result in a cancellation of the rest of your stay without refund.
transit: Walking is the best way around in our area, however the COTA Circulator (free) is available to get to different neighborhoods and districts throughout Columbus. Free ride sharing via Hopper Carts is also available in the Short North and Downtown Columbus area. Several CoGo Bike stations in the area make great use of the bike lanes and quick jumps around town without having to deal with the traffic.
access: Aside from your private room and private attached bath, you may use the main floor shared space and the back yard.

neighborhood_overview: My house is located on a tree-lined street in an established neighborhood near OSU. Besides all of its greenery and unique homes, my street is close enough to campus to walk there but far enough from it to avoid the loud party areas.
notes: During the school year, most of my housemates are international graduate students, post-docs, and professors. In the summer, I open my house to short-term guest, too. Everyone here is respectful of others, quiet, and friendly. This is a nice place to relax or study on your own or connect with others who may have some of the same queries or interests that brought you to Columbus.
transit: The High Street bus (main line) is a 3 minute walk from my house, campus is 10 minutes, and two grocery stores are 15 minutes. Two CVS pharmacies and a variety of American, organic, and ethnic food restaurants are in-between. If you take the airport shuttle or arrive by bus, you'll be downtown on or near High Street. Simply take a High Street bus heading north of campus, and get off at my street. From there, it's a three minute walk as noted above.

interaction: I am from Columbus and an OSU alum, so happy to help out with any questions you may have about my city and school.
host_about: I am an OSU alum (historian) who continues to enjoy the campus area while having easy access to downtown and Clintonville. I have lived and taught abroad (Europe, Africa, and Asia) for many years. I have increasingly limited familiarity with French and German though enjoy conversing in both when I have the chance. I have a big house with housemates, mostly international graduate students, post-docs, and professors. Lastly, I love Columbus!

notes: If you smoke do it outside at least 20 feet away from the building, not on the front porch. We do have security camera that is outside the front door. Also, if you have groups of over 8 we have additional cleaning fee of $40. Thanks!

Lastly, call or text me when leaving when checking out so I know when our cleaner can go in and if you need to stay past check of time of 11 AM just let me know in advance and we should be able make it work.
host_about: Hello Airbnb friends! I am outgoing try anything once type of person. Love to travel and meet new people and I am frequently out of town for work, travel and skydiving. Happy traveling and happy to answer any questions about the Columbus area if you stay or not. Cheers!

name: The White Squirrel Inn
summary: Welcome to the White Squirrel Inn — so named because of a white squirrel that likes to frequent our neighborhood! Nestled in the heart of Victorian Village in Columbus, Ohio, this turn-of-the-century house exudes warmth and charm from the moment you step onto the covered porch. Within walking distance of the Short North, Downtown and The Ohio State University, this highly sought after location has something for everyone. And there are 2 off-street parking spaces.
space: We are kid-friendly and pet-friendly, but we do charge an extra $50 cleaning fee for four-legged guests. Please notify us when booking whether you are bringing an animal. There are 3 bedrooms — two with queen beds, and one with a futon. There are 1.5 baths, with a clawfoot tub/shower upstairs. There is a fenced-in backyard with a picnic table, and there are covered porches in the front and back. Smoking is allowed only on the porches and in the backyard. Parties are okay in the back yard, but please no indoor parties.

neighborhood_overview: I am located in a diverse, URBAN NEIGHBORHOOD built in the mid 1800's. In its day, it was the about the best real estate you could buy and represented the optimism of a growing city. For old house aficionados, I'm surrounded by interesting architecture, some outstanding restorations, and lots of potential . Olde Towne East/King Lincoln is one of the city’s largest historic neighborhoods, over 50 architectural styles can be found here. The diversity of the neighborhood and its many charms include beautiful homes, impressive churches, great restaurants , Central location, nearby Franklin Park Conservatory and The Columbus Art Museum makes this neighborhood extra special , I know I'm a little bias :-)
notes: This is a 3rd floor level apartment which means there are stairs to negotiate. There is a sturdy handrail, but for some potential guests who need handicap accessibility, this unit may not be appropriate.
transit: The apt. is located 2 minutes from the interstate. 15 min. from the airport. COGo Bike sharing is located in the neighborhood for bike rentals. Bus stop is less than 100 ft. from the apt. $6.00 Uber ride downtown. $8-15 to and from the airport.

interaction: Generally, I am in and out, much of the time but available by phone. If something out of the ordinary occurs, I'll let you know. I want your stay in Columbus to be pleasant. name: Perfect Short North Location - Steps to High St!
summary: Our historic brick cottage is in the absolute BEST location in Columbus. Built in the 1880's it is a 2 bedroom, 1 bath located just steps off High Street. Our apartment has 7 beds, an updated kitchen and bathroom, and a brand new washer/dryer. It scores a 92 on WalkScore = Walkers Paradise! You are steps from all of the action. Less than a mile south from OSU Campus, less than a mile from the Columbus Convention Center, and steps from all of the best bars and restaurants Columbus has to offer!
space: Our place is completely updated and all furnishings are brand new! There are brand new memory foam mattresses and all new furniture throughout the place. The place has 2 large bedrooms and 1 bathroom. The master bedroom has two queen beds. The second bedroom on the second floor has a queen bed ,twin bed, and air mattress. The living room has a sleeper sofa as well as an air mattress. There is 1 full bath as washer/dryer located on the first floor of the place. The kitchen appliances, washer/dryer, and bathroom are all new. There is free parking on the grass driveway of the house and a gravel drive behind the house. This is a HUGE perk due to parking in the Short North often being limited.

neighborhood_overview: Our place is located in the Short North/ Italian Village neighborhood. Italian Village offers a plethora of breweries, coffee shops, and restaurants tucked within the neighborhood borders. The Short North is a mile of the best art galleries, restaurants, nightlife, pubs, and shops! You also are less than 1 mile to OSU campus, the convention center, and Nationwide Arena!
transit: There is public transit (COTA) all up and down high street that is easily accessible from our place. You can walk to everything on high street, take a quick Uber, or request a Hopper cart, which is a free golf cart ride anywhere in the Short North! There is free parking on the grass driveway of the house for 2-3 cars. This is a HUGE perk due to parking in the Short North often being limited.
access: You have the whole place!
interaction: I am born and raised in Columbus so I am more than happy to give recommendations for anything that interests you! With that being said, you will have all the privacy you need to enjoy the trip.
host_about: I am from Columbus, Ohio. I went to college at Ohio State where I played football and studied finance. I then moved to Chicago for a real estate finance position. After four years there, I left that position and now run my own businesses. I love traveling, attending concerts and sporting events, skiing, trying new restaurants, grabbing beers with friends, cooking, juicing, yoga, high intensity training, and running.

summary: Contemporary newer home located in the heart of the Italian Village!  Less than 5 minunte walk to all of the many restaurants, breweries, and shops located in the Short North and Italian Village. Less than 10 minute drive to OSU campus.  Spacious, quiet, and modern home. Beautifully landscaped backyard with fire pit, water feature and grill. Electronic keypad entry to the home for your convenience. Non-metered parking is available on the street surrounding the house.
space: The main level of the home is situated above the street, so there are some stairs to enter the home.  Once in the home, the main level has an open space with kitchen, living room, and half bath.  Upstairs you will find two of the three bedrooms.  The master bedroom has a king sized sleigh bed fitted with organic cotton sheets and a luxurious bathroom with walk-in shower and marble vanity.  The secondary upstairs bedroom has a queen sized bed fitted with soft, organic cotton sheets and a bathroom with jetted tub and granite vanity. The lower level of the home has a living area, laundry room, as well as the third bedroom.  The bedroom has a queen sized sleigh bed fitted with soft, organic cotton sheets and attached bath.  The lower level room also has a small fridge and keurig coffee maker.  All rooms are fitted with large, plush cotton towels and bathroom amenities. The backyard features a firepit with seating, water feature and built-in grill and refrigerator.

neighborhood_overview: The Italian Village neighborhood is an eclectic combination of new and old homes, and businesses. We are an easy, short walk to the Short North Arts District, which is Columbus' trendy, hip district full of restaurants, art galleries, shops, and businesses for you to explore! You will find almost anything you need within walking distance of the home.
notes: Free street parking is available around the house, however, it is on a first come first serve basis. Parking is usually available earlier in the day. Although our neighborhood is safe, it is part of an urban area, so we encourage removing anything valuable from your vehicle and locking doors. If you are an Amazon Prime member, Amazon Prime Now is available at the house and will deliver: groceries, food, cold beer, chilled and non-chilled wines. We have two cameras on the property, one on the main level in a common area of the home and one outback.  Tampering with the security features of the home will result in a cancellation of the rest of your stay without refund.
transit: Walking is the best way around in our area, however the CBUS Circulator (free) is available to get to different neighborhoods and districts throughout Columbus. Free ride sharing via Hopper Carts is also available in the Short North and Downtown Columbus area. Several CoGo Bike stations in the area make great use of the bike lanes and quick jumps around town without having to deal with the traffic.
interaction: When staying in our home, we will be close by for help and are always available by phone or email. We respond quickly to any guests' needs.

neighborhood_overview: We love living here - our street is full of friendly neighbors and is a quiet side street that feels almost like a small town. However, it's in the heart of Columbus near Ohio State campus and plenty of things to do and good food to eat. A ten minute walk would get you to a section of North High Street with ample restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Just south of that High street runs through the heart of Ohio State campus with more dining, shopping, bars, a great local movie theater and more. You can get to the Short North Arts district from our house in ten minutes driving and check out the art galleries, shopping, finer-dining and drinking options it provides and more. A fifteen minute drive would get you to downtown, the Arena District or to historic German Village. Most places of interest can also be accessed by a bus stop that is a five minute walk from our house, but parking is pretty easy throughout the city. There are also a number of great parks nearby. Mapfre Stadium (home of
notes: As stated, the bed is a lofted double with a ladder for access. If this is a concern we would be glad to take the mattress off of the loft and put it on the floor for your stay, or bring in the air mattress. If more than two guests are staying, the only way to accommodate everyone is to have the air mattress on the floor as well as the lofted bed, so it would become necessary for someone to sleep in the loft at that point, so just be aware and feel free to ask what we can do to accommodate you if you aren't comfortable climbing into a loft to sleep! We also do have a dog - Luca - who is very friendly, but sometimes a bit jumpy. He'll be kept out of the guest room but otherwise has the run of the house, so be aware of that when booking. He loves everybody and would be delighted to have you stay.  Check in flexible - can do early, particularly if you're looking to come for an OSU game day.
transit: Columbus is most easily accessible by car. Parking isn't much of a problem most places you would want to go (sometimes for a fee, or meters that take card, but many places have free parking) and traffic generally isn't that bad. The local bus system is ok, but can be fairly slow and doesn't cover a ton of the city. If you wanted to go downtown, Short North, the arena district, or german village there is a bus route that is pretty convenient from our house for $2 one-way if you don't mind a little bit of walking in addition to the ride. Columbus is super bike friendly and if you want to bring bikes we'd be glad to accommodate finding a safe place for them during your stay. Uber is pretty good in Columbus, and there is a bike-docking rental program that covers the downtown/short-north/arena-district area pretty thoroughly but the nearest station to our house is probably a couple miles away.
access: Private: bedroom. Shared: bathroom, kitchen, living room, office, screened-in porch, yard, basement with laundry.
interaction: Whatever you like! If we're in town during your stay we'll be glad to chat with guests, offer advice on restaurants and other local activities/attractions, and help in any way possible. We'll also leave you to your own devices as desired.
