host_about:
10 years honorably discharged US Navy Vet. Born in Jamaica, grew up and attended high school in South Florida. Attended and graduated college with degree in Psychology and Business. Currently working in the Information Technology Field. I am very neat, clean and organized. Don't like drama and confrontation. Like the simple life.

I was fortunate to travel to more that 25 countries and numerous international cities. My favorite countries to visit were Singapore, Hong Kong, Bermuda, Dubai and Canes. Yes, there was the most scary countries I visited were Haifa Israel, Manama Bahrain, Alexandra Egypt and Kingston Jamaica. Most memorable country I lived in was Manama Bahrain. 

There are not many things I don't like with the exception of lizards. Most noted likes are electronic gadgets, riding motor cycles, watching track and field, playing soccer and various sports, cooking authentic Caribbean cuisines and learning about other cultures.

Let me see, 5 things I can't (well choose not to) live with out... Ummmm, 1. Amazon Alexa, yes she is like my living companion. 2. Electronic gadgets - have to have the man toys. 3. The internet - would be lost without being connected to the rest of the world. 4. Music and 5. Good food.

I love the quiet times to sit back and watch a tear jerker movie and at the same time can appreciate war, drama and military movies.

I am very open minded and love to welcome guest of all diversity. But if I had to chose the ideal guest, it would be... Someone honest, neat, clean, open minded about life, food, music of other cultures. Quiet but not shy to having intellectually stimulating conversations. Someone that can appreciate quiet times, wine, jazz and movies. I don't care too much for loud and rambunctious character.

A simple motto I live by... What you do for yourself will die with you, the good you do for others, the positive impact you make on another person's life will live long after you are gone.

neighborhood_overview: Sometimes referred to as the 4th and Main district or the Gallery District, our neighborhood is home to bars, restaurants, salons, galleries and green spaces.  Dine at Hadley's for the best burger in the city or check out Mikey's Late Night Slice for the best New York style pizza Columbus has to offer!  Pamper yourself across the street at Square One, an Aveda Salon before you head out to an upscale dinner at Side Bar.  Whatever you need, its right here!
notes: Our listing is located on one of the major thoroughfares in the city.  There is a direct route to OSU Campus, Columbus School of Art and Design and Columbus Community College.  We are a short drive from Otterbein and Ohio Dominican University.

neighborhood_overview: Old North Columbus is a neighborhood located just north of the Ohio State University in Columbus, Ohio. It was founded in 1847 where, at the time, it was a stand-alone city out of the confines of Columbus until it was incorporated into the City of Columbus in 1871. In its early years the city was a popular stagecoach stop with people traveling from Worthington to Columbus. Today Old North Columbus is popular for its local music and its unique "untouched architecture" which is reminiscent of its old roots.

Also note that we cannot issue refunds due to the reasons above.

neighborhood_overview: The best part about our hideaway is the Franklin Park Conservatory right across  the street, as well as the park. A few blocks east on Broad, you'll find Wolfe Park and tennis courts. Panera Bread is down the street about a mile. Spend an afternoon or evening on Main Street in Bexley, home of Capital University. Take in a movie at the Drexel Theater, visit Guiseppe's Italian Bistro, Aab India, Cafe Instanbul, Zen Cha Tea Salon, or any number of ice cream and pizza parlors. The Grain and Grape has an excellent choice of wines and beers, and there are several nail salons and banks. Pick up a few groceries at Kroger or Giant Eagle (which also boasts a restaurant at the top called The Table).
notes: There are 2 parking spots for this condo, and you must park only in those spots. They are the 2 spots on the very left side lane of the parking lot in back, when looking towards Broad Street from the alley.
transit: Heading west on Broad Street, you're within 8 minutes of downtown Columbus. The COTA bus picks you up steps from the front door and lets you off across the street. A bus transfer will take you to the Short North, The Ohio State University and Nationwide Children's Hospital. An Uber or Lyft ride is inexpensive to all points, including the airport. You'll find shopping and dining in the Short North and Easton Towne Center. You won't be bored in our beautiful city.
access: Guests will be able to access the entire house except the basement. There is also a common space in the front main courtyard that is used by all of the neighbors, but is open for use by our guests as well. There is a BBQ grill, and some chairs there for use as well.

neighborhood_overview: Old Town East is one of the oldest neighborhoods in the city. The redevelopment of the neighborhood began about two decades ago and my street has been transformed over the last few years as more and more houses have been renovated and updated. There is are also three new houses under construction on block and the blocks immediately to the east and west. The neighborhood is quiet and I know all of my neighbors. They are interesting, diverse, and super-friendly people.  Parts of the neighborhood are still transitioning and this is clear on a couple of streets that most GPS mapping programs will take you down when you exit I-70 or I-71. The area around my home is safe and well maintained. I encourage visitors to use the Broad Street Exit near downtown as an alternative - it won't add any time on to your trip. As you head east down Broad Street you'll see some amazingly restored historic houses as well as Franklin Park, which is a beautiful and perfect for running, walking, and exploring.
notes: Price listed is for up to 2 guests. There is and a 25.00 charge for a 3rd guest, who can sleep on the couch. No more than 3 guests at once.
transit: Access to COTA, the city's bus system, is 2 blocks away. Access to I-70 and I-71 is a 1/2 mile away.
access: I live here and guests have complete access to the house with the exception of the owner's bedroom. This includes access and use of the kitchen, dining room, living room, laundry area, and outdoor spaces. I am mostly able to meet my guests personally and would rather work this way. However, I can leave you a key and send you instructions for entry and information about the room and the house if you let me know ahead what time you are arriving.
interaction: I am available for any questions or concerns via email, text, phone, or in person. I will not always be present when there are guests. This is especially true on weekends, but you can reach out to me anytime. I can be as involved or uninvolved as you would like during your stay. It's completely up to you.
house_rules: 1. Check-in is 3:00 to 10:00pm and checkout is at 11:00am. These times can be flexible; ask me if you need to make adjustments.  2.. Please do not put anything other than toilet paper into the toilet.  3. Please do not smoke in the house. A $300 fee will be charged if you smoke in the house. You can smoke outside on the porch. 4. I live in the house but will not always be present when there are guests. Generally speaking, quiet time starts at 11:00pm during the week and 12:00am on the weekend.  5. Clean up after yourself after using the common areas. Place dirty dishes in the dishwasher after rinsing them.  6. The second floor is warmer than the first. You can adjust the thermostat to make yourself comfortable. The thermostat is on the outside wall of the living room on the first floor. Use the up and down arrows to adjust the temperature. Please leave the "fan" switch on "auto."

Historical fiction is my favorite read.

neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village, which runs along Neil Avenue south of The Ohio State University and northwest of downtown Columbus, is one of central Ohio’s cores of fine residential architecture. The area is known for its Victorian houses, which were built when a streetcar line first ran along Neil Avenue around 1900.  Victorian Village is directly west of the well known Short North area of Columbus. Some of the most celebrated spots to eat and drink in Columbus are in the Short North Arts District, which is gaining recognition as a dining destination. This portion of High Street is filled with boutiques, art galleries, coffee houses, restaurants, and bars.
notes: We have a strict no party policy. While our house is able to host large groups, we expect you to treat this home respectfully and obey all house rules. Thank you in advance!
transit: There is free street parking located on streets in the neighborhood. We also have one residential parking pass that you are able to use to park right near the house. High Street is 1/2 mile walk or a very quick Uber. Most everything in Columbus is a very quick drive/Uber from our house.

interaction: We are hands-off hosts but are available as needed!

I love traveling, attending concerts and sporting events, skiing, trying new restaurants, grabbing beers with friends, cooking, juicing, yoga, high intensity training, and running.

neighborhood_overview: What I love about my neighborhood is that it has quiet mature neighbors. The property is on a cul-de-sac and has very little traffic. An interesting note: if you are a bird observer, you'll enjoy a variety of birds such as Blue Jays and Cardinals living in the neighborhood. Make sure to check out my Guidebook for activities, entertainment and restaurants - it's a reference of all my favorite places in Columbus. I'm a member of a Pizzeria meetup - My favorite mom & pop pizzerias are listed.
notes: A custom made key code will be generated for the keyless entry lock upon your successful booking. There are two twin size mattresses available for your use, located in the utility room, simply pull them out and place in the family room. Let me know if you plan to use either the couches/mattresses and I will set out the bed linen. I use Tide detergent to wash the bed linen/body pillow. I use a regular fabric softener. If you prefer no fabric softener, please provide this information in your correspondence. I use an ink free/fragrance free toilet paper. For longer stay reservations above 4 days: I offer cleaning services at an additional $20 per cleaning visit. This includes laundering bed linens/towels, vacuuming, light dusting and washing the dishes. Number of Guests: I ask that all my guests be honest and accurate in the number of guests occupying my home. My property is priced competitively and fairly.
transit: The property is ideally located four blocks to the nearest bus stop and it is also five minutes to either highways 270 or 315.
access: Guests will have access to community areas of the home such as the dining room, fully stocked kitchen, family room, laundry room and bathrooms. Coffee/tea/bedside chocolates are provided complimentary, however, I do ask you to reimburse me with grocery money for any wine, beer, food or snacks from the kitchen that you consume. Guests will also have access to the fenced backyard and patio. Feel free to use the gas grill - simply clean it after you are done using it. Guests can park their cars either in the driveway or in the street - whichever they prefer. For reservations with 3-6 guests, There are two twin size mattresses available for your use, located in the utility room, simply pull them out and place in the adjacent family room. Let me know if you plan to use the mattresses and I will set out the bed linen. Regarding the use of my laundry resources, I ask for $5 PER LOAD of laundry to compensate for consumption.
interaction: Since guests dictate how much or how little they would like to interact with me, if certain guests would like to be social and include me that is fine and for those guests who want to be independent and do their own thing that is also fine as well.
house_rules: #NAME?
host_about:
Howdy! I’m Jake. I’m originally from New York, and while I miss my friends and family back home (not to mention the beach!), I absolutely love my mid-west home here in Columbus, Ohio!
By day I’m a real estate investor and by night I’m a social butterfly with my friends. I'm also an Airbnb cohost where I mentor aspiring local hosts. I earned my Superhost status because I have high standards for value, cleanliness, and communication.
I enjoy travelling and creating new experiences. My favorite country is Guatemala. The people, the food and the historical sites are breathtaking. My favorite city is Chicago. Through these travels and coupled with my 12 years landlording, I’ve been fortunate to learn what makes a great host: a great home, with a friendly host, in an awesome neighborhood, and the ability to do the things you love! I try to ensure that each and every guest I host walks away with all of that and hopefully more.
My life motto is, well, really my grandmother’s advice, “Jakey, live with NO REGRETS” (I can hear her thick NYer accent now). Sometimes I guess we just need a little reminder of that… And so, I invite you to travel more and see the big, beautiful world we live in.

transit: The property is ideally located four blocks to the nearest bus stop and it is also five minutes to either highways 270 or 315.
access: Guests will have access to community areas of the home such as the dining room, fully stocked kitchen, family room, laundry room and bathrooms. Coffee/tea/bedside chocolates are provided complimentary, however, I do ask you to reimburse me with grocery money for any wine, beer, food/snacks from the kitchen  and laundry services that you consume. Guests will also have access to the fenced backyard and patio. Feel free to use the gas grill - simply clean it after you are done using it. Guests can park their cars either in the driveway or in the street - whichever they prefer. Regarding the use of my laundry resources, I ask for $5 PER LOAD of laundry to compensate for consumption.
interaction: Since guests dictate how much or how little they would like to interact with me, if certain guests would like to be social and include me that is fine and for those guests who want to be independent and do their own thing that is also fine as well.
house_rules: Welcome to my comfy home! There are some house rules: you may not smoke on the property. This is a smoke-free property. Also, please remove your shoes at the door as I just had the carpets shampooed. Feel free to help yourself to the wine, beer, snack and food items in the kitchen WITH THE UNDERSTANDING THAT YOU SHALL LEAVE GROCERY MONEY ON THE COUNTER for me to replace the items that you enjoyed. Please ONLY eat in the dining and/or kitchen areas. Please DO NOT eat in the carpeted areas - this includes bedrooms and the downstairs family room. Feel free to use the gas grill located on the back patio. Simply clean it after you are finished using it. Lastly, this is not a house to host a party. I would suggest using another venue to host your party.
host_about:
Howdy! I’m Jake. I’m originally from New York, and while I miss my friends and family back home (not to mention the beach!), I absolutely love my mid-west home here in Columbus, Ohio!
By day I’m a real estate investor and by night I’m a social butterfly with my friends. I'm also an Airbnb cohost where I mentor aspiring local hosts. I earned my Superhost status because I have high standards for value, cleanliness, and communication.
I enjoy travelling and creating new experiences. My favorite country is Guatemala. The people, the food and the historical sites are breathtaking. My favorite city is Chicago. Through these travels and coupled with my 12 years landlording, I’ve been fortunate to learn what makes a great host: a great home, with a friendly host, in an awesome neighborhood, and the ability to do the things you love! I try to ensure that each and every guest I host walks away with all of that and hopefully more.
My life motto is, well, really my grandmother’s advice, “Jakey, live with NO REGRETS” (I can hear her thick NYer accent now). Sometimes I guess we just need a little reminder of that… And so, I invite you to travel more and see the big, beautiful world we live in.

summary: Columbus, Ohio is quickly emerging as one of the country's artistic and creative hubs. Columbus plays an important role as Ohio's capital city, as well as the home of The Ohio State University Buckeyes. This exciting Midwestern destination offers a lot to visitors in the way of arts, culture, sports, and nightlife!
space: This spectacular 2-bedroom, 1.5-bathroom cottage is actually a renovated carriage house, built in 1870. It has been meticulously restored in the last year to comfortably accommodate 4 guests and feels more like a trendy loft than a carriage house! There is even a comfortable blow-up mattress available by request, which brings the guest occupancy up to 6. A 60-inch TV with full surround sound gives you a front row seat to your favorite sporting event or movie screening. A hayloft area features 20-foot ceilings and a full kitchen with stainless appliances and countertops, as well as a full bar for entertaining. The master bedroom also boasts a fireplace, which is perfect for those chilly Columbus winters.

A "Gallery Hop" takes place on the first Saturday of every month on the main strip only 50 yards from the home, where local art galleries come together to showcase the work of local and regional artists. The property is also a short drive from The Ohio State University's campus and the famed Ohio Stadium, where the Buckeyes play. The historic Ohio Theater hosts full-scale Broadway productions and is sure to please everyone in your group, whether you go for a play, concert, or any other performance. Museums, parks, gardens, and more all contribute to the beauty and culture of Columbus. When you book this wonderful property for your next trip to Columbus, you'll love having the best of the city practically right at your doorstep!

neighborhood_overview: The Short North Arts District is a pioneer in urban revitalization.  The Short North Arts District is the most vibrant spot in the City of Columbus and is home to over 300 exciting businesses, the majority of which are locally owned or headquartered. It has received numerous national accolades, is considered a model for urban revitalization, and is known as the art and soul of Columbus. Directly east of High Street is Italian Village. New energy is transforming this spot into a nightlife hub. Little Rock hosts live music, Seventh Son Brewing uses its creative energy to craft category-busting beers, and Hoof Hearted Brewing combines heavy-hitting brews with a thoroughly mod taproom. In the daylight hours, check out The Market Italian Village for upscale picnic supplies and delicious pizzas, or the sunlight-drenched Fox in the Snow Cafe for an outstanding latte

name: Art at 185 German Village
summary: Welcome to Art at 185, our studio apartment in the heart of German Village. This space has been created for guests to enjoy not only a stay in Historic German Village but also a display of local art, currently featuring works from Open Door Art Gallery, located in Grandview. (URL HIDDEN)  Once a working art studio has now been turned into a cozy studio apartment walking distance from the fabulous restaurants in German Village, downtown Columbus and Children's Hospital.
space: Art at 185 is bigger than it looks and is quite spacious. Currently the studio showcases original art created by Columbus artists. Founded in 2007, Open Door Art Studio empowers artists with disabilities to work with professional creative mentors in an environment of mutual respect and creative freedom. I also have several of my father’s hand crafted birdhouses for sale. As a former working art studio, we did not want to lose sight of how this space was originally intended and are fortunate Open Door has agreed to use our space as a gallery.

neighborhood_overview: ABOUT GERMAN VILLAGE You are in one of the best parts of Columbus, Ohio—beautiful and historic German Village. There is so much to see and do and most of the area is pedestrian friendly. We have our favorite eateries including Barcelona, Sycamore Café, Brown Bag Deli, Pistachio Vera, Taco Tuesday at The Kitchen, Lindey’s, Katzinger’s, G Michaels, Harvest….. Check out German Village Society for details.  For fitness options, there is a Snap Fitness facility on Third Ave and Schiller Rec Center in the Park (both are fee-based). Laundromat is available a block away.
notes: *The apt is on the second floor accessible by one flight of stairs. Please note there is no elevator. **Allergy alert: while we don't allow guest's pets we sometimes bring our dog when we clean the apt. ***Please note this a one bedroom apt with a full bed. Second bed is a queen sleeper sofa in the LR. (limited privacy as LR is a pass through room from bedroom to kitchen/bath).
transit: Schiller Park is just a block south. Programming includes Actors’ Theatre Shakespeare in the Park Thursdays-Sundays throughout the summer.  The closest rental bike (CoGo) station is by the Giant Eagle grocery store a block east of the apt (corner of Whittier and Jaeger). CoGo allows you to rent bikes and return to either this or any CoGo station in the city.  There is a free bus service—COTA’s Cbus that offers continuous service between German Village, Brewery District and the Short North.

neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village, which runs along Neil Avenue south of The Ohio State University and northwest of downtown Columbus, is one of central Ohio’s cores of fine residential architecture. The area is known for its Victorian houses, which were built when a streetcar line first ran along Neil Avenue around 1900. Victorian Village is directly west of the well known Short North area of Columbus. Some of the most celebrated spots to eat and drink in Columbus are in the Short North Arts District, which is gaining recognition as a dining destination. This portion of High Street is filled with boutiques, art galleries, coffee houses, restaurants, and bars.
notes: We have a strict no party policy. While our house is able to host large groups, we expect you to treat this home respectfully and obey all house rules. Thank you in advance!
transit: There is free street parking located on streets in the neighborhood. We also have one residential parking pass that you are able to use to park right near the house. High Street is 1/2 mile walk or a very quick Uber. Most everything in Columbus is a very quick drive/Uber from our house.
access: You will have access to the entire place!
interaction: We are hands-off hosts but are available as needed!

After four years there, I left that position and now run my own businesses. I love traveling, attending concerts and sporting events, skiing, trying new restaurants, grabbing beers with friends, cooking, juicing, yoga, high intensity training, and running.

host_about:
During college, I spent two years on the road as a musician, stayed at hostels and couchsurfed all around the US and Europe. Through my travels, I founded a few businesses and non-profits and launched them in Columbus. Now I’m a Senior Consultant at Kalypso. I travel internationally for technology projects, speak at conferences on music industry, and consult smart cities on technology and cultural initiatives.

Through AirBnB, I enjoyed creating a the ideal setup that I would want to have for myself in my hometown, Columbus, Ohio. It's better than any hotel room. It's a place where travelers and business professionals can stay in comfort, with updated technology, and fresh amenities at all times. It's in the heart of downtown, near all of the excitement of concerts, theaters, restaurants, and conferences that I would want to be at as a traveler, but still quiet and peaceful at night.

I love traveling, attending concerts and sporting events, skiing, trying new restaurants, grabbing beers with friends, cooking, juicing, yoga, high intensity training, and running.

notes: I have lived here for more than three years. Aside from the minor hum of cars driving by, it is a very quiet and safe space.
transit: Highway access to 71 North and 70 West is about two minutes down the street. Whether catching a bus out front, using the riverfront bikeway that passes around the corner, or taking an Uber, all of Columbus is just minutes away. There are also Car2Go options across the street. The heart of downtown is 1.6 miles away, and the Short North is 2.5 miles away. Both areas are centered on the same street the house is located on: High Street.
access: Two private offices, two rooms upstairs, and the basement are to remain private. Guests are encouraged to enjoy the rest of the home.
interaction: I'm open to socializing with guests, or giving them their space. I do tend to be busy and on the go often. Contacting me via text message is the best way to get a very quick response.
house_rules: Smoking is not allowed in the home. If you smoke outside, please dispose of things in a safe manner. You are welcome to use the kitchen, but please clean up after yourself and load the dishwasher. You are welcome to come and go as you wish, but please just be mindful of possible business activity on the first floor during the day. It is rather infrequent, and there should not be any issues with noise disturbing you. You should not expect any business activities ever after 5pm.
host_about: I'm a guy from the Midwestern U.S. who was lucky enough to first move to Europe at 18. That dramatically changed my view of the world, and my place in it. Four years living in Europe, and 31 countries later, one of my greatest joys in life is discovering new places, and revisiting ones I love. I am a small business owner in healthcare for seniors, and I split my time between Ohio and NYC.

neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village, which runs along Neil Avenue south of The Ohio State University and northwest of downtown Columbus, is one of central Ohio’s cores of fine residential architecture. The area is known for its Victorian houses, which were built when a streetcar line first ran along Neil Avenue around 1900. Victorian Village is directly west of the well known Short North area of Columbus. Some of the most celebrated spots to eat and drink in Columbus are in the Short North Arts District, which is gaining recognition as a dining destination. This portion of High Street is filled with boutiques, art galleries, coffee houses, restaurants, and bars.

Easy access to riverfront biking and jogging path.

name: German Village & Shumacher Place- Cozy Bungalow
summary: Cozy bungalow style house with modern finishes and private yard. Very private with a large front yard and everything you need to feel at home. This Is in the Historical Schumacher and German Village area within walking distance from Children's Hospital, Downtown and many popular shops and restaurants.
space: This has a queen size bed in the larger room and a queen and desk in the smaller room that will sleep two. The living room has an Ikea sofa bed that's between a full and Queen and can sleep 2. There is also a queen size air mattress available. Living room also has electric fireplace and smart Wi-Fi TV and streaming services from Spectrum, Netflix. Spectrum Tv also includes 4 premium channels. Well equipped Galley kitchen with full size appliances. I don't cook but if you like too and want to make sure it has what you need just message me and I will do my best to accommodate any requests. There is a Keurig single brew coffee maker and complimentary coffee and bottled water as well. You will have this whole main floor to yourself. I have a separate apartment in the lower level/basement that is sound proof for privacy. I know you will enjoy!

name: Family friendly, clean, restful stay
summary: Clean and peaceful stay on the south side of Columbus. Our place is a 10 minute drive to downtown, a 5 minute walk to the bus station on South Parsons Ave. (Bus line #8 will take you downtown in 15 minutes), a 5 minute drive to Scioto Downs raceway, and a 2 minute drive to the I-270 outerbelt. It takes about 15-20 minutes to get to or from Columbus John Glenn International Airport. We have free high-speed internet and a washer and a dryer for a small fee.
space: Our place isn't in downtown, but it is close and easily-accessible to all the major attractions of Columbus. Further, our proximity to the highway allows you to travel around the central Ohio area rather easily. We live in a peaceful and safe neighborhood on the south side conveniently (2-5 minutes) to shopping and restaurants. Within walking distance is a nice recreation center and park which has a half mile track. Our three bedroom bi-level house is home to my wife, son, and I as well as one roommate. As our AirBnB guest, you are welcome to use the upstairs full bathroom. Your guest bedroom has a full-sized bed, desk, lamp, and closet space to hang or put your folded clothes or suitcase.  We are always happy to give rides if one needs one (work schedules permitting) and would love to welcome our guests with a warm delicious meal. neighborhood_overview: This residence is located in Southern Orchards part of Columbus, right next to German Village. It is also few blocks from Nationwide Children's Hospital. There is a variety of local restaurants such as Barcelona, Lindey's, The Sycamore, The Crest, Skillet, The Brown Bag Deli, Scrambler Marie's, Panera and Tim Horton's. Or get meals delivered through Grub Hub or an awesome new delivery service called Clustertruck! Please note that while we are a couple blocks from German Village and half a million dollar homes, this is an up-and-coming neighborhood. It is in the process of being revitalized, but that type of work takes years. Nationwide Children's Hospital has improved it tremendously in the time we have been there, but is still a little rough around the edges. There are neighbors that are holding out for higher property offers, leaving their buildings boarded in the meantime.
notes: Master bedroom : 1 queen bed 2nd bedroom: 1 bunk bed (sleeps one person on the top &  one on the bottom) Also futon converts to bed in tv room.
transit: There is Uber/Lyft, taxis and also the COTA bus line a block away.

name: Newly renovated duplex minutes from Downtown
summary: I'm honored you chose my property. This is my second Airbnb property. During your stay, you'll enjoy a spacious 900 square feet apartment, close to restaurants, family-friendly activities, and a 5 minute drive downtown. You’ll love the location, comfy living, in an up and coming neighborhood that is being gentrified by the local gov't. As last minute cancellations are costly - My place is perfect for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers who are committed to their booking dates.
space: As the real estate saying goes, location location location. The newly renovated property is ideally located 5 minutes from COSI, Downtown Columbus and only a 8 minute drive to the Convention Center. Minutes from restaurants, entertainment and the business sectors. Simply take either Town or Broad Street East for a quick 5 minute ride to downtown Columbus. Situated in Franklinton, the property enjoys a quiet, mature neighborhood. The property is a two story side by side twin double (aka duplex). The adjacent unit is occupied by a tenant. Since the upstairs is being renovated, guests may use the middle room upstairs and have full access downstairs for their lodging needs. When you enter the property you will be in the living room. Next, you'll enter the dining room which is temporarily converted into a bedroom (during the finishing stage of the upstairs renovation) and then into the kitchen. The newly renovated bathroom is adjacent to the kitchen. Access the backyard thru the kitchen. In

neighborhood_overview: What I love about the neighborhood is that it has quiet mature neighbors and it's proximity to the downtown area. Franklinton is an old community. The local city and state government are spending millions gentrifying this neighborhood. It is 5 minutes from Downtown/Arena District. (Nationwide Arena, Express Live, North Market), 9 minutes from the infamous Short North. The "art & soul" of Columbus, the Short North is a vibrant cultural and small business community. Park your car along Goodale Park on Buttles Ave for free and gallery hop, thrift or have dinner/drinks at just about any type of bar. 8 minutes away from the Greater Convention Center. Make sure to check out my Guidebook for activities, entertainment and restaurants - it's a reference of all my favorite places in Columbus. I'm a member of a Pizzeria meetup - My favorite mom & pop pizzerias are listed.
notes: When going upstairs it is necessary to duck your head. There is a low ceiling in the middle of the staircase.  I use Tide detergent to wash the bed linen/body pillow. I use a regular fabric softener. If you prefer no fabric softener, please provide this information in your correspondence. I use an ink free/fragrance free toilet paper. For longer stay reservations: I offer cleaning services at an additional $40 per visit. This includes laundering bed linens/towels, vacuuming, light dusting and washing the dishes. Number of Guests: I ask that all my guests be honest and accurate in the number of guests occupying my home. Utility expenses add up for larger groups. My property is priced competitively and fairly. Utility consumption: Please be considerate of your consumption. Please turn off the T.V. and the lights when not in use. Especially the T.V. because it consumes a lot of power.
transit: The property is ideally located on the same block to the nearest bus stop and it is also five minutes to either highways 70 & 315.
access: Guests may use the middle bedroom upstairs and have full access to the first floor of the home such as the living room, dining room/bedroom, dining area, kitchen, and bathroom. The second floor is being renovated (only when the unit is vacant) and only the middle bedroom is intended for guest usage at this time. Coffee/tea/bedside chocolates are provided complimentary, however, I do ask you to reimburse me with grocery money for any wine, beer, food or snacks from the kitchen that you consume. Guests will also have access to the fenced backyard and patio. Feel free to use the gas grill - simply clean it after you are done using it. Guests can park their car in the street (no garage).
interaction: Since guests dictate how much or how little they would like to interact with me, if certain guests would like to be social and include me that is fine and for those guests who want to be independent and do their own thing that is also fine as well.
house_rules: Welcome! There are some house rules: you may not smoke on the property. This is a smoke-free property. Also, please remove your shoes at the door. Feel free to help yourself to the wine, beer, snack and food items in the kitchen WITH THE UNDERSTANDING THAT YOU SHALL LEAVE GROCERY MONEY ON THE COUNTER for me to replace the items that you enjoyed. Please ONLY eat in the dining and/or kitchen areas. Please DO NOT eat in the Living room - this includes the bedroom. Feel free to use the gas grill located on the back patio. Simply clean it after you are finished using it. Lastly, this is not a house to host a party. I would suggest using another venue to host your party.  -- SOME LEGAL PRINT TO READ: Smoking, house parties, and rowdy behavior are not permitted on the property. This is not the house for you if you are looking to have a party or bring the party back with you. Guests are expected to be respectful of the neighbors by keeping noise levels to a minimum, especially at night. Guests
host_about:
Howdy! I’m Jake. I’m originally from New York, and while I miss my friends and family back home (not to mention the beach!), I absolutely love my mid-west home here in Columbus, Ohio!
By day I’m a real estate investor and by night I’m a social butterfly with my friends. I'm also an Airbnb cohost where I mentor aspiring local hosts. I earned my Superhost status because I have high standards for value, cleanliness, and communication.
I enjoy travelling and creating new experiences. My favorite country is Guatemala. The people, the food and the historical sites are breathtaking. My favorite city is Chicago. Through these travels and coupled with my 12 years landlording, I’ve been fortunate to learn what makes a great host: a great home, with a friendly host, in an awesome neighborhood, and the ability to do the things you love! I try to ensure that each and every guest I host walks away with all of that and hopefully more.
My life motto is, well, really my grandmother’s advice, “Jakey, live with NO REGRETS” (I can hear her thick NYer accent now). Sometimes I guess we just need a little reminder of that… And so, I invite you to travel more and see the big, beautiful world we live in.

name: Small Clintonville House with Large Shady Yard
summary: This delightful 2-story house is conveniently located about a block east of High Street and 18 blocks north of OSU. It has a large shady ravine-facing back yard and has a gravel driveway parking area suitable for 2 cars.  It’s a short walk to numerous restaurants, bars, two supermarkets, a CVS, a post office, and the High Street bus lines.
space: The house has a Living Room, Dining Room, Kitchen, Bath, and Laundry on the first floor, and a Bedroom on the second floor.  The Bedroom has a queen- size bed. The Living Room and Dining Room have knotty pine floors, and the Bedroom is carpeted. The Bathroom is off the Dining Room, at the bottom of the steps to the Bedroom. The kitchen is nicely-equipped with dishes, silverware, pots, pans, etc., and has a 24” electric range, a side-by-side refrigerator, and a dishwasher.  It also has a microwave, coffee maker, toaster, mixer, and blender. It includes a comfortable built-in sofa and a small 'table for two'.  There is a washer-dryer unit in a space adjacent to the kitchen.  The bath has a toilet, a lavatory, and a tub with shower. Towels and bed sheets are provided.  The house has gas heat and central AC, and is equipped with wireless internet and cable TV.  There is a 43” smart TV in the living room. name: Wilson Ave Flat
summary: Our company specializes in developing premium housing in developing neighborhoods. We love working with abandoned structures and turning them into artwork. We do as many homes in a localized area as possible to create a positive footprint that has real neighborhood impact. This unit is my personal unit in a building that has two units. It has been completely remodeled, with high efficiency HVAC, windows, appliances and flooring. We design for the urban dweller, with quick downtown access.
space: This top floor unit is bright and airy. Lots of windows provide sunshine during the day. Everything has been touched from lighting to flooring. We have taken special care to create a homelike environment. The unit is well heated and cooled with ceiling vents, providing comfort. All appliances and fixtures are new. The desk workspace is private and enable more than one person to work comfortably. Whether you want to stay in and watch netflix, or go out and enjoy what Columbus has to offer, this unit is a perfect choice.

neighborhood_overview: For many, seeing a neighborhood in development is exciting and unique.  Others may be wary. Those who find it exciting will enjoy the amenities we are able to offer while being close to a number of historic and growth-oriented neighborhoods. German Village, Columbus Downtown and Olde Towne East all offer amazing dining and after work cocktail opportunities. And for those who want the art scene, the Short North is a short inexpensive Uber ride away.
notes: It's important to note that this neighborhood is experiencing significant development. Newly remodeled beautiful homes and buildings sit next to boarded-up homes and units. It's impossible to drive down the street without seeing homes and multiunits being remodeled. As Columbus as grown, this and other areas have become extremely fashionable. We want you to enjoy Columbus and understand the neighborhood in which you will be staying and living.
transit: My building has off-street parking.  For those without a car, Uber is the best method of transport, with quick rides to all the areas of interest within the downtown core.
access: The building has both a front and back entrance with each unit having separate inner access for increased security. All aspects of the unit are available - living room, dining space, kitchen, office space, bedroom and bathroom.
interaction: I live in Columbus part-time and when I am here, I enjoy interacting with guests. I also have a group of specialists who I work with to ensure I exceed your expectations.
house_rules: Guests should always remove shoes in the unit.
host_about: I am a developer who has a passion for creating new urban experiences in areas that are developing and close to the core of what's happening in the city.  Equally I love to travel, and spend 6 to 7 months a year traveling both within the USA and throughout the world.  I take my job with me and enjoy the benefits of experiencing new living environments while working a job I love!  I look forward to sharing my developed properties with the Short Stay community.

name: Beautiful & Spacious Home Next to Downtown!
summary: We're Liz & Atticus and we live in the historic Southern Orchards. Our home is a beautiful & spacious new build with an open floor plan & lots of indoor plants right next to Nationwide Children's Hospital just a few blocks from Downtown & German Village. We live with our two dogs Rogue & Ghost, and our roommate Shannon. You'll find everything you need within minutes of our home including shopping, dinning, entertainment, and transit with easy access in & out of the city. Welcome to Columbus!
space: A new build with 4 bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms. Open floor plan, but feels very cozy. Lots of indoor plants. Large kitchen. Very clean and tidy. We have two dogs, Rogue and Ghost. Rogue is Doberman and Ghost is Great Pyrenees. Our cat Maria stays in our room so it's unlikely you'll see her. Large fenced in backyard. Liz and I are often around in the evening cooking dinner, watching a movie, and playing with the dogs.

neighborhood_overview: Southern Orchards is a diverse neighborhood rich in history and experiencing a lot of revitalization. We're only a few blocks from the beautiful and historic German Village and Downtown Columbus!
transit: Traveling in Columbus is easy! Street parking is available on our street. The COTA Bus (Central Ohio Transit Authority) runs the #1, #4, #5 line four blocks from our place. These lines will get you direct access to Downtown, The Greater Columbus Convention Center, Short North Arts District, and easy transfers to locations like The Ohio State University and Easton Town Center. A COGO Bike Share station is only four blocks from the house. COGO services all of Downtown Columbus. Car2Go Carsharing services most of the city. You will need to create an account prior to your trip. We're happy to answer any question regarding travel while you're here!
access: You'll have a private bedroom and a private bathroom with a double sink on the second floor. Ironing board and iron are in the closet. Wifi of course. We've got a new washer and dryer in the laundry room that you can use anytime with detergent. You're welcome to use any cooking utensils in the kitchen. Coffee and tea provided. Any common space is available for your use!
interaction: Elizabeth, Shannon, and I all work 40 hours a week. Shannon's 3 kids stay at the house periodically, but they're very nice and polite. We love having them here! We host movie night with some friends every Thursday night. You're more than welcome to join us. We're happy to hangout when you're here, or you'll have plenty of space if you prefer privacy. We'll be using the common areas in the mornings and evenings.

summary: Craftsman Home in arguably the best, most desirable neighborhood in the city.  430 sq. ft. fully loaded private guest suite in basement. Full size bed plus 8 ft. couch.  Kitchenette, private bath and entrance.  Easy access to all things Columbus.

Living room space with 8 foot couch and 2 chairs, coffee table, 40 inch flat screen, cable, DVD/CD player, movies, and Wii.  Sleeping area with full size bed, closet, desk and chair. neighborhood_overview: The home is in a single family residential highly desirable neighborhood.  A large park, library and rec center are 400 meters away.  There is a sit down or carryout deli a block away.  They do sell beer.  The is a Kroger half a mile south.  A nice chain restaurant/sports bar is a half mile north.
notes: Let me know if you would like to borrow bicycles.
transit: There is a bus stop a block away.  The bike/running trail is at the end of our street.   You may use our bicycles.  I-71 and SR 315 are about a mile away.  The airport is a 15 - 20 minute drive (more during rush hour).  OSU stadium is 2.9 miles away.  the Ohio State Expo fairgrounds 4.3 miles.  Mapfre stadium is 3.3 miles.  Ohio State House / Ohio Theater / Downtown / Arena District is a 13 minute drive.
access: Private entrance in back to suite and bathroom.  Self check in / out.   Shared laundry and fitness space can be accessed by request.
interaction: We will give you complete privacy, but are happy to entertain and socialize if you like.  When we are in our kitchen and dining room you can hear us walking.  Our floor is your ceiling.
house_rules: My wife has requested no couples.  She feels it would be best for our kids.
host_about: I am a lifelong Ohio Resident.  I have lived in Columbus since going to OSU in 1987.  I have been married for 20 years and we have 2 girls ages 13 and 11.  I taught elementary school for 20 years.  Now I have an exterminating/handyman business.  My wife has worked in and around politics and social issues for 20 years.  We met in the Army Reserves.  She's cool, I'm a geek.

summary: Our home is central to everything Columbus has to offer. Whether it be bar-hoping in the Short North, going to an Ohio State football game, or just cozying up to the fire with Netflix. neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood Franklinton is situated just west of Downtown Columbus, and is full of historic homes. This neighborhood has experienced many phases through out it's existence, and is currently in a revitalization phase. There are lots of properties being renovated, and some that still remain boarded and empty. This area has experienced some crime in the past, but has improved in recent years.  Franklinton has experienced several great floods in the past, and has been somewhat neglected throughout the middle to late part of the 1900's. The Franklinton Floodwall, completed in 2004, is 7 miles long, cost $134 million. The wall's completion has released the area from being considered a floodplain, as well as releasing the previous building restrictions that often prevented development in the past. As a result, commercial and industrial activities are starting to grow in the Franklinton Area.  The City of Columbus is focusing on creating a new Short North style neighborhood in Franklinton
transit: Uber and Lyft are great ways to get around in Columbus, and our central location allows you to get to most parts of downtown in under 10 minutes, and most other parts of Columbus in under 20 minutes.  We also are close to a COTA public bus stop. Also available in columbus are a bike share, and CAR2GO car-share program.

interaction: We will be available and close by if needed, however we like to let our guests have their privacy and not need to be bothered.

neighborhood_overview: The University District represents modern ideas and century old traditions, preservation and renewal, urban living and secluded wooded hollows. The University District is comprised of the neighborhoods surrounding one of the nation's larget public universities, The Ohio State University. It is an eclectic mix of thirteen distinct neighborhoods: Dennison Place/The Circles, Glen Echo, Indianola Forest, Indianola Terrace, Iuka Ravine, Northwood Park, Old North Columbus, Peach District, Sohud, Tuttle Park, and Weinland Park. The area now known as the University District was not originally part of the City of Columbus at all. In 1842, out of expansive farmland emerged a separate town, North Columbus. name: Charming Clintonville Cottage
summary: Cozy vintage cottage in South Clintonville, steps to the bike path in one direction, High St and shops, restaurants, and bars in the other.  The whole 1st floor, with 2 bedrooms, dining and living room, and kitchen and bath is available to spread out and make yourself at home. I’ll sometimes be home, mostly hanging out upstairs, and sometimes I’ll be out of town. The bathroom and kitchen are shared when I’m home. Our home is 110 years old, with all the quirks and charms that come with it!
space: Our eclectic bohemian home is in one of Columbus’ older neighborhoods, on a quaint brick lined street in Clintonville. Built in 1907, it’s unusual in its- mostly- original design, with a quirk of no hallways, and each room having a minimum of two doorways. There are even two front doors, confusing UPS drivers for a few generations now! We have a front porch and shady back yard and garden to enjoy during the warmer months. Inside, there’s a comfortable and elegant living room and dining room with plenty of seating, and a kitchen with a desk for working or just hanging out while cooking. The kitchen is equipped with the usual kitchen stuff, and pantry of basics- you’re welcome to use anything there. Our claw foot tub is great for a leisurely soak, and use the shower to efficiently rinse off your day. We have two bedrooms- the main bedroom, with a queen sized brass bed, faces the front of the house, with a small library you’re welcome to browse while you’re with us. I’ll have the top draw

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood, Clintonville, is one of C-bus’ jewels. Just north of the University area, the neighborhood is full of vintage homes, built between 1900 and the 1930s. Always in the top 3 of best places to live and hang out in Columbus, it’s progressive, walkable, and safe. Clintonville has lots of restaurants, breweries, coffee shops, and bars, along with shops of all kinds, many of which are within a few block walk of our home. Our home is exactly halfway between High St, with all the stops and places to eat and drink, and the Olentangy Bike Trail, which takes you from downtown to the south, to Worthington, a few miles to the north, and several parks along the way. High St is Columbus’ main thoroughfare, and it can take you pretty much anywhere you need to go. Busses are frequent and inexpensive, and Uber or Lyft can take you downtown, OSU, or the Short North in just a few minutes.
transit: We have both on- and off-site parking, with 1-2 (depending on whether I’m home) spots behind the house, and public street parking in front. The #2, or High St, COTA bus runs every few minutes, and late on the weekends, and of course Uber and Lyft can take you anywhere you need to go.
access: As a guest, you have access to our first floor, and our porch and back yard. The attic and basement are private.
interaction: I travel a lot during the week, so if that’s when you’re coming, you will likely have the house to yourself. When I’m in town, I’ll generally leave the first floor to you. I’m very availed by text, whether I’m in town or not.
house_rules: No smoking in the house.
host_about:
Introvert who loves people. Liker of books, food, sharing opinions, pretty things, and bad music.

When you’re staying with me, sometimes I’ll be home but staying out of your way, and sometimes I’ll be traveling for work. I’m a Certified Tourism Ambassador for Columbus, so I’m very happy to share recommendations for places to while you’re spending time in C-bus.

If I’m traveling, I’ll be looking for a place to relax after seeing your town, and while we will surely find you delightful we will largely be seeking alone time.

The house is located on one of the quietest streets in the short north with no through traffic and no daily parking issues.

neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village, which is situated northwest of downtown and south of The Ohio State University is one of central Ohio's cores of fine residential architecture. The area is known for its Victorian houses, which were built when a streetcar line first ran along Neil Avenue around 1900. Centrally located, no part of Columbus is more than 15-20 minutes away. The brick paver streets complete the neighborhood giving it an early 1900's vibe.
transit: Major ride share platforms, CoGo bike share rack is a couple blocks away, Car2Go (need membership) and newly founded Hopper Carts, which is a free shuttle service are all available.
access: You have access to everything in the house and on the property including the basement where the washer/dryer unit is located and patio space outdoors.
interaction: As a lifelong resident of Columbus and just a phone call or text away, I'm happy to make suggestions on places to eat, drink, play and see while visiting our spectacular city! Let me know how I can make your stay the most enjoyable.
house_rules: If personal items are left at the property, you must notify host within 12 hours of check-out to ensure cleaning crew does not dispose of items not associated with the home. Late check-out is not always possible, but in the event that you need to check out late, you will be charged $29 for the first hour and then $10 for every hour after that. After three hours (2 pm), you will be charged for the full amount for that day in addition to the $49 late check-out fees stated above.  If there is another guest staying after you, the cleaning crew has the right to access the property at 1 pm to prepare it for the next guest who checks in at 2 pm. When needing late check-out, please notify the host ASAP to work through the late check-out process.

neighborhood_overview: We've enjoyed this quiet, family-friendly neighborhood for over 25 years. Our neighbors are friends, and we take pride in our diverse local community. Our home is situated near the far end of our neighborhood, which offers less traffic and more privacy. There are several fast food restaurants and gas stations at the nearest large intersection to meet any immediate needs you may have. Venture out a little further, and you have access to nearby Ohio Dominican University campus, the historic town of Bexley, as well as retail shopping, AMC movie theatre, and a variety of restaurants at Easton Towne Center.  Looking for brunch, nightlife, or a unique group experience? Downtown Columbus includes diverse neighborhoods like Olde Town East, Arena District, Short North, and Brewery District where you can find everything from The Columbus Museum of Art to The Ohio Theatre to Hot Chicken Takeover.
notes: Onsite parking is available for up to 3 cars in the driveway and 2 cars in the covered, secure, attached garage. Beautiful, tranquil pond and outside patio areas (front deck, Florida room, and back patio), well-groomed lawn, and kid-friendly swing-set with hide-away picnic table.
transit: Access to the large major highways is just minutes away from our doorstep. If you don't have your own transportation during your stay, our neighborhood also provides easy access to Uber, Lyft, and COTA, our timely and affordable public transportation system ($4 for a daily pass!).
access: Our home provides the perfect comforts of your own home, with an added tropical flair! Guests will have easy access to several common areas, including a fully finished basement, two living rooms, TWO 60" plasma flatscreen tvs perfect for watching sporting events or your favorite shows, a beautifully restored dining room for 6, a fully functional and recently renovated kitchen, exercise equipment on 2 floors, 2.5 beautifully decorated bathrooms, and 3 spacious bedrooms with mounted flatscreen tvs. FREE WiFi and access to Netflix. We also have lots of beautiful outdoor space for you to enjoy.
interaction: We will be nearby in the city during your stay. Please let us know if you need any help with the working appliances, or deciding on dinner plans for the night!

neighborhood_overview: This walkable, bikeable neighborhood, just two miles from downtown Columbus and its major highways, is one of Columbus’ most beloved areas. A hybrid of urban flair and neighborhood warmth, Grandview’s vibe is at the same time laid-back and buzzing with energy. Stroll the wide, tree-lined sidewalks of Grandview Avenue amid the hum of café-table chatter. Discover specialized independent shops, curated New York-style boutiques, a chocolatier’s gorgeous handmade truffles, independent breweries, top-rated coffee roasters, cutting-edge salons, and of course, world-class restaurants that use fresh, locally-sourced ingredients. The eclectic mix of restaurants here have consistently been recognized by critics and diners alike for their cuisine, ambience, and outstanding attention to detail. Grandview is also home to a collection of award-winning craft microbreweries and taprooms. A hub of creativity, culture, and out-of-the-ordinary experiences, Grandview offers an array of guided food and drin
transit: We have parking behind the house and free street parking in front of the house. Our place is a quick and cheap Uber to anywhere in the downtown area.
access: You are able to access the entire place.
interaction: We are hands-off hosts but are available as needed!
host_about: I am from Columbus, Ohio. I went to college at Ohio State where I played football and studied finance. I then moved to Chicago for a real estate finance position. After four years there, I left that position and now run my own businesses. I love traveling, attending concerts and sporting events, skiing, trying new restaurants, grabbing beers with friends, cooking, juicing, yoga, high intensity training, and running.

neighborhood_overview: The Discovery District is the eastern district of downtown Columbus. Within the Discovery District are buildings of culture, art, design, and education. Columbus Metropolitan Library and the Columbus Museum of Art are both located within the district. Also, there are numerous educational options within this district.  Located in the district are the Columbus College of Art and Design, which was founded in 1879 as the Columbus Art School and enrolls roughly 1,300 students, and the Capital University Law School. The area allows for easy accessibility to everything Columbus has to offer including the Arena District, German Village, Short North, Crew Stadium, and is 10 minutes from Port Columbus International Airport.

summary: Immersed in the historical charm of Victorian Village, our carriage house will give you the feel of a "tiny home" in the city. The friendly atmosphere of the community is evident as neighbors walk their dogs, jog, and cycle throughout the day. This stand alone home is in very close proximity to The Ohio State University, Arena District, and Goodale Park, and is a short trek to High Street and the Short North.  It is ideal for solo, couples, or small families who enjoy a cozy, intimate setting.
space: Our tiny house is located in the heart of great destinations in our city. It is .5 mile from Goodale Park, about 1 mile from The Ohio State University, 1.1 mile from the Short North, 1.3 miles from the Arena District, 1.3 miles from the Greater Columbus Convention Center, and 2.2 miles to our downtown. This stand alone home is in very close proximity to The Ohio State University, Arena District, and Goodale Park, and is a short trek to High Street and the Short North.  It is ideal for solo, couples, or small families who enjoy a cozy, intimate setting. Our tiny house is located in the heart of great destinations in our city. It is .5 mile from Goodale Park, about 1 mile from The Ohio State University, 1.1 mile from the Short North, 1.3 miles from the Arena District, 1.3 miles from the Greater Columbus Convention Center, and 2.2 miles to our downtown.  Our house is a cozy, intimate 600 sq. feet. It has a small, front yard with a sidewalk that leads to the house from the street. The private, keypad entry will welcome you into the living room comp
neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village a lovely neighborhood with historical architecture and large trees nestled in urban surroundings.  Some homes are even nationally registered historical landmarks. Neighbors leisurely traverse throughout the community walking dogs, jogging, and cycling, and there is a welcomed respect among one another. It is a walkable neighborhood, with a walk score of eighty, to many of Columbus' prime locations including the Olentangy walking/biking path, Goodale Park, the Short North, The Ohio State University, the Arena District, and the Greater Columbus Convention Center.
notes: Every home has a personality of a sort. Here are some tips to consider while in ours: *Our home is tiny, so please do not entertain guests that are not an agreed part of our visiting arrangements. ONLY PRE-APPROVED GUESTS ALLOWED. *The floor has a slight tilt to it, hardly noticeable. You may feel your body shift a millimeter to adjust to this characteristic. *If it rains, the wood on the deck can get a little slick so be careful while walking on it. *The hot water tank in our home is smaller than typical, so be creative in managing hot water use, particularly with two or more guests. *You will notice two ottomans in the living room. One contains linens and pillows for the sleeper sofa. The second one is accompanied by an eating tray with extendable legs to use as a lap table while sitting on the sofa, or just use it on the ottoman as a little table. *If it's a windy day, keep a hold of the front screen door handle as you enter and exit so it doesn't slam open. *When you leave, be sure
transit: Parking at the house has free, first come first serve parking on the street. Please note that two of three streets around our house are free 24/7, but the third is permit only. Be sure to pay attention to the parking signs.  If you enjoy walking, many of the prime locations in close proximity are a mile or less away. The public COTA bus services the area with a bus stop on the block. UBER, Lift, and taxis are available of course. For first time UBER riders, we invite you to get your first ride free by using our invite code "sonjad790ue", and enjoy the excursion on us!
access: You will have access to the entire home, front yard, and deck. Note that the parking space behind the house is someone else's property to which our guests do not have access.
interaction: We extend utmost privacy to our guests and will primarily correspond with you through Airbnb messaging or phone calls. In all instances, we will do our part to make you feel welcome.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood Franklinton is situated just west of Downtown Columbus, and is full of historic homes. This neighborhood has experienced many phases through out it's existence, and is currently in a revitalization phase. There are lots of properties being renovated, and some that still remain boarded and empty. This area has experienced some crime in the past, but has improved in recent years.  Franklinton has experienced several great floods in the past, and has been somewhat neglected throughout the middle to late part of the 1900's. The Franklinton Floodwall, completed in 2004, is 7 miles long, cost $134 million. The wall's completion has released the area from being considered a floodplain, as well as releasing the previous building restrictions that often prevented development in the past. As a result, commercial and industrial activities are starting to grow in the Franklinton Area.  The City of Columbus is focusing on creating a new Short North style neighborhood in Franklinton
transit: Uber and Lyft are great ways to get around in Columbus, and our central location allows you to get to most parts of downtown in under 10 minutes, and most other parts of Columbus in under 20 minutes.  We also are close to a COTA public bus stop. Also available in columbus are a bike share, and CAR2GO car-share program.
access: Guests will have the entire second and third floor, two bedroom apartment to themselves. Private bathroom and kitchen included. Guest will also have access to the basement where laundry machines are.
interaction: We will be available and close by if needed, however we like to let our guests have their privacy and not need to be bothered.
host_about: I continue to be excited about Airbnb and home sharing every day! I enjoy hosting guests, I LOVE to travel, and I really love meeting new people. I am a real estate broker that owns my own business, and I feel that my calling in life is to making spaces for people to enjoy. 5 things I can't live without are live music, friends, exploring new places, bacon, my drum set!

neighborhood_overview: The house is located in a safe, quiet, working-class neighborhood. We love that the house has a peaceful, spacious garden in the middle of the city.  We also like that it is unexpected in it's location. We love the cultural and economic diversity of the neighborhood. Our house is set back from the street and rests on an acre of land with old growth trees and an abundance of lush landscaping. The north side of the house faces a wooded ravine. In late spring, summer, and early fall, you can't even see the nearby streets. It feels like you are far from city life, when in fact you are only minutes away. Our house is close to all things in Columbus through highway access. If you are looking to venture close to eat or get coffee, Bexley is a half mile away and has many great options. While there are things to do fairly close by, the neighborhood itself is not walkable and is best navigated via car.
notes: Our family lives on the premises. During the day time you may hear us walking around the house and muffled chatting with our kids. You may hear us laughing and talking during dinner time. You may also catch us working or playing outside when it’s nice out! After 8pm you shouldn’t hear much noise beyond the occasional creaky stairs.  There is a beautiful antique claw foot tub in the bedroom, and beautifully moody private half bath. No shower however.  There is kitchenette in the living room, but there is no sink (there is a sink in the bathroom) or stove (there is a toaster oven). There is a fireplace in the living room, but it is only for use during the winter months.  There is a door in the bathroom that goes to private space and is locked.  Photo Shoots May be permitted at a separate rate and with permission. Please provide detailed information about the shoot when requesting to book.
transit: The house is close to I-670, which connects to all major highways. It is a half mile from the Bexley coffee shop and Bexley natural market.  There is a public bus stop (COTA) close; a 4 minute walk.  The house is a quick uber / lyft ride from the airport.
access: You will have a private entrance with keypad entry into the bedroom. Attached to the bedroom is your own private large living room with extra spots for sleeping, relaxing, eating or working. Also attached to the bedroom is your own private half bathroom (no shower).
interaction: We may cross paths outside while coming / going, enjoying our beautiful property, or sitting by the fire pit, but other than that we leave you be. But of course, we are available by phone / text if you need anything at all.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood Franklinton is situated just west of Downtown Columbus, and is full of historic homes. This neighborhood has experienced many phases through out it's existence, and is currently in a revitalization phase. There are lots of properties being renovated, and some that still remain boarded and empty. This area has experienced some crime in the past, but has improved in recent years.  Franklinton has experienced several great floods in the past, and has been somewhat neglected throughout the middle to late part of the 1900's. The Franklinton Floodwall, completed in 2004, is 7 miles long, cost $134 million. The wall's completion has released the area from being considered a floodplain, as well as releasing the previous building restrictions that often prevented development in the past. As a result, commercial and industrial activities are starting to grow in the Franklinton Area.  The City of Columbus is focusing on creating a new Short North style neighborhood in Franklinton
transit: Uber and Lyft are great ways to get around in Columbus, and our central location allows you to get to most parts of downtown in under 10 minutes, and most other parts of Columbus in under 20 minutes.  We also are close to a COTA public bus stop. Also available in columbus are a bike share, and CAR2GO car-share program.
access: Guests will have the entire house including the bottom floor two bedroom apartment, and end/3rd floor apartment to themselves. 2 Private bathrooms and 2 kitchens included. Guest will also have access to the basement where laundry machines are.
interaction: We will be available and close by if needed, however we like to let our guests have their privacy and not need to be bothered.
host_about: I continue to be excited about Airbnb and home sharing every day! I enjoy hosting guests, I LOVE to travel, and I really love meeting new people. I am a real estate broker that owns my own business, and I feel that my calling in life is to making spaces for people to enjoy. 5 things I can't live without are live music, friends, exploring new places, bacon, my drum set!

name: Historic 1920’s Craftsman Home. Perfect location!
summary: This historic 1920’s Craftsman home is perfectly situated in the charming Clintonville Neighborhood. Walkable to the best Farmers Market in Columbus, local coffee shops, charming boutiques and nationally known restaurants (Little Eater, Hot Chicken Takeover, and Jeni's to name a few!). While a vibrant walkable community is right outside your door, you can easily get away from the hustle and bustle. Whestone Park and the Olentangy trail is just a stroll down the street in the other direction.
space: Our 1920's home has an interesting history. In 1924, this bungalow style house was known as the Sherman Private School which was an extension of the Morrey School of Music. Now, it serves as a warm home to a music loving family. While the home has been updated, the original charm has been preserved. A multitude of windows in every room let natural light in making this home feel even more warm and spacious.

You'll see lots of morning dog walkers if you wake up early and kids playing outside in the afternoon. Being on the west side of high street is known locally for having spacious tree lined streets. Our particular street is special because it leads to a private park called Webster Park. If you walk further down, a path takes you to the Olentangy Trail which offers a seamless route from Worthington to downtown Columbus, traveling through the heart of the Ohio State University campus. This trail also winds through several neighborhoods along the Olentangy River, with trailheads at several major city parks, including Whetstone Park which is a 5 minute walk from the house. Whetstone Park is a community park and landmark for the Clintonville neighborhood that encompasses over 136 acres for both active and passive use.  While close to nature, this home is also close to coffee shops and restaurants giving o
notes: Our home is perfectly situated for travelers who want access to a lot that Columbus has to offer. 315 and 71 on ramps are both easily accessible in minutes. Port Columbus Airport is 17 minutes from our home. Ohio State University, Mapfre Stadium, Ohio State Fairgrounds, and Wexner Medical Center are all approximately 5 minutes away and can be easily accessed by COTA or Uber/Lyft if you'd prefer not to drive. The Short North Arts District and the Convention Center are less than 15 minutes away. Farther south find the historic German Village which is a 17 minute drive and Easton Mall is 19 minutes away.  If you want to say local, you are in the HEART of Clintonville close to parks, restaurants, coffee shops, boutiques, and the best Farmer's Market. neighborhood_overview: Enjoy Northstar Cafe just around the corner for breakfast, brunch, lunch, or dinner. If you're into tacos, Condado is a fun spot. Mouton is a lovely choice for craft cocktails, and if caffeine is your need One Line Coffee shop is a great choice. The Short North has it all - from great events in Goodale Park and at the Convention Center, to restaurants, bars, coffee shops, galleries, and local shops. This apartment puts you in the heart of the neighborhood.
notes: This is a first floor apartment, but there are two steps up from the sidewalk.
transit: The Short North is conveniently located between Ohio State University and Downtown Columbus. You're within easy walking distance of the Convention Center, Express Live, Nationwide Arena, and Goodale Park (which hosts ComFest and the Pride Festival), plus many of the city's best restaurants, shops, and galleries. A longer walk takes you to Ohio State University to the north or Downtown to the south.  In addition to walking, the free circulator bus (Cbus) stops just around the corner and takes you to Downtown and German Village. CoGo bike rental stations dot the neighborhood.  Of course Lyft and Uber are popular options for getting around.  The apartment also features a reserved off-street parking space behind the house for guests who have a car.
access: There's a washer and dryer just off the entrance of the unit.  You are only sharing it with me. Parking is available in a parking lot behind the building. Just let us know how many cars your group will have. The apartment comes with high speed internet access - 100mbps.
interaction: We live nearby, and can be available if needed for maintenance issues or other concerns. We may briefly come by to greet you and make sure everything is going well with your stay. Check-in is automated.

host_about:
I dig psychology, gardening, cycling, being a gym rat, and cooking. I have volunteered at a kids camp every summer since 1999 that teaches critical thinking and a love for nature. 

I have lived in Columbus most of my life and I love it here and I love sharing it with other people. 

My career in the non-profit sector has let me travel all over the country. I love the Bay Area, NYC, Washington state, and the Rockies.

neighborhood_overview: This walkable, bikeable neighborhood, a short 1.5 miles from downtown Columbus and it’s major highways, is one of Columbus’ most coveted areas. A hybrid of urban flair and neighborhood warmth, Grandview’s vibes are at the same time laid-back and buzzing with energy. Stroll the wide, tree-lined sidewalks of Grandview Ave amid the hum of cafe-table chatter. Discover specialized independent shops, curated New-York style boutiques, a chocolatier’s gorgeous handmade truffles, independent breweries, top-rated coffee roasters, cutting-edge salons, and of course, world-class restaurants that use fresh, locally-sourced ingredients. The electric mix of restaurants here have consistently been recognized by critics and diners alike for their cuisine, ambience, and outstanding attention to detail. Grandview is also home to a collection of award-winning craft microbreweries and taprooms. A hub of creative culture and out-of-the-ordinary experiences, Grandview offers an array of guided food and drink
transit: If you’re going to hang around Grandview, the best option would be to just walk due to the ideal location of the property, but parking is easy to come by as well so driving or Uber will work. If you’re going to head downtown or Short North, Uber is the best option since parking is hard to come by.

neighborhood_overview: Victorian Village, which runs along Neil Avenue south of The Ohio State University and northwest of downtown Columbus, is one of central Ohio’s cores of fine residential architecture. The area is known for its Victorian houses, which were built when a streetcar line first ran along Neil Avenue around 1900. Victorian Village is directly west of the well known Short North area of Columbus. Some of the most celebrated spots to eat and drink in Columbus are in the Short North Arts District, which is gaining recognition as a dining destination. This portion of High Street is filled with boutiques, art galleries, coffee houses, restaurants, and bars.
notes: We have a strict no party policy. While our house is able to host large groups, we expect you to treat this home respectfully and obey all house rules. Thank you in advance!

I live with my wife Kate in the Short North, between Ohio State's campus and downtown Columbus.

neighborhood_overview: There's an energy and excitement in Columbus that's going to hit you as soon as you arrive. Big things are happening here, and you're invited to join in. The city is booming, and not just in population. The Columbus Museum of Art added a spectacular new wing, and the Scioto Mile puts 33 acres of new riverfront parkland in the heart of downtown. The innovative food scene melds artisan food producers with imaginative chefs to create meals that are far greater than the sum of their parts. Nationally acclaimed distilleries work together with brewers, coffee roasters and high-end cocktail bars, black box stages, music halls and dive bars to deliver unforgettable nightlife. Neighborhoods on all sides of downtown are bursting with new places to eat and shop, and artists are shaping new areas of the city into dynamic spaces to explore. It's time to get to know the Columbus that grew up when you weren't looking.
notes: Dining options range from student-centric to upscale; find a variety of options around High Street and 11th Avenue. The Wexner Center for the Arts showcases rotating modern art exhibitions, and also hosts a huge variety of events, ranging from music, theater and dance performances to film screenings and artist talks. Across the plaza, the free Billy Ireland Cartoon Museum has the largest collection of cartoons and comics in the world, and features rotating exhibitions of historic, classic and modern comics.
transit: It's easy to get around Columbus. We have lots of great options to get around the city from public transportation to car sharing services. Columbus is also home to all major national car rental brands including Dollar, Enterprise, and Thrifty. Get real-time flight information for departures and arrivals at John Glenn Columbus International Airport. CoGo Bike Share: Apps: Transit app for iPhone & Android. See real time availability in app and generate release codes. Cost: 1-Day access pass ($8) 3-Day pass ($18) annual memberships ($75/year or $7/mo with annual commitment) CoGo is a public transportation system with 365 bikes at 46 stations located throughout downtown Columbus. Available for use 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. The CoGo system is intended to help you quickly get from Point A to B.Trips over 30 minutes accrue an additional $3 per half hour left undocked. Timer resets when you dock. E.C.T. Pedicab: Cost: $1.50/minute; trips between downtown districts average $5-$25 Inspire
