neighborhood_overview: This residence is located in Southern Orchards part of Columbus, right next to German Village. It is also few blocks from Nationwide Children's Hospital. There is a variety of local restaurants such as Barcelona, Lindey's, The Sycamore, The Crest, Skillet, The Brown Bag Deli, Scrambler Marie's, Panera and Tim Horton's. Or get meals delivered through Grub Hub or an awesome new delivery service called Clustertruck! Please note that while we are a couple blocks from German Village and half a million dollar homes, this is an up-and-coming neighborhood. It is in the process of being revitalized, but that type of work takes years. Nationwide Children's Hospital has improved it tremendously in the time we have been there, but is still a little rough around the edges. There are neighbors that are holding out for higher property offers, leaving their buildings boarded in the meantime.

neighborhood_overview: This property is located in Old North Columbus, conveniently located near the Ohio State campus, Ohio Stadium, known as “The Shoe,” and Ohio Expo Center. Old North Columbus is popular for its local music and it's unique "untouched architecture" which is reminiscent of its old roots. Old North Columbus is a great walkable neighborhood with dining options range from student-centric to upscale. Where to go: •	Ohio State University Campus – 5 min walk •	Short North Art District – 5 min drive •	German Village – 12 min drive •	Easton – 13 min drive •	Scioto Mile – 5 min drive What to do: •	Franklin Park Conservatory and Botanical Gardens – 14 min drive  •	Wexner Center of Arts – 9 min drive •	COSI – 6 min drive •	Columbus Museum of Art – 8 min drive •	Greater Columbus Convention Center - 7 min drive •	Columbus Zoo & Aquarium – 26 min drive •	Columbus Coffee & Ale Trail
transit: This listing is located in Old North Columbus just two miles north of downtown and accessible via CoGo Bike Share and COTA buses, the Old North District is situated next to the massive campus of Ohio State, along with its sports venues, nightlife spots and restaurants.

This house is available for certain events, as long as the details of the event are disclosed to me, and approved by me ahead of time.  • NO SMOKING OR VAPING inside the house – please do not discard your cigarettes butts in the house trash cans. They get stinky.  • DO NOT ENGAGE IN ILLEGAL ACTIVITIES anywhere on the property. • DO NOT LEAVE ANY FOOD OUT that will attract uninvited pests. Our home is pest-free and we intend to keep it that way with your help. • QUIET HOURS: Sunday - Thursday: 9pm - 8am, Friday - Saturday: 10pm -8am • If you break or damage something, please let me know and arrange for its replacement or repair.
host_about:
What's up fellow Airbnbers!

Thanks for checking out my profile! Hopefully, I get to connect with you further through hosting you at one of my properties or staying as your guest on Airbnb. 

For me, Airbnb fulfills two of my life's biggest passions; technology and real estate. 

My first stay in an Airbnb came in 2013 while I was on a trip with my roommate to Spain.  Since then I have always been enthusiastic about experiencing unique homes in foreign places through the Airbnb platform. It wasn't until 2017, that I opened up my first Airbnb and I now wish I hadn't waited so long!! 

I’ve been investing in real estate since 2008 when I house hacked my way to my first investment property. Since that first deal, I have done dozens of real estate investments, from campus rentals to fix and flips. All along the way, I have looked at ways technology could help me invest.   As a certified millennial and real estate investor, it doesn't get much better then Airbnb.  

Here is a little more about me:

I was born and raised in Akron, Ohio, went to The Ohio State University and lived in Ohio for the first 26 years of my life. So I guess you might say I am a good 'ol midwestern boy but with one caveat, I inherited the traveling gene from my parents. It is hard keeping up with those two, they have visited all 50 states and are now retirees traveling the world. 

In 2013, on a surprisingly sunny February day in Columbus, OH, while dressed in head to toe denim for a charity bar crawl, I met my now wife, Danica (see, Ohio is for lovers ;-). Together we decided to move to California where we currently reside.  

Today, I fulfill my desire for technology as a Technical Project Manager while expanding my experience as a remote real estate investor. 

My other interests include:

- Competitive sports (mostly basketball).
- Exercise (but only so I can keep up with my wife).
- Experiencing new things, especially food (yes, I am a foodie).
- Hanging out with friends and family.

As I head into my 30's I am looking forward to growing my presence on Airbnb. I am excited for the experiences that I will have and the people I will meet as both a host and a guest.

The neighborhood has seen lots of development recently with several mixed use development projects close to downtown and many existing single family homes getting rehabbed and brought back to life.

neighborhood_overview: Great quiet neighborhood located right next to the hustle and bustle of High Street. Park your car and walk to High Street for plenty of dining and shopping options, and just a few blocks down near 2nd, you can catch the Cbus (Columbus' free bus) that can take you downtown, to German Village, and the Brewery District. A quick walk Neil Street and you'll be right in the heart of Ohio State's campus and near all the tail gaiting for football games at Ohio Stadium. Also a few blocks away is the great Olentangy Bike trail that stretches for miles along the Olentangy River.
transit: Easy on street parking (opposite side of street does not require a permit and there are always plenty of spaces). We are close to COTA bus stops (1,2, and 5). A few blocks down is also a Cbus stop (free bus that goes from the short north south to the brewery district with stops downtown). There are also hubs for Cogo bike rentals within walking distance and a short trek to the Olentangy bike path. Of course there are also plenty of uber and lyft options.
access: Guests have access to entire home.
interaction: Will we not have interaction with guests but we be easily reachable should you need anything.

summary: Welcome to Columbus! We're Kelli & Teno and we live with our 2 dogs in Historic Southern Orchards just a few blocks from Nationwide Children's Hospital & Livingston Park. space: Fully renovated home with open concept floor plan and lots of natural light. Spacious kitchen, Laundry access and fenced in back yard. Very clean and tidy. Plenty of street parking available. This is 1 of 2 bedrooms listed in our home. You'll have a private bedroom with a queen sized bed and closet, located on the second floor. The bathroom is also on the second floor and may be shared if both bedrooms are booked at the same time. You will have a lock & key to your bedroom.  There’s a great workspace in the bedroom, perfect for those traveling for work or business! Use the Amazon echo dot (Alexa) to listen to your favorite artist or set an alarm! description: Welcome to Columbus! We're Kelli & Teno and we live with our 2 dogs in Historic Southern Orchards just a few blocks from Nationwide Children's Hospital & Livingston Park. Everything you need is within minutes of our home including shopping, dining, and transit access. This is the perfect space for visiting medical professionals! **Please read all details carefully**  If you'd like to book both bedrooms, visit: https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/26462596?s=51 Fully renovated home with open concept floor plan and lots of natural light. Spacious kitchen, Laundry access and fenced in back yard. Very clean and tidy. Plenty of street parking available. This is 1 of 2 bedrooms listed in our home. You'll have a private bedroom with a queen sized bed and closet, located on the second floor. The bathroom is also on the second floor and may be shared if both bedrooms are booked at the same time. You will have a lock & key to your bedroom.  There’s a great workspace in the bedroom, perfect for those tra
neighborhood_overview: Southern Orchards is a diverse neighborhood experiencing a lot of revitalization due to the Nationwide Children's Expansion.  Our home is just 10 minutes from the airport and right around the corner from Nationwide Children's Hospital and Livingston Park. Minutes from Franklin Park, Historic German Village, Schiller Park, and the Short North Arts District. There is a Panera Bread, CVS, Fitness Center, and multiple restaurants within walking distance.
notes: We're early risers and typically wake between 6-7:30am. We have 2 friendly dogs, Rainey & Anya. Depending on how light you sleep you may hear us briefly in the morning when we let the dogs out and get ready for the day. We try to keep the noise level to a minimum and tend to let the dogs spend more time outside when guests are here, weather permitting. They also sleep in our bedroom at night. They love meeting new people and will happily interact with you. We hope you’re an animal lover!  We have another bedroom listed that shares a bathroom with this listing. It is possible that there may be other guests in the home. Please feel free to ask whether the other room will be booked during your stay. For the safety of you and your belongings, you will have a lock & key to your bedroom. Master Bedroom and our Personal Office Space are not available for guest use.
transit: Getting around is super easy! Street parking is available on our street right in front of the house. There is a COTA bus stop and COGO Bike Share Station just a few blocks from us. Zipcar, LimeBike, Uber, and Lyft also available. I-70/I-71 and 670 are easily accessible.
access: Private Bedroom and either Private or Shared Bathroom depending on whether or not the other bedroom is booked. Half bathroom located on the first floor. You're welcome to use common areas including the kitchen plus all utensils and appliances, living room, and washer/dryer.  There is a large flat-screen TV with DVD's, video games, and a PS3 stored in a closet on a roller cart. Play a video game or watch some Netflix. Feel free to hang out in the back yard and enjoy your morning cup of coffee or tea!
interaction: We live on-site and will be available for questions and recommendations. You'll have space and privacy, but we're happy to hangout if you would like. Level of interaction is entirely up to each guest's preference. You're more than welcome to share the common spaces alongside us. If you need anything when we're not home, please feel free to shoot us a text or send a message in the Airbnb app.

neighborhood_overview: There's an energy and excitement in Columbus that's going to hit you as soon as you arrive. Big things are happening here, and you're invited to join in. The city is booming, and not just in population. The Columbus Museum of Art added a spectacular new wing, and the Scioto Mile puts 33 acres of new riverfront parkland in the heart of downtown. The innovative food scene melds artisan food producers with imaginative chefs to create meals that are far greater than the sum of their parts. Nationally acclaimed distilleries work together with brewers, coffee roasters and high-end cocktail bars, black box stages, music halls and dive bars to deliver unforgettable nightlife. Neighborhoods on all sides of downtown are bursting with new places to eat and shop, and artists are shaping new areas of the city into dynamic spaces to explore. It's time to get to know the Columbus that grew up when you weren't looking.
notes: Dining options range from student-centric to upscale; find a variety of options around High Street and 11th Avenue. The Wexner Center for the Arts showcases rotating modern art exhibitions, and also hosts a huge variety of events, ranging from music, theater and dance performances to film screenings and artist talks. Across the plaza, the free Billy Ireland Cartoon Museum has the largest collection of cartoons and comics in the world, and features rotating exhibitions of historic, classic and modern comics.
transit: It's easy to get around Columbus. We have lots of great options to get around the city from public transportation to car sharing services. Columbus is also home to all major national car rental brands including Dollar, Enterprise, and Thrifty. Get real-time flight information for departures and arrivals at John Glenn Columbus International Airport. CoGo Bike Share: Apps: Transit app for iPhone & Android. See real time availability in app and generate release codes. Cost: 1-Day access pass ($8) 3-Day pass ($18) annual memberships ($75/year or $7/mo with annual commitment) CoGo is a public transportation system with 365 bikes at 46 stations located throughout downtown Columbus. Available for use 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. The CoGo system is intended to help you quickly get from Point A to B.Trips over 30 minutes accrue an additional $3 per half hour left undocked. Timer resets when you dock. E.C.T. Pedicab: Cost: $1.50/minute; trips between downtown districts average $5-$25 Inspire

host_about:
What's up fellow Airbnbers!

Thanks for checking out my profile! Hopefully, I get to connect with you further through hosting you at one of my properties or staying as your guest on Airbnb. 

For me, Airbnb fulfills two of my life's biggest passions; technology and real estate. 

My first stay in an Airbnb came in 2013 while I was on a trip with my roommate to Spain.  Since then I have always been enthusiastic about experiencing unique homes in foreign places through the Airbnb platform. It wasn't until 2017, that I opened up my first Airbnb and I now wish I hadn't waited so long!! 

I’ve been investing in real estate since 2008 when I house hacked my way to my first investment property. Since that first deal, I have done dozens of real estate investments, from campus rentals to fix and flips. All along the way, I have looked at ways technology could help me invest.   As a certified millennial and real estate investor, it doesn't get much better then Airbnb.  

Here is a little more about me:

I was born and raised in Akron, Ohio, went to The Ohio State University and lived in Ohio for the first 26 years of my life. So I guess you might say I am a good 'ol midwestern boy but with one caveat, I inherited the traveling gene from my parents. It is hard keeping up with those two, they have visited all 50 states and are now retirees traveling the world. 

In 2013, on a surprisingly sunny February day in Columbus, OH, while dressed in head to toe denim for a charity bar crawl, I met my now wife, Danica (see, Ohio is for lovers ;-). Together we decided to move to California where we currently reside.  

Today, I fulfill my desire for technology as a Technical Project Manager while expanding my experience as a remote real estate investor. 

My other interests include:

- Competitive sports (mostly basketball).
- Exercise (but only so I can keep up with my wife).
- Experiencing new things, especially food (yes, I am a foodie).
- Hanging out with friends and family.

As I head into my 30's I am looking forward to growing my presence on Airbnb. I am excited for the experiences that I will have and the people I will meet as both a host and a guest.

summary: Built in 1870, our home is located across from Schiller Park in the heart of German Village, just minutes from the best restaurants and book shops in Columbus.    The house is very comfortable but its 9 ft ceilings make it feel grand!  Three living spaces occupy the main floor including a cook's kitchen/dining area opening out onto the garden patio. The walled garden is designed as a series of outdoor rooms & the attached carport serves as an 'al dente' covered dining room.   Enjoy!

neighborhood_overview: German Village is an historic neighborhood developed in the mid-1800's by German immigrants who moved to Columbus to work in the breweries along the river, now known as the Brewery District.  Brick streets are lined with brick cottages and larger Italianate and Queen Anne houses, intermingled with great restaurants and shops.  Schiller Park is the heart and soul of German Village with a recreation center, public gardens, tennis courts, a ball field and an outdoor amphitheater for summer plays.
notes: Although the house is fully air conditioned, you will find ceiling fans throughout the house for open fresh air living and sleeping if you choose.  Help yourselves to the fully stocked kitchen or dine outside with the charcoal Weber grill in the carport for a peaceful reprieve from the many wonderful restaurants and bars in the Village.
transit: German Village is a walking neighborhood, 15 minutes from the Statehouse or a 30 minute walk to the Short North.  The COTA bus line runs continually connecting German Village to downtown, the Short North and Ohio State, with bus stops on Reinhard and  Whittier Streets at Mohawk Street - steps from the house.  There is also COGO bike share bikes located in Schiller Park as well as Car 2 Go car share vehicles always close by.
access: You’ll have full access to all parts of the house so we hope you'll make youself comfortable!  We love to cook and have a well equipped kitchen that is yours for full during your stay....Bon Appetit!
interaction: We will meet you upon arrival to introduce you to the house and answer any questions. It’s a great house in a great location!  You will have your own smart lock access code for easy access to the house at all times, so no keys to deal with.  And street parking is always available.
house_rules: - While small dinner parties are welcome, late outdoor noise travels and all neighboring houses are very close.  Must be respectful and aware of outdoor noise  (the neighbors will be listening!).
host_about: Brooke and I are design professionals and we travel for business and for fun.   We are life-long-learners and readers, nature lovers and art enthusiasts who love to connect with family, friends and locals in the cultural fabric of any community, close to theatre, parks, museums and restaurants - which is why we live where we do and travel whenever we can.  Life is good!

neighborhood_overview: Stretching north from Ohio State to Worthington, Clintonville is a large neighborhood with many attractions, from the Park of Roses to the independently owned retail shops and restaurants that line High Street. Standout shops include modern decor purveyor Elm and Iron, fabric mecca Sew to Speak and all-locally made Wholly Craft.  During warmer months, people flock to the Clintonville Farmers Market to get fresh produce and to the Olentangy River recreational trail to hike and bike. Arts venues like Wild Goose Creative and Studio 35 provide cultural opportunities year-round.  Start your day with a cup of coffee at Cup O' Joe or Crimson Cup, both on the Columbus Coffee Trail. Dining choices veer toward farm-to-table, with Acre, Harvest Pizzeria, The Crest Gastropub and Angry Bear Kitchen as standouts. Get in line for world-class barbecue at the Ray Ray’s Hog Pit truck, at live music hotspot Ace of Cups.  Learn some new skills amid a gorgeous setting at The Seasoned Farmhouse. Grab a deli

host_about: Hi, I'm Tommy!  I met my wife Errin here in Columbus, OH.  We're proud to call this our home.  We enjoy a wide range of activities that Columbus has to offer.  Including riding our bikes on one of the many scenic bike paths offered around town; going to a Clippers or Blue Jackets game, Ohio State University football tailgating; grabbing a bite to eat at a Cameron Mitchell Restaurant; and my wife loves to shop at Easton Town Center and Tanger Outlets. I love a good book.  I spend my Saturday mornings on my front porch with a book in hand and a cup of coffee.  My favorite travel destination is Washington DC because I love history and could spend hours at the Museum.  My wife prefers the sunshine, warm sand, and the smell of the ocean. We hope that you choose our home during your stay.  We have put a lot of careful thought into the details to make it a home away from home whether you're a business traveler or in town for pleasure.

neighborhood_overview: Blue Silk Guesthouse is a located in a quiet neighborhood of mid-century ranch homes. It is a well-kept residential area.
notes: Because we travel regularly, we have paid attention to what makes a stay comfortable, practical, and enjoyable. Each bedroom has wall hooks, closet space with felt hangers, and a mirror (The queen bedrooms even have magnifying mirrors) We hope you will enjoy!
transit: Right off of I-71, Blue Silk Guesthouse is located seven miles from the Columbus Convention Center, five miles from the Ohio State Fairgrounds, nine miles from Polaris Shopping District, and five miles from the Horseshoe Stadium and the center of OSU Campus! Ubering is easy and public bus routes run nearby.
access: Coded lock entrance means you can let yourself in. You have access to the entire house and yard.  The house comes with WiFi, full kitchen, cutlery, dishes, pots & pans, both a Keurig and coffee pot, parking in the garage (upon request) or on the private driveway, heat & AC, linens & towels, basic toiletries, hair dryer, 1 Smart TV, toys and games, and complimentary washer, dryer and ironing space in the basement.
interaction: We live 10 months of the year in Cambodia. The Blue Silk Guesthouse is hosted by our son and daughter-in-law, who live a few houses down. You will have a completely private stay, but Meri and Josh will be available if questions arise or if anything is needed during your stay.
host_about: My husband and I spend 10 months each year in Cambodia, working with Cambodians and a multi-national team, running a mission hospital. We came in 2002 with our 4 children who are all grown now. I am an artist/ art teacher/ and non-profit development worker and Tim is a medical doctor, and the director of the hospital. Our work takes to many interesting places, but home base is Ohio, where our kids reside at this time. We love good coffee and quiet places to rest, read, reflect and walk. We speak Khmer and English fluently. Recently, we were able to buy a home in Ohio again. Having enjoyed the hospitality of many people around the world, we are happy to share our own place as well!

Rooms have mini-split zoned air conditioning and heating, so you can be comfy in any room of the house.

neighborhood_overview: Westgate is a historic neighborhood just ten minutes west of downtown Columbus. Walk the quiet, tree-lined streets to view charming homes, or hop in your car to quickly access night-life, entertainment, sporting events, shopping and more.
transit: Columbus is the perfect driving city. Rent a car or drive your own for the ultimate freedom in this extremely drivable city. Use the C-Bus to get up and down High Street once you're downtown, or Uber just about anywhere. If you love biking, our bike trails are beautiful, and you can ride some trails from one end of the city to the other.
interaction: We live less than 1/2 hr away and my husband will be available for any maintenance issues.  But since the house has been fully renovated in last 3 years there should be no problems.
house_rules: - Quiet hours 11pm to 8 am.
host_about:
My husband and I are a 48 year "design-build team."  Basically, we find a home with lots of potential, I have tons of design ideas and then he does all the hard work of bringing it to life. 

This home was supposed to be our final project, but instead we are currently looking forward to our next adventure:  building an addition to  our youngest son's house so we can enjoy his family in a small farming community outside the city. So we find ourselves in the exciting position of living in a home that we custom renovated to suit ourselves perfectly in our golden years and leaving it to spend more time with the grandkids.  It's just how things work sometimes, and we couldn't be happier with our decision!

So even with the prospect of our new house we couldn't bear the thought of selling this one that we poured so much effort into so we decided to set up an Airbnb  and allow others to enjoy it when they visit our city, and to feel the same happiness we have felt in our peaceful home. 

I have been sewing since I was a little girl, and my passion for quilting is something that has grown over the last twenty years or so.  Much of the house is decorated with quilts made by me and I hope you use them and enjoy them during your stay. 

When I travel, I like the space I stay in to feel warm, comfortable and clean, and I hope each of my guests feels the same way when they visit. We've updated our home to truly feel like an "urban oasis". We love that we are just a convenient 10 minutes from downtown Columbus, but that our home feels tucked quietly in the heart of a charming, small-town neighborhood.

name: Cozy Short North apartment right off HIGH STREET
summary: Originally a hotel. Located right in the heart of Columbus Night-Life. In the historic short  north/campus both 1 block from my apartment.  My unit is the largest it features a kitchen right when you walk in followed by a living room and bedroom. This building is a 1 flight walk-up corner unit. On the back side of the building a patio great for smokers also with a grill.  My apartment is cozy and good for people wanting to experience the night life and not drive anywhere. Can fit up to 4people.
space: Remaining unique there are still radiator heaters out the floor but they do not work. I feel it give the apartment  character. Being a corner unit natural light flow into both the living room and bedroom. It's a full size bed in the bedroom and a full size futon. I also have a mini pool table in the apartment for activities. Place is great for one person but not more then 4. I did have a cat in my last apartment but are not allowed pets in this apartment or I get fined. So no cat lives on the property. He lives with my Ex. Rest assured I steam the floors and bleach counter tops and fridge after every visit.

neighborhood_overview: Living here is amazing with over 50 different Restaurants/bars/boutiques starting from the corner of my building to over 5 blocks walking. I'm only 6 blocks from the Greater Columbus Convention Center. And 1 block from Kroger Market place. 3 blocks from The Ohio State University.  6 minute Uber/lift downtown ($6.65 each way). Also 5blocls from the beautiful Goodale Park.  It's so amazing everything is in walking distance when it's warm. Every first Saturday now through Sept is Gallery Hop a gathering of people who browse High Street and go into Art Studios where there is normally wine tasting and street performers.
notes: UPON CHECK-IN Popsicles, snacks, water, coffee. There is everything within reach of my door step. Food, drinks, brewery's, and art galleries and a grocery store.  I'm only a phone call or email away and will be so full of knowledge of things to do. Don't hesitate to ask
transit: Most places are walking distance. Uber is 6-7 min ride downtown to the Columbus Commons. You can also catch the COTA our city bus $2.50 or there is a Cbus which is free stop is also around corner from my building on High Street
access: On the back side of the building there is a shared patio. All tenants of the building use them. There is a locked door to get into the building. There is no cable or kitchen table the apartment is small but there is a large glass end table. Wifi will be connected next week.
interaction: I am available always by text, call or email. I will normally meet with you to give you the keys show you the property or my cousin will. I have been home to Columbus for 15 years any questions I will be more then happy to help. Suggest food/bars/parks/shows
house_rules: Do not get in the closet in bedroom it will be a separate cabinet for your belongings. Leave keys on fridge for checkout after stay before leaving.
host_about: I'm 30 . I'm a server/bartender getting promoted to management. I am at the age where I'm wanting to travel more instead of being blackout wasted every weekend in my own town. I love Broadway shows and fancy dinners I'm into the good life now and still fun just more responsible.  I look forward to being able to occupie your location for my travels. My recent motto has been. Uplift everyone you come in contact with. You never know what someone is going through. Do kind be kind get kind.

Guests will also have access to the fenced in patio.  Guests can park on the street; it’s quiet and literally right across my street.
interaction: Since guests dictate how much or how little they would like to interact with me, if certain guests would like to be social and include me that is fine and for those guests who want to be independent and do their own thing that is also fine as well.
house_rules: No slamming doors, keep it quiet for other guests. Coordinate with me or other guests for bathroom times and leave the bathroom door opened or cracked when your done. Please remove your shoes at the door. Feel free to help yourself to the wine, beer, snack and food items in the kitchen WITH THE UNDERSTANDING THAT YOU SHALL LEAVE GROCERY MONEY ON THE COUNTER for me to replace the items that you enjoyed. Please ONLY eat in the dining and/or kitchen areas.  Feel free to use the gas grill located on the back patio. Simply clean it after you are finished using it, the wire brush hanging on the right side of the closet that is by the front door. Lastly, this is not a house to host a party. I would suggest using another venue to host your party.  -- SOME LEGAL PRINT TO READ: Smoking, house parties, and rowdy behavior are not permitted on the property. The area is known for its Victorian houses, which were built when a streetcar line first ran along Neil Avenue around 1900. Centrally located, no part of Columbus is more than 15-20 minutes away. The brick paver streets complete the neighborhood giving it an early 1900's vibe.

space: Historic 1850’s Italianate brick building, located in the downtown east sector of Columbus.  This spacious first floor, one bedroom apartment ( 1400 square feet.) comes with one off-street parking space.  It includes all new furnishings. It is a short Uber ride to The Franklin Park Conservatory,  German Village,  OSU stadium, Mapfre stadium, COSI and The Short North.

name: Level Two Studio @ Short North & OSU
summary: A new listing from experienced Airbnb hosts, Level Two is a renovated second floor studio apartment with a private outside entrance, located between the Short North Arts District and Ohio State University.  Ask about parking if you need it - we may have one space available for a small additional fee.  Window AC unit in the bedroom for the summer.  Part of the building is being renovated and the entrance is outside up a metal exterior staircase - please read all of the details before booking.
space: This is a recently updated studio apartment (open doorway between the kitchen and bedroom) on the second floor of a vintage building on a quiet street, right between OSU and the popular Short North Arts District - walk to campus, shops, night life, and restaurants!  Part of this building is currently being renovated, and there may be some construction noise from 9 am to 7 pm.  If you need quiet during those hours, this is not the best place for you.  This space is closed off from the construction areas and the dust.  We do not allow parties and request that noise is kept to a minimum after 9pm to respect our neighbors. ***** The bedroom has a new queen memory foam mattress and can sleep two guests.  There is a TV on a shelf in the bedroom, with a digital TV tuner (no cable, just local channels) and a (Hidden by Airbnb) Chromecast, so you can watch Netflix and stream video using your own accounts. neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is in the perfect location between Ohio State and the Short North. Our street and the nearby ones have some beautiful grand Victorian homes. This neighborhood draws a healthy blend of graduate students, young professionals, and families. Many of the grand Victorian homes have been split up into multiple units, like this one!
notes: -There is laundry in the basement that can be made available for guests staying seven or more nights.  -There are two cats that live in the other part of this building.  They never go inside the Airbnb (and please don't let them) but you might see them ou
transit: Here are just a few of the places you can easily get to on foot - actual WALKING times: ~3 minutes to Junior's Tacos (food truck at 5th and Highland) ~3 minutes to Angry Baker (coffee shop), the Bottle Shop (bar), and Hamptons on King (bar) ~5 minutes to High Street (North High Brewing, Condado Tacos, Paulie Gee's Pizza, Kroger grocery store, and more bars, shopping, and restaurants) ~10 minutes to Ohio State's central campus ~15 minutes to Wexner Medical Center ~20 minutes to Ohio Stadium ~30 minutes to Express Live ~30 minutes to Columbus Convention Center ~30 minutes to Nationwide Arena
access: Check-in time is 5:00 pm.  On the day of your arrival, if you have not heard from us by 4:00 pm, please send us a message on Airbnb and we'll get back to you quickly.  Please send this message through Airbnb (instead of texting or calling directly) so that we will all see the message. We'll provide the code to the keypad lock as soon as the place is ready.
house_rules: It's very important to us that you have a great stay and that you take good care of our house. If you have any issues during your stay, please let us know right away so we can address them! We live nearby and we want to make sure your stay is excellent.  Here are a few rules that you can follow to make us happy hosts. Rule 1: be respectful and leave the space as clean as you found it. We reserve the right to assess additional fees for cleaning or damages if these rules are not followed. Hopefully this is pretty basic stuff, but we want to be clear about how we expect our space to be used. This is not a hotel or a place to throw a party. Trash & Recycling: Use the bins provided throughout the apartment. Do not leave any trash around the space. If you generate more trash than will fit in the bins, throw it away in the big bins in the alley behind the house.  Blue for recycling. Smoking/Drugs/Parties: No smoking. Please go outside to the back yard. Leave no evidence. No drugs or parties.
host_about: Hi, I'm Nat!  I'm a long time Columbus resident - raised in the Short North (between downtown and campus) graduated from Ohio State, and settled in the Short North after living in Indianapolis and Chicago for a while. I care very much about the neighborhood and the properties that I manage. For my day job, I'm an IT consultant, but on the weekends I like to spend my free time renovating and managing properties.  I live with my wife Kate in the Short North, between Ohio State's campus and downtown Columbus.

name: Olde Towne East: 10 min to all Cbus hot spots!
summary: Beautifully updated home in the historic, charming Olde Town East neighborhood! A convenient, central location only a 10 minute ride to Downtown, the Ohio Theater, historic German Village, and the Short North! 15 minutes from the Ohio State University and Port Columbus airport. You will have a private bedroom with a queen size bed & your own private bathroom.
space: This 1800 sq ft home was built in 1900 and had a major face-lift in 2018. Home includes hardwood floors, a fireplace, and large windows with lots of natural light. Updated open kitchen with granite counters and stainless steel appliances. Laundry available. Large fenced in back yard with a grill. Plenty of free on street parking. There are popular (and delicious) local bar/restaurants only a 10 minute walk from the house: Yellow Brick Pizza, Angry Baker, Olde Town Tavern, and Camelot Cellars Winery.

host_about:
Welcome to my Buckeye Retreat. As a frequent traveler I understand the complexities of traveling both for work and pleasure. 

Traveling with children and staying in a hotel was always complicated and staying in hotels for work can become monotonous. 

So .... I decided to start an airbnb to make traveling easier and more comfortable for others. 

I am proud to be able to provide safe, clean and reasonably priced lodging for people visiting my beautiful city. 

I hope you enjoy my house and Columbus as much as I do.

name: Beautiful, Cozy Room near Nationwide Children's
summary: Welcome to Columbus! We're Kelli & Teno and we live with our 2 dogs in Historic Southern Orchards just a few blocks from Nationwide Children's Hospital & Livingston Park. Everything you need is within minutes of our home including shopping, dining, and transit access. This is the perfect space for visiting medical professionals! **Please read all details carefully** If you'd like to book both bedrooms, visit: https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/26462596?s=51
space: Fully renovated home with open concept floor plan and lots of natural light. Spacious kitchen, Laundry access and fenced in back yard. Very clean and tidy. Plenty of street parking available. This is 1 of 2 bedrooms listed in our home. You'll have a private bedroom with a twin size bed and closet located on the second floor. The bathroom is also on the second floor and may be shared if both bedrooms are booked at the same time. You will have a lock & key to your bedroom.  Alexa/Sonos Speaker available in the living room. Enjoy some tunes while you cook a tasty meal in the kitchen.  We are open to pets on a case by case basis. Please send a message before booking if you are interested in bringing your pet along with you.

neighborhood_overview: Southern Orchards is a diverse neighborhood experiencing a lot of revitalization due to the Nationwide Children's Expansion.  Our home is just 10 minutes from the airport and right around the corner from Nationwide Children's Hospital and Livingston Park. Minutes from Franklin Park, Historic German Village, Schiller Park, and the Short North Arts District. There is a Panera Bread, CVS, Fitness Center, and multiple restaurants within walking distance.
notes: We're early risers and typically wake between 6-7:30am. We have 2 friendly dogs, Rainey & Anya. Depending on how light you sleep you may hear us briefly in the morning when we let the dogs out and get ready for the day. We try to keep the noise level to a minimum and tend to let the dogs spend more time outside when guests are here, weather permitting. They also sleep in our bedroom at night. They love meeting new people and will happily interact with you. We hope you’re an animal lover!  We have another bedroom listed that shares a bathroom with this listing. It is possible that there may be other guests in the home. Please feel free to ask whether the other room will be booked during your stay. For the safety of you and your belongings, you will have a lock & key to your bedroom. Master Bedroom and our Personal Office Space are not available for guest use.
transit: Getting around is super easy! Street parking is available on our street right in front of the house. There is a COTA bus stop and COGO Bike Share Station just a few blocks from us. Zipcar, LimeBike, Uber, and Lyft also available. I-70/I-71 and 670 are easily accessible.
access: Private Bedroom and either Private or Shared Bathroom depending on whether or not the other bedroom is booked. Half bathroom located on the first floor. You're welcome to use common areas including the kitchen plus all utensils and appliances, living room, and washer/dryer.  There is a large flat-screen TV with DVD's, video games, and a PS3 stored in a closet on a roller cart. Play a video game or watch some Netflix. Feel free to hang out in the back yard and enjoy your morning cup of coffee or tea!
interaction: We live on-site and will be available for questions and recommendations. You'll have space and privacy, but we're happy to hangout if you would like. Level of interaction is entirely up to each guest's preference. You're more than welcome to share the common spaces alongside us. If you need anything when we're not home, please feel free to shoot us a text or send a message in the Airbnb app.

host_about:
Hey! I'm Kelli. I'm a Social Worker and Aspiring Entrepreneur working on starting a business. I love traveling, food, tea, wine, and animals. I'm also a nature lover and enjoy peace & quiet. 

My husband and I, along with our 2 dogs, Rainey & Anya, enjoy opening our home to others and meeting new people. We want you to feel welcome and at home. We love hearing about our guests' travels and are open to interacting as much as you would like. Feel free to join us in the kitchen and cook alongside us, or in the living room on the rare occasion we pull the tv out and watch Netflix. Let us know if you need any recommendations for places to eat and see. We enjoy sharing what we love about this new city we now call home!

transit: I’d say the majority of people in Columbus have a car and get around that way. name: Guest Room on Private Floor near OSU & Short North
summary: You'll have a private floor (the first floor) all to yourself in our Italian Village home. Parking on street is free. You'll be across the street from an Italian eatery, around the corner from a bustling coffee shop and a five-minute walk to the Short North, where you'll find restaurants, boutique shops and galleries. The Convention Center is 1 mile, Nationwide Arena and Express Live 1.5 miles and Ohio Stadium 2 miles. Business travelers, couples and solo adventures will feel at home.
space: We love living in Italian Village and love our modern home. The first floor of our home is all yours. The private bedroom is connected to a full private bathroom. In the room you'll find a queen-sized bed, a mini-frig, and a TV connected with a Roku streaming device where you can watch content from many cable channels. On the second floor is our kitchen, living room and dining room. You'll find plenty of free street parking.

neighborhood_overview: The Short North is less than a five-minute walk where you'll find many restaurants, bars, boutique shops and galleries.
transit: Uber and Lyft is about $6 to most popular destinations and $15-20 to and from the airport. The free COTA Cbus stop is only a few steps from our home and will take you south on High Street, to the Convention Center, Nationwide Arena, Columbus Commons and German Village.
access: You'll have the entire first floor to yourself, which includes a bedroom with a queen bed and a connected full bathroom. You'll have access to our high speed wifi, clean towels and linens, shampoo, soap and lotion. You are welcome to use the microwave in the kitchen on our second floor. You're also welcome to the Keurig and Kcup options we have in the morning.
interaction: This is our home, so we'll be around and are happy to interact as little or as much as you want. We'll greet you when you arrive to give you a key so you can come and go as you please. One of us works from home and will be in the home office most of the day if you need anything. We've lived in the neighborhood for years and would be happy to share things to do, restaurant and happy hour recommendations.
house_rules: - Please remove your shoes at the door. - Please smoke outside on the front porch.  - Weekday quite hours from 11 p.m. to 7 a.m.
host_about: My husband Mike and I love having a home to call our own in Italian Village. We've lived in the neighborhoods in the heart of Columbus - Short North, Victorian Village and Italian Village - for 10 years. We enjoy cheering on the Buckeyes during football season and going to both new and our favorite restaurants and bars in the lively Short North.

neighborhood_overview: Being so close to the university, our neighborhood is diverse and welcoming for all life styles and life choices.The area went through a period of significant urban decay during the 1960s and 1970s. In recent years, the area has experienced a complete renaissance--both with preserving older buildings and constructing new ones. We expect this trend to continue in the years ahead.
notes: Please note that we are a liberal gay couple. We welcome all visitors to our home, be they straight, lesbian, gay, or transgender. In a similar spirit, we weclome visitors from all over the world to stay in our home. We travel internationally extensively and never tire of learning about new peoples and cultures. That said, we are not obtrusive. We take our cue from our guests as to how much they would like to interact with us during their stay. Also note that we have two bichons, Sam and Sadie, and a tuxedo cat, Joey. All three have the run of the house. That said, the room might not be appropriate for someone with severe cat allergies. We have excellent cleaners who prepare everything for your arrival. However, it is almost impossible to get rid of all vestiges of cat dander. The bichons are hypoallergenic, so there should be no issues there.
transit: Bicycles are for rent a block away. They are an excellent way to get to know the neighborhood. And remember, this is the Midwest, no mountains. The room comes with an on-street parking pass. But perhaps the best way to get to know the neighborhood is to walk it! It is eminently walkable, and every street and corner includes surprises—whether they’re open markets, shops, or just the eclectic people you meet! Urban living at its best!

neighborhood_overview: Southern Orchards is a diverse neighborhood experiencing a lot of revitalization due to the Nationwide Children's Expansion.  Our home is just 10 minutes from the airport and right around the corner from Nationwide Children's Hospital and Livingston Park. Minutes from Franklin Park, Historic German Village, Schiller Park, and the Short North Arts District. There is a Panera Bread, CVS, Fitness Center, and multiple restaurants within walking distance.
notes: We're early risers and typically wake between 6-7:30am. We have 2 friendly dogs, Rainey & Anya. Depending on how light you sleep you may hear us briefly in the morning when we let the dogs out and get ready for the day. We try to keep the noise level to a minimum and tend to let the dogs spend more time outside when guests are here, weather permitting. They also sleep in our bedroom at night. They love meeting new people and will happily interact with you. We hope you’re an animal lover!  You will have a lock & key to each bedroom.  Master Bedroom and our Personal Office Space are not available for guest use.
transit: Getting around is super easy! Street parking is available on our street right in front of the house. There is a COTA bus stop and COGO Bike Share Station just a few blocks from us. Zipcar, LimeBike, Uber, and Lyft also available. I-70/I-71 and 670 are easily accessible.
access: Two Private Bedrooms and Bathroom. Additional half bathroom located on the first floor. You're welcome to use common areas including the kitchen plus all utensils and appliances, living room, and washer/dryer.  There is a large flat-screen TV with DVD's, video games, and a PS3 stored in a closet on a roller cart. Play a video game or watch some Netflix. Feel free to hang out in the back yard and enjoy your morning cup of coffee or tea!
interaction: We live on-site and will be available for questions and recommendations. You'll have space and privacy, but we're happy to hangout if you would like. Level of interaction is entirely up to each guest's preference. You're more than welcome to share the common spaces alongside us. If you need anything when we're not home, please feel free to shoot us a text or send a message in the Airbnb app.

name: Great Tuttle Crossing Community!
space: The Pines at Tuttle Crossing is much more than a place to live. It is a community, and an oasis of calm in the heart of bustling Central Ohio. It is a place where children play, families flourish and trees and parks abound. A place where quality of life is the only thing that really counts. In many ways The Pines is one of the most unique apartment communities around because it is in a location where the options to live, work and play meet the needs of everyone. Convenient, desirable location close to modern restaurants, shops, and Tuttle Crossing Mall. Feel at home in our comfortable, quiet setting. Easy access to highways, main commuting routes, and bus routes. Everything you desire in minutes! Come experience our exquisite clubhouse with many resident benefits. Work out in our well-equipped Fitness Center or use our Media Parlor for a private viewing of the latest movies or sports games. Warm up with a hot cup of Starbucks coffee or cocoa and lounge in our relaxing common room.

summary: It’s the ideal retreat for a comfortable city stay, located in the Historical Northwood Park District. We believe it’s the ultimate location to experience The University District; amongst tree lined streets just minutes from The Shoe, Bars, Restaurants, Live Music, Parks, and more! Our street ends at the 13 mile Olentangy bike trail, which follows the river all the way to Downtown.
space: Perfectly suitable for all-season trips. This superbly styled one bedroom apartment is a perfect getaway. Ideal for business travelers, parents visiting students, Buckeye fans, those visiting for a show, or couples looking for a “home away from home”.  Brand new luxury mattress, pillows, linens, furniture, and supplies as of July 2018!  Comfortable and cozy, right in the middle of a tree lined street 1/3 of a mile from Campus. Calm and convenient. We love to go that extra mile so you feel like you are at home.  We’ll supply you with: -High-end bed Linen -Towels -Toiletries -High speed WiFi -Fully updated kitchen stocked with tools needed to prepare your own meals. Just bring the food, we've got the rest covered! -Coffee -Tea The house functions as a duplex, the two units are separated by an always locked door. We happily share the front and back yard. We guarantee an absolutely private stay while inside your apartment. No sharing, no disturbances while inside.

neighborhood_overview: This property is amazing all year round for a visit to to the University District. Steps away from Ohio State University, directly connected to Olentangy river and Olentangy Bike Trail at the end of the street. Northwood Park Historical District is a beautiful, interesting and diverse part of Columbus where families, students, artists, OSU Professors reside. Houses built between 1905 and 1920 remain completely intact to this day. A variety of styles can be seen on Oakland and Northwood Avenues with four-square being the most common. These streets are regularly referred to as some of the most beautiful in Columbus. As for entertainment, just a few of the many options in the area include:  - Theaters · Gate Way Film Center · AMC Lennox · Studio 35 Cinema and Draft House - Music Venues · Express live · Space bar · The Newport · Rambling House · Ace of Cups · Dicks Den · Many more smaller venues within walking distance, tell us your taste in music and we can make some suggestions! -Cafes ·
notes: Living room amenities - Fully Furnished & exquisitely designed - Toshiba SMART TV with Amazon Fire stick and a Netflix account ready for your use -Four place Cherry table  -Comfortable microfiber couch that doubles as an extra sleeping space. Comfortable for those 6' and under to sleep on. Kitchen -New stainless steel appliances -Keurig and Coffee K Cups  -Variety of Tea bags -Quick boil electric kettle -New dish ware, eating and cooking utensils, knife set, and pots/pans Bedroom - Extremely comfortable queen sized bed in the bedroom - High-end bed linen  -Desk with comfortable chair and light -Large dresser -Wardrobe with hangers  -Comfortable couch and air mattress ready for your use as additional sleeping space. Couch is comfortable for sleeping someone up to around 6 feet. Please note, the air mattress takes up much of the space in the living room/takes away from functionality. Apartment is most enjoyable using the primary queen bed and couch as sleeping space but the mattress and
transit: Cota bus line 1/4 mile down the street, Uber, Bicycle friendly city. We have one one off street parking spot that will fit small SUV's/cars. It's 10' wide by 17' long, it will not accommodate larger vehicles! For larger vehicles, you'll have to park near on Adam's Ave 1/2 block down and walk up as our street is permit parking only.
access: You have access to the entire exterior of the home and your one bedroom apartment on the first floor which includes a private kitchen and a private full bath.
interaction: We will be happy to tailor to all of your needs during your stay to make your trip to Columbus an unforgettable one. neighborhood_overview: The University District represents modern ideas and century old traditions, preservation and renewal, urban living and secluded wooded hollows. The University District is comprised of the neighborhoods surrounding one of the nation's larget public universities, The Ohio State University. It is an eclectic mix of thirteen distinct neighborhoods: Dennison Place/The Circles, Glen Echo, Indianola Forest, Indianola Terrace, Iuka Ravine, Northwood Park, Old North Columbus, Peach District, Sohud, Tuttle Park, and Weinland Park. The area now known as the University District was not originally part of the City of Columbus at all. In 1842, out of expansive farmland emerged a separate town, North Columbus. Even before the establishment of The Ohio State University, which was first established in 1871 as the Ohio Agricultural and Mechanical College, North Columbus thrived as a transportation node for stagecoaches travelling between Columbus and Sandusky. It existed on its own until it was official
notes: Dining options range from student-centric to upscale; find a variety of options around High Street and 11th Avenue. The Wexner Center for the Arts showcases rotating modern art exhibitions, and also hosts a huge variety of events, ranging from music, theater and dance performances to film screenings and artist talks. Across the plaza, the free Billy Ireland Cartoon Museum has the largest collection of cartoons and comics in the world, and features rotating exhibitions of historic, classic and modern comics.

transit: I have private parking in my backyard, or you can park for free on the street. A car is recommended but ride sharing services are readily accessible and easy to use. Zipcar is nearby as well. Bus lines take you everywhere and there’s a stop right across the street.
access: You’ll have your own private entrance to the top two floors through the side door. I live in the downstairs unit and access my home through the front door, which you will not have access to.

name: Cozy  1BR apartment in Grandview
summary: Feel like you're a local in this 2nd floor apartment situated in the centrally located neighborhood of Grandview Heights! You're minutes away from Grandview Avenue (restaurants, bars, coffee shops, and boutiques).  It's a 5 minute drive to Downtown Columbus, Short North, the Horseshoe, Convention Center, Nationwide Arena, and the Arena District! There's a free parking space in the back of the apartment building, and street parking in the front.
space: The apartment is located on the second floor of an apartment building.  The apartment doesn't include central air- however there is a portable AC unit that you have full thermostatic control of in the living room as well as a window AC unit in the bedroom! There is a parking pad out back. You are allotted 1 parking space. There is also free parking in the front of the building on the street.

name: Beautiful New Albany Condo.
summary: They only give me 500 charters so I have to make make this short. Text or call me with any questions. Common space includes the backyard/porch, and laundry room. There is also free access to upgraded gym (see picture), pool, and newer washer and dryer. If you smoke that is fine just please do it outside.
space: We are minutes away from 161 and 270, shops,  Easton and walking distance to Giant Eagle, Kroger, Wendy's, Burger King, Taco Bell, Panera, The Goat, Tim Hortons, Jets Pizza, Rooster, UPS, Bob Evans, Wallgreens, Huntington and Chase bank. We are about 15 min. from everything downtown including the Shotenstein Center, Express Live, Cossi, The Arena District, The Arnold Classic, Rock on the Range!, Huntington Park (Columbus Clippers).  There is a microwave and small fridge in the room, laundry room, work desk, high speed internet (100 Mbps), TV with Amazon firestick (Netflix). There is a coffee maker in the room and coffee along with some breakfast bars and things like that for breakfast. This is the perfect location for people coming to an event, work or on a fun road trip. If you need to stay for a short period of time, more than a day, text or call me and we can work something out. If you have more than 2 people that is fine as the room is big just reach out to me so we can discuss the

name: Modern Apartment in beautiful Grandview!
space: Modern apartment close to downtown! Take a dip in the pool, enjoy a coffee on the balcony, and relax.
description: Modern apartment close to downtown! Take a dip in the pool, enjoy a coffee on the balcony, and relax. Shared pool, outdoor grill, and workout facility. I am available for questions by text, call or email. Grandview is constantly growing with restaurants, bars, parks and much more! You can walk to Endeavor Brewery and cheer on the soccer match. Order delicious meatballs at Palle. Watch a movie at Grandview theater. And top your night off with frozé at Grandview Cafe or a delicious ice cream cone at Jeni’s! Grandview is easy to navigate by car, uber, lyft, bike or bus. Located just outside beautiful Columbus, you will be ten minutes from Short North, Arena District, German Village and The Ohio State University.

name: Central: OSU, Arena District & Downtown
summary: Quiet, safe, & centrally located apartment (free parking & pool) in the Victorian Village neighborhood of Downtown. Walking distance (roughly ten minutes) to the Arena District (Nationwide Arena & Huntington Park baseball field) and the Short North where all of the boutiques, restaurants, bars, lounges, & more are located. A short drive (five minutes) or walk (fifteen to twenty minutes) to the Ohio State University campus and sporting facilities. I may be able to accommodate up to four guests.
space: The apartment is spacious, featuring an open-concept layout kitchen (stocked with essentials) and living room that overlooks the pool (and includes a balcony). The bedroom offers a very comfortable queen-size antique mahogany poster bed (over one hundred years old, don't worry it does not make a noise) with large closet and Roku television (only internet television, no cable). The bathroom is shared with the owner of the unit (a law student and multi-property Airbnb owner).

neighborhood_overview: The Victorian Village is one of Columbus's most historic and affluent neighborhoods, featuring beautiful tree-lined streets, parks, and large Victorian manor houses (some well-over one hundred years old). It is a quiet and safe neighborhood that is centrally located within downtown. It's location puts its residences almost in the heart of everything Columbus has to offer.
transit: The apartment is walking distances to pretty much everything--even the OSU if you are someone who enjoys walking. The OSU campus is only a few minutes drive away. Outside of that, guests can utilize Uber, Lyft, and other car-sharing services.
access: Guests have access to all areas except the owner's bedroom and closet (which is, in a way, attached to the bathroom--think Sarah Jessica Parker's "Sex and the City" apartment).
interaction: As a law student, I may not be hanging around the apartment with you as I may be at school or work. However, I do go out all the time in the Short North and am more than happy to have guests join. Nonetheless, I am available for recommendations.
house_rules: Smoking is allowed, however it MUST be done on the balcony or somewhere else not inside the apartment or building. The apartment is also 420-friendly for those guests who know what that means--this MUST be done on the balcony or somewhere else not inside the apartment or building. Owner will not tolerate he use and misuse of hard drugs or prescription medicines anywhere.
